name: Whisk Patisserie
homepage_content: Welcome to Whisk Patisserie - Whisk Patisserie Welcome to Whisk Patisserie Step into Whisk Patisserie & Cafe, where the charm of a Parisian patisserie meets the warmth of your favourite neighbourhood cafe. Nestled in the heart of Goodwood, we are your go-to destination for exquisite pastries, artisanal desserts, and a perfectly brewed cup of coffee OUR DREAM At Whisk, our dream is to create unforgettable experiences through the art of patisserie, with a special focus on exquisite gateaux and celebration cakes. Every cake we craft tells a story, blending tradition with innovation bring you sweetest dreams to life. Using the finest ingredients and time-honoured techniques, we take pride in delivering cakes that elevate every occasion. Whether it’s a whole cake or an elegant gateau for an intimate gathering, we’re here to make your moments truly extraordinary. ALWAYS FRESH, SWEET & DELICIOUS FRESH BREAD BARISTA COFFEE DELICIOUS PASTRY Opening hours Monday 8am – 2pm Tuesday 8am – 2pm Wednesday 8am – 2pm Thursday 8am – 2pm Friday 8am – 2 pm Saturday 9am – 1pm Sunday – CLOSED Public Holidays – CLOSED Follow us on social media For the latest updates and specials on our products Facebook Whisk Patisserie Instagram @whiskpatisseriecafe Wholesale & Catering At Whisk Patisserie, we believe every bite should tell a story. Whether you’re a cafe, restaurant, or boutique looking for premium pastries or planning a special occasion that deserves unforgettable desserts, we’re here to help. How to Contact Us: We’d love to hear from you! For inquiries, please reach out via: Email: whiskpatisserie95@gmail.com Phone: 0474 096 048 Or to discuss in person visit us at our store: 95 Goodwood road. Goodwood. Let Whisk bring our signature flavours and handcrafted delights to your table. CAKE ORDER All our cakes are made to order with the utmost care and attention to detail. To ensure the highest quality and freshness, we kindly request orders be placed at least 48 hours in advance Whisk Patisserie Facebook Instagram Copyright © 2023 | WordPress Theme by SuperbThemes

name: Whyalla Wetlands
homepage_content: Whyalla South Australia for extraordinary Natural Wonders EXPLORE CUTTLEFEST Snorkel or dive with our Australian Giant Cuttlefish EXPLORE CUTTLEFEST Witness a globally unique phenomenon EXPLORE CUTTLEFEST Drive along the cuttlefish coastline EXPLORE CUTTLEFEST See the incredible cuttlefish themed art around Whyalla Whyalla, south australia Unearth unforgettable experiences; Whyalla offers natural wonders contrasted with industry in vivid landscapes, aquatic serenity, sea life and great adventures. Located on Eyre Peninsula’s Spencer Gulf in South Australia, Whyalla is an important hub and the region’s biggest city for retail shopping. Whyalla boasts a warm climate, accessible ocean shores and saltwater fishing. Whyalla represents South Australia’s foremost combination of industrial and nature-based experiences. With vivid scenery, small city charm, distinctive mystic outback landscapes and year-round things to do, Whyalla offers discovery, unique Australian natural wonders and absolute contrast in nature based and industrial activities. Activities that are significant to the landscape and geography of the region that will enthral and gratify those looking to unearth and experience learning, adventure time and witness unrivalled sights and happenings. Cuttlefest Be brave this winter, and unearth adventure. Discover a vibrant underwater world and witness a globally unique phenomenon. Living in Whyalla Whyalla is more than just a place to visit – it’s a city of opportunity that you’ll fall in love with and never want to leave. The Whyalla Jetty Take a self guided tour of the new Whyalla Jetty today Whyalla Visitor Centre Whyalla’s central location makes it easily accessible and ideally located for touring, holidaying and living a great lifestyle. Find out about travel and transport, weather, maps and more. Experience Whyalla Whyalla is famous for our captivating cuttlefish and dolphins, steelworks industry and nature based activities. Unearth natural wonders, experiences and landscapes. Book a tour Step aboard a WWII vessel built right here in Whyalla, Learn of steelmaking, ship building and the heritage of our beautiful region. You will be awed by the dramatic events and vivid colours and textures that shape Whyalla. Witness the spectacle the Whyalla steelworks and learn about the transformation of ore into steel; wonder at the antics of the local resident dolphins and feel the sand between your toes when searching for a delicious meal of fresh crab off the Whyalla Foreshore beach. Witness the camouflage and colourful mating rituals of Whyalla’s distinctive giant cuttlefish; Relax within the ocean and wonders of the unique Northern Coastline and beaches on the tranquil Spencer Gulf, set against backdrop of the ancient Southern Flinders Ranges. Check out the video below and discover some of the many reasons why you should Unearth Your Next Step in Whyalla! Share your favourite photos on Instagram , Facebook and Twitter with #unearthwhyalla talk to us about your next Holiday Whyalla Visitor Centre, Lincoln Highway Open: 7 days Mon–Fri 9am–4pm. Weekends and public holidays 10am–4pm. Closed: Good Friday and Christmas Day Phone: (08) 8645 7900 Email: visitor.centre@whyalla.sa.gov.au TOLL FREE: 1800 088 589 Contact us by filling out the form below and pressing "submit". name: 10/10 cafe
homepage_content: Home - 10/10 Cafe Skip to content Welcome to 10/10 Cafe Experience exquisite dining in a cozy ambiance Book Table Now or 0422 971 047 Our Story Our Journey and Commitment to Excellence Welcome to 10/10 Cafe where we combine top-notch coffee with delectable cuisine in a cozy setting that feels like home. Experience the perfect blend of flavors and comfort at 10/10 Cafe. Meet Our CHEF Sanjay JUNG SHAHI Sanjay, the heart and soul behind 10/10 Cafe, brings years of culinary expertise to create a dining experience like no other. Driven by a passion for exceptional food and service, Sanjay’s journey began with a vision of a place where taste meets warmth. Explore Our Dishes Taste the Flavors 1. Breakfast Toast Choice of sourdough, rye, soy, linseed or fruit toast with peanut butter/butter Eggs your way 2 free range eggs with sourdough bread Egg Benny Two free range eggs wilted spinach and mushroom, served with the choice of ham/bacon/salmon, and hollandaise sauce on a piece of sourdough 2. Lunch Steak sandwich Premium scotch fillet, lettuce tomato, cheese and caramelised onion, aioli chips or salad Beef Burger Grilled beef patty, bacon, cheese, lettuce, tomato, caramelised onion, pickles, mayo, mustrd sauce, chips Grilled chicken burger Grilled chicken thigh, lettuce, tomato, cheese, jalapeno, aioli and chips explore Menu Explore a world of flavors at 10/10 Cafe Book Table Now Our Customers Love Us ★ ★ ★ ★ ★ We had a great experience here, friendly service in a clean and modern space. The omelette was cooked perfectly and the coffee was the best I’ve tasted in Canberra. Highly recommended if you are in the area. Paul Leach ★ ★ ★ ★ ★ Friendly staff, good menu and decent coffee. The food was delicious and value for money. Lovely cafe will definitely return. Francis Fl Join Us Today Reserve your table now and experience the essence of fine dining with us. name: A1 Bakery
homepage_content: A1 Bakery 0 Authentic Lebanese bread, pies and pizza since 1992 . Brunswick-born. Family-owned. Loved across Melbourne. Find Your Store Three Iconic Locations A1 Brunswick 643-645 Sydney Rd. Brunswick Our birthplace and flagship store, where it all began. Explore Brunswick A1 Fitzroy 295 Brunswick St. Fitzroy Compact and convenient, ideal for a takeaway lunch. Explore Fitzroy A1 Highpoint L2 Highpoint Shopping Centre Fresh Middle Eastern bakery fare, ready to grab and go. Explore Highpoint A Middle-Eastern Grocery From pantry staples to hard-to-find ingredients, our grocery shelves are stocked with the flavours of home. Pick up zaatar, halva, olives, tahini, pickles, sweets and more — the same ingredients we use in our kitchen, ready for yours. Explore the Grocery Your All-Time Favourite Menu From zaatar and falafel to wraps, pizzas and platters — all your A1 favourites, made fresh and served with heart. Find Store Menus And Catering for any occasion Planning a gathering? We make it easy to feed a crowd. Choose from fresh pastries, mini pizzas, dips, falafel and more. All catering must be pre-ordered at least a day ahead. Explore Catering

name: Aboriginal Bush Traders
homepage_content: Aboriginal Bush Traders: Aboriginal Art gallery, retail store and cafe Skip to content Close menu Home Shop Café What's On Corporate Gifts Catering About Us Our History Artists & Suppliers Contact/FAQ's Log in Facebook Instagram WELCOME TO ABORIGINAL BUSH TRADERS A 100% not-for-profit organisation committed to selling ethically sourced and sustainable products that directly support local Indigenous communities. The story behind the Green Ant Logo. The three green ants: Aboriginal People and Aboriginal Bush Traders with Industry/Government working together towards creating a secure and sustainable economic future (the nest) for Aboriginal people. The logo also feature raark (cross hatching) which is typically found in Top End artworks, signifying our regional interest. You can't build a strong nest without working together. exhibition Ngaruwanajirri Bark Painting NOW! At Wurrumiyanga on Bathurst Island, one beautiful building known as the Tiwi Sistine Chapel or The Keeping Place houses a small group of Tiwi artists who attend daily to create artwork in a peaceful environment. The artists are guided towards excellence in their finished artworks and are represented in State Galleries across Australia and over the world. Renowned for their use of traditional Tiwi cultural materials such as ground-up local ochre pigments, artists also work with a variety of contemporary media including wax and dyes on silk. Aboriginal Art Christmas Decorations View all Quick view Tina Martin Xmas Ball $14.00 Quick view Jacinta Numina Assorted Hand Painted Bush Medicine Leaves Christmas Decorations $12.00 Quick view Betsy Lewis Mina Mina Dreaming Xmas Ball $14.00 Quick view Julie Woods Two Sisters Xmas Ball $14.00 View all 12 products Tina Martin Xmas Ball Regular price $14.00 8 in stock Size: 7.6cm "Close (esc)" Jacinta Numina Assorted Hand Painted Bush Medicine Leaves Christmas Decorations Regular price $12.00 81 in stock These Hand Painted Christmas Decorations come in different shapes and designs. Online orders will be a random selection "Close (esc)" Betsy Lewis Mina Mina Dreaming Xmas Ball Regular price $14.00 37 in stock Xmas Ball - 7.6cm-BLE611 The country associated with this painting is Mina Mina, a place far west of Yuendumu, significant to Napangardi and Napanangka women who are the custodians of the Jukurrpa that created the area. The Dreaming describes the journey of a group of women of all ages who travelled east gathering food, collecting Ngalyipi (Tinospora smilacina or snake vine) and performing ceremonies as they travelled. The women began their journey at Mina Mina where Karlangu (digging sticks) emerged from the ground. Taking these implements the women travelled east creating Janyinki and other sites. Their journey took them eventually beyond Warlpiri country. In contemporary Warlpiri paintings traditional iconography is used to represent the Jukurrpa, associated sites and other elements. The primary motif used in paintings of the Jukurrpa are the Karlangu digging sticks which rose up out of the ground at Mina Mina. The women used them to collect bush tucker on their travels. This painting shows the motion of the digging sticks as the women move them to dig. homepage_content: Launceston Accommodation - Balmoral On York Address: 19 York Street, Launceston, TAS, 7250 03 6331 8000 BOOK NOW Welcome to the multi award winning Balmoral On York. Experience the difference that our friendly efficient service and comfortable spacious accommodation make to your visit. Centrally Located Offering a variety of spacious accommodation options and free WiFi, Balmoral On York is located just 400 m from Launceston's CBD and a short walk from vibrant restaurants and bars. On-site Restaurant There is an on-site restaurant that serves breakfast and a bar that serves beverages until 19:00. Accommodation Launceston - Balmoral on York Welcome to the multi award winning Balmoral on York . Please enjoy our friendly service and spacious clean rooms when you next stay in Launceston . All rooms have complimentary superfast NBN wireless internet with Smart TV ’s allowing you the convenience of logging into your favourite streaming service. Every guest enjoys our complimentary continental breakfast featuring fresh fruit, yoghurt, cereal, toast, juice, tea and coffee. Book directly via our website and receive a free cooked, hot breakfast upgrade! Come and see why we are the accommodation provider of choice for most business travellers with the perfect location on the edge of the CBD , a close walk to all cafes, shops and restaurants. Our city side rooms enjoy some of the best views across the CBD and down to the Tamar Valley as we are one of the tallest buildings (four storeys with a lift) in town. We invite you stay to enjoy the leather couches, five star quality beds , renovated corporate style bathrooms and modern remote climate controlled heating and cooling in all rooms. If you desire a walk to our famous historic parks, all can be reached within a 5-10 minute walk of our property or if you need to see one of the many specialist medical facilities or hospitals, they are very near within 10-15 minutes or a very short drive by car. “Why Stay anywhere else”? name: The Bond Store
homepage_content: BondStore Cafe 0 A little piece of Europe in Southbank. Slide 1 Slide 1 (current slide) Slide 2 Slide 2 (current slide) Slide 3 Slide 3 (current slide) A cafe with a distinctive European feel. Located in one of Melbourne’s most original warehouses. You’d be forgiven for thinking you’d walked into a little piece of Europe. A carefully crafted menu including cold pressed juices, locally and imported wine and beer and one of the city’s finest coffees can be found amongst the high rises and usual dining experiences. Located opposite the Eureka Tower in Southbank. At BondStore we’ve been serving honest food, sourcing only the best produce for over 20 years. We’re open 7 days a week for breakfast and lunch and private events after hours. View fullsize

name: Bottles And Barrels
homepage_content: Home | BOTTLES & BARRELS top of page BOTTLES & BARRELS COFFEE | WINE | FOOD A Bit About Us Pop in to Bottles & Barrels wine store and café. Our friendly establishment at 132 Aberdeen Street Geelong West, is where friends and family come together to enjoy great coffee, fine wine and wholesome food. Our coffee has the right amount of flavour and is served just the way you like it. Our wine is from far and near and you'll be sure to find just the right drop to suit. Our food includes great toasties, healthy salads, filling soups, fancy pies and there is always room for something sweet. We also offer take home meals for those who want a home cooked meal but don’t have the time. Our relaxed atmosphere offers a delightful escape for wine enthusiasts and coffee connoisseurs alike. So come join us, raise a glass and toast to good company, great food, and unforgettable memories. Cheers! COFFEE | WINE | FOOD Take Your Pick CAFE MENU SEVEN SEEDS COFFEE house made biscuits, muffins and slices fruit toast granola avocado & tomato with goats cheese on toast egg & bacon roll chicken & avo wrap reuben ham, cheese & tomato toasty mushroom toasty fresh chicken sandwich zucchini slice fresh daily soups take home meals ​ ​ ​ WINE STORE CRAFT BEER & PRODUCE As lovers of a good drop, we have handpicked our favourite local wines including Lethbridge, Mazzini and Mermerus, then we’ve added the very best from the regions that make them famous. For us it is Bollinger for Champagne, Peyurassol for Provence, Skillogalee for Clare Valley, Syrahmi for Heathcote just to name a few! We are also proud champions of local craft breweries with the advantage of stocking limited release beers, you'll always find something to tickle your fancy, if not just a little bit different. For traditionalists, we stock a range of the usual suspects as well to ensure everyone can find a beer at Bottles & Barrels. FUNCTIONS COCKTAIL & DINNER PARTIES At Bottles & Barrels we can cater for a variety of events or small. We specialise in intimate dinner parties for between 8 - 18 guests hosted in our private dining room. Whether it’s a special occasion, a work event or you’d rather outsource a dinner party, we have got you covered. We don’t mind the odd intimate cocktail party or two either. Let us help you organise the ultimate party or event for up to 50 guests. To receive a copy of our event menu or for further information about how we can help, please contact us. name: Brodburger
homepage_content: Home - Brod — Brodburger Skip to content VIEW MENU BROD view burgers Burgers view hotdogs Hot Dogs view sides Sides FAQs can I change or add ingredients on my burger? You can edit your order or add extra ingredients to your burger when you order online. We offer a range of extras as outlined below: Avocado, bacon, egg, slaw – $2 ea 200g beef patty or chicken breast – $7 ea Mushroom, eggplant, zucchini, capsicum – $2 ea Cheese, beetroot, pineapple, pickles, jalapenos – $1.50 ea Gluten free buns (not available in baby sizes) – $2.50 ea do you cater for large groups? We now take bookings online and cater for large groups. Please see our locations page to book . where do your ingredients come from? We make our burgers from the freshest local ingredients. do you cater for pregnant mothers? Any burger can be made into a BROD MAMA burger which are made with a well done beef patty, egg free aioli and your choice of Swiss or cheddar cheese. can I have my beef cooked well done? We cook our beef patties to perfection, which is medium. If you prefer your beef patty to be cooked more, please let us know when you order. do you have gluten free buns? Yes! We have gluten free buns available (except in baby sizes) at $2 extra.

name: Coffs Coast Coffee Coffs Harbour
homepage_content: Organic Coffee Beans | Coffee Farm Coffs Coast Coffee | Coffs Harbour top of page Organically grown, hand-picked, sun-dried and roasted in the tropical hills of Coffs Harbour. Coffs Coast Coffee was born in the Mid North Coast town of Korora. It has been due to the temperature sub tropical climate and suitable soils that have enabled us to successfully organically grow our product of Arabica coffee. Our coffee is 100% Arabica single origin that is grown on our small batch hobby farm here in Korora. Hand hand-picked, sun-dried and roasted to perfection. Shop for Coffee It doesn't stop at coffee We have ensured sustainability by including a by-product from the cherries to make two types of healthy teas. The cherries and turmeric are dried then prepared as a pleasant tasting, healthy tea. Shop for Tea Get in touch Prefer to have a chat with us? Give us a call or email. Contact Us bottom of page

name: Daark Espresso
homepage_content: Daark Espresso - Chirn Park Speciality Coffee Pioneers Locally Sourced x Brewed With Love Table Service Venue. we are doing table service. to be seated, wait at the front. Embrace the dark side with Daark Espresso Daark is an espresso bar celebrated for its exceptional coffee, warm service and standout food — and judging by the regular queue for a table, it’s clearly a local favourite. When you're on the hunt for the best breakfast in Southport, Daark is well worth the extra few minutes’ drive. A true institution among seasoned brunch-goers, it's always buzzing with coffee lovers soaking up the relaxed vibe from the wrap-around deck. With full table service, we kindly ask that guests wait at the bottom of the stairs to be seated — our team will get you settled as soon as possible. From Sweet Potato and Feta Fritters to Turkish Eggs and Lamb Salad, the menu offers a delicious variety for breakfast and lunch, all paired with award-winning Supreme Roasters coffee. You’ll also find treats like our Biscoff latte, a rotating selection of matchas (including strawberry, blackberry and classic ceremonial etc..) and a full drinks lineup to suit every mood..Oh — and don’t forget the homemade vanilla cold foam that makes every drink just that little bit better. Trust us. Tucked away in the charming pocket of Chirn Park on the Northern Gold Coast, Daark is open seven days for dine-in and takeaway specialty coffee, with all-day breakfast, lunch, beer, wine and cocktails. And if you’re struggling to leave your cosy bed, we’ve got you covered — literally. We provide warm woolly wraps to snuggle into while you dine alfresco. Drop by for a coffee or something chilled and see if you can resist the lure of our house-made French toast or crispy hash browns. Email Address Sign Up We respect your privacy. Thank you! Book a table for 4 or more Call Us : You can also book a table by calling or texting us directly at 0450 988 899 during our opening times. (05.30am - 02.30pm) Booking Policy : Note: We don’t take Bookings on Public Holidays or the Gold Coast Marathon Weekend. We accept reservations for groups of 4 to 10 people. No same Day Bookings We hold the table for 15 minutes past your reservation time. If you do not show up within this time, the table may be given to another customer. Tables are reserved for 1.5 hours. If you wish to stay longer, please let us know when you book the table. We look forward to serving you! Contact Us Please complete the form below No bookings enquiries via email. Please call or text us (0450 988 899) for a booking. Daark Espresso Menu If you’re passionate about coffee and thrive in a dynamic environment, we’d love to hear from you! Please send your resume and a short cover letter to drink@daark.com.au. name: Dark Arts Cafe & Bar
homepage_content: Dark Arts Cafe & Bar | Cafe | Cox Lane, Coffs Harbour NSW, Australia top of page Locally roasted coffee . Craft beer . Wine . Comfort food...done well ​ ​ Private bookings . Functions . Pa rties . Weddings . Receptions . Events BOOK A SPOT WITH US About Us The something unexpected behind that laneway door.... We're open... 6.30am - 2pm, 7 days (Brekky, Lunch) We're also available in the evenings for private bookings, functions, parties, weddings, receptions, events (Booking Fee + minimum spend required for private functions) Click here for our Function Packages Menus Menus Our Coffee Our Coffee Dark Arts Coffee Roasters ​ Dark Arts Coffee Roasters is a small boutique roastery located right here on the Coffs Coast. ​ Partnered with Origin Coffee Traders & other ethical traders, Dark Arts Coffee Roasters seeks to ensure the ethical sourcing of coffee, looking after both the farmers & the environment, whilst maintaining quality & consistency. Currently, our house blend “BLACK MAGIC” is our definite favourite, with a medium style roast & a beautiful full body. “BLACK MAGIC” is a four bean blend of Colombian, Costa Rican, Peruvian & Sumatran coffee & perfect for milk & black coffee drinkers (as well as alternate milks like soy, almond, macadamia, coconut & lactose free, which are all available). It has low acidity with a lovely cut through, delivering a rich, chocolate & caramel body, with a hint of floral after tones. We also have “BLACK MAGIC” whole beans available for sale & can grind in house to your chosen specifications. ​ ​ Functions & Parties Functions & Parties We're available in the evenings for private bookings, functions, parties, weddings, receptions, events, with a range of packages to make sure you have a great time !! If you have an event you'd like to chat about, sing out... name: Dixie Bakery Cafe
homepage_content: Dixie Cafe 0 224 Balaclava Rd, Caulfield North VIC 3161 Your Local Cafe, Nestled in Caulfield North reserve a table Welcome to Dixie Cafe Nestled in the heart of Caulfield North, Dixie Cafe has been your friendly local spot for delicious, homemade food and great coffee. We’re all about warm welcomes, hearty meals, and that cozy, laid-back vibe that makes you feel right at home. No fuss, just honest flavours, friendly faces, and plenty of good times. Whether you’re popping in for your morning coffee, a lazy brunch, or a catch-up with friends, Dixie is the place to slow down and savour the moment. Reservations We can’t wait to welcome you to Dixie — where fresh, flavour-packed food and warm smiles come standard. Whether you’re grabbing a casual breakfast, lunch, or planning a small celebration, we’ve got you covered. Walk-ins are always welcome, but if you want to book ahead, simply use our online reservation system below or give us a call. For larger groups or special requests, just reach out and we’ll do our best to make it happen. At Dixie, every visit feels like coming home — we look forward to seeing you soon! make a reservation Our Menu At Dixie Cafe, our menu is all about fresh, homemade dishes that feel like a warm hug. From our crispy schnitzel sandwiches and loaded toasties to vibrant salads and comforting shakshuka, there’s something to satisfy every craving. view our menu

homepage_content: Florey Pharmacy Cart 0 Scroll WELCOME TO FLOREY PHARMACY Open 7 days a week 8am - 8pm (mONDAY - FRIDAY) & 9AM - 8PM (SATURDAY - SUNDAY) Open all public holidays (excluding Christmas AND NEW YEARS DAY) About Us At Florey Pharmacy the health and wellness of our community is our top priority. By focusing on our customer’s health needs we provide trusted advice and information to improve their wellbeing. We strive to help our customers understand and take control of their health. We believe that access to a Pharmacist is key – so we ensure there is always an experienced Pharmacist available to assist you with any of your concerns or needs. From infants to the elderly we provide care to all age ranges and disease states. We are a diabetes care Pharmacy, with NDSS and a diabetes educator on appointment. To understand the best solutions for you and your family, come in or call us for more information. We are here to help. Our Services We have a great range of health services to suit everybody’s needs, visit our services page to find out more! Alerts 10 Find a park What's on Walk on the 'wildlife' side Explore our natural environment on foot Keeping Oxeye Daisy out of the ACT Protecting grasslands, woodlands, wetlands and agriculture Recreational Trail Enhancement Improving trail resilience, visitor safety and the user experience Browse all of our current feature articles Get out there! Inspiration for your next adventure. Explore the outdoors! Enjoy your favourite outdoor activity in one of our special parks or reserves. Stay under the stars Places to camp out in an ACT park Acknowledgement of Country Dhawura nguna ngurumbangu gunanggu Ngunnawal. Nginggada dindi dhawura Ngunnawalbun yindjumaralidjinyin. Mura bidji mulanggaridjindjula. Naraganawaliyiri yarabindjula. This country is Ngunnawal (ancestral/spiritual) homeland. We all always respect elders, male and female, as well as Ngunnawal country itself. They always keep the pathways of their ancestors alive. They walk together as one. We acknowledge the Ngunnawal people as Canberra’s first inhabitants and Traditional Custodians. We recognise the special relationship and connection that Ngunnawal people have with this Country. Prior to the displacement of Ngunnawal people from their land, they were a thriving people whose life and culture was connected unequivocally to this land in a way that only they understand and know and is core to their physical and spiritual being. The segregation of the Ngunnawal people from Culture and Country has had long-lasting, profound, and ongoing health and well-being effects on their life, cultural practices, families, and continuation of their law/lore. We acknowledge the historic interruption of the Ngunnawal people of Canberra and their surrounding regions. We recognise the significant contribution the Ngunnawal people have played in caring for Country. For time immemorial they have maintained a tangible and intangible cultural, social, environmental, spiritual, and economic connection to these lands and waters. Alerts 10 Find a park What's on Walk on the 'wildlife' side Explore our natural environment on foot Keeping Oxeye Daisy out of the ACT Protecting grasslands, woodlands, wetlands and agriculture Recreational Trail Enhancement Improving trail resilience, visitor safety and the user experience Browse all of our current feature articles Get out there! Inspiration for your next adventure. Explore the outdoors! Enjoy your favourite outdoor activity in one of our special parks or reserves. Stay under the stars Places to camp out in an ACT park Acknowledgement of Country Dhawura nguna ngurumbangu gunanggu Ngunnawal. Nginggada dindi dhawura Ngunnawalbun yindjumaralidjinyin. Mura bidji mulanggaridjindjula. Naraganawaliyiri yarabindjula. This country is Ngunnawal (ancestral/spiritual) homeland. We all always respect elders, male and female, as well as Ngunnawal country itself. They always keep the pathways of their ancestors alive. They walk together as one. We acknowledge the Ngunnawal people as Canberra’s first inhabitants and Traditional Custodians. We recognise the special relationship and connection that Ngunnawal people have with this Country. Prior to the displacement of Ngunnawal people from their land, they were a thriving people whose life and culture was connected unequivocally to this land in a way that only they understand and know and is core to their physical and spiritual being. The segregation of the Ngunnawal people from Culture and Country has had long-lasting, profound, and ongoing health and well-being effects on their life, cultural practices, families, and continuation of their law/lore. We acknowledge the historic interruption of the Ngunnawal people of Canberra and their surrounding regions. We recognise the significant contribution the Ngunnawal people have played in caring for Country. For time immemorial they have maintained a tangible and intangible cultural, social, environmental, spiritual, and economic connection to these lands and waters. What's on Keep up to date with events happening near you! 17 Dec 25 ParkCare Volunteering Information Session Time: 16:00 - 17:00 Location: Online via Microsoft Teams Cost: No cost Bookings: Register here for ParkCare Volunteering Information Session Are you interested in volunteering with ACT Parks and Conservation Service and want to find out more? The ParkCare Volunteer Information Session is an online information session hosted by our ParkCare volunteer management team. The session will cover: Who is ParkCare What volunteering roles are available What you can expect as a ParkCare volunteer Rights, responsibilities and workplace health and safety How to get started There will also be an opportunity for questions and answers at the end of the session. Come and find out more about our incredible volunteer community! Register through Eventbrite . See more events

homepage_content: Home - Parks ACT Skip to content In a life threatening emergency dial Triple Zero (000) Emergency Contact In a life threatening emergency dial Triple Zero (000) triple zero 000 ACT Public Hospitals Canberra Hospital 5124 0000 North Canberra Hospital 6201 6111 Mental Health Call Mental Health Triage on 1800 629 354 (free call except from mobiles or public phones) or 6205 1065 Poisons Hotline For a poison emergency in Australia call 13 11 26 Drug and Alcohol Help Line The Drug and Alcohol Help Line is available 24-hours, 7 days a week on 5124 9977 Health Protection Service For after hours urgent public health matters including environmental health, radiation safety, food poisoning and communicable disease management phone: (02) 6205 1700 healthdirect 24 hour health advice 1800 022 222 ACT State Emergency Service Emergency help during flood or storms 13 25 00 Parks ACT - Home Discover Canberra's outdoor spring adventures The family friendly guide to spectacular spring activities across our parks and reserves . Alerts 10 Find a park What's on Walk on the 'wildlife' side Explore our natural environment on foot Keeping Oxeye Daisy out of the ACT Protecting grasslands, woodlands, wetlands and agriculture Recreational Trail Enhancement Improving trail resilience, visitor safety and the user experience Browse all of our current feature articles Get out there! Inspiration for your next adventure. Explore the outdoors! Enjoy your favourite outdoor activity in one of our special parks or reserves. Stay under the stars Places to camp out in an ACT park Acknowledgement of Country Dhawura nguna ngurumbangu gunanggu Ngunnawal. Nginggada dindi dhawura Ngunnawalbun yindjumaralidjinyin. Mura bidji mulanggaridjindjula. Naraganawaliyiri yarabindjula. This country is Ngunnawal (ancestral/spiritual) homeland. We all always respect elders, male and female, as well as Ngunnawal country itself. They always keep the pathways of their ancestors alive. They walk together as one. We acknowledge the Ngunnawal people as Canberra’s first inhabitants and Traditional Custodians. We recognise the special relationship and connection that Ngunnawal people have with this Country. Prior to the displacement of Ngunnawal people from their land, they were a thriving people whose life and culture was connected unequivocally to this land in a way that only they understand and know and is core to their physical and spiritual being. The segregation of the Ngunnawal people from Culture and Country has had long-lasting, profound, and ongoing health and well-being effects on their life, cultural practices, families, and continuation of their law/lore. We acknowledge the historic interruption of the Ngunnawal people of Canberra and their surrounding regions. We recognise the significant contribution the Ngunnawal people have played in caring for Country. For time immemorial they have maintained a tangible and intangible cultural, social, environmental, spiritual, and economic connection to these lands and waters. What's on Keep up to date with events happening near you! 17 Dec 25 ParkCare Volunteering Information Session Time: 16:00 - 17:00 Location: Online via Microsoft Teams Cost: No cost Bookings: Register here for ParkCare Volunteering Information Session Are you interested in volunteering with ACT Parks and Conservation Service and want to find out more? The ParkCare Volunteer Information Session is an online information session hosted by our ParkCare volunteer management team. The session will cover: Who is ParkCare What volunteering roles are available What you can expect as a ParkCare volunteer Rights, responsibilities and workplace health and safety How to get started There will also be an opportunity for questions and answers at the end of the session. Come and find out more about our incredible volunteer community! Register through Eventbrite . See more events

name: Fortnums Restaurant & Wedding Venue
homepage_content: Fortnums Restaurant | Wedding Reception Venue | Functions | Dandenong Ranges Home Restaurant Menu Lunch Menu Dessert Menu Wine Menu Gluten Free Menu Mothers Day Menu Christmas in July Menu Weddings Functions Private Function Garden Room High Tea Contact Picnics and Platters 03 9755 1200 Online Shop Home Restaurant Menu Lunch Menu Dessert Menu Wine Menu Gluten Free Menu Mothers Day Menu Christmas in July Menu Weddings Functions Private Function Garden Room High Tea Contact Picnics and Platters Fortnums Restaurant, Weddings & Functions Venue Restaurant & Wedding Reception Venue Dandenong Ranges Fortnums is set in the heart of the beautiful Dandenong Ranges, in the quaint village of Sassafras, a short drive from iconic attractions such as Puffing Billy and the Rhododendron Gardens. Fortnums overlooks the spectacular nearby ranges and is set amongst picturesque gardens. Fortnums has the bright airy look and feel of an English conservatory with a charming atmosphere created by warm friendly staff and relaxing music. Our menu draws its inspiration from a variety of good honest comfort food and modern Australian cuisine. We are known near and far for our high quality lunch, desserts and High Teas, not to forget our famous traditional scones served with a variety of jams and conserves all made on our premises. We serve a selection of local wines from the Yarra Valley and other Australian regions, and also stock a wide variety of local and imported beers and spirits. Fortnums is open almost every week of the year, Wednesday to Sunday 11:00am to 4:00pm, and we welcome bookings and enquiries . Fortnums can also cater for small and large group bookings and can create a set menu to suit your taste and budget. Dining in the restaurant or our private garden room overlooking our garden and Melbourne's skyline. If you are planning a birthday, an event or that very special day, your wedding, fortnums can offer itself as the premier boutique wedding and function Venue in the Dandenongs. Call us on 03 9755 1200 Fortnums News Christmas in July! Its that time of the year again! At Fortnums we love Christmas so much that we do it twice a year! Come and join us for our famous Christmas 2 or 3 course lunch, served every day we are open. Please click this link to see our menu. homepage_content: The Glasshouse Cafe | Coffee • Food • Catering COFFEE • FOOD • CATERING brighten your day COFFEE • FOOD • CATERING CITY TUGGERANONG A place to meet The Glasshouse Cafe is a place to meet friends or colleagues for business, converge with family and friends, or simply enjoy great food in a relaxed atmosphere. With a wide range of tasty dishes, you can always find something to suit your mood - from home-style meals to gourmet delights to sandwiches and salads. We also provide catering services for corporate clients too - so you may be enjoying our delicious food right now in your office! CITY 10 Binara St, City, ACT, Australia Mon - Fri 7:00 am - 4:00 pm Sat - Sun Closed SEE THE MENU CONTACT US Tuggeranong South.Point Shopping Centre Tuggeranong Saturday - Thursday 8am - 4pm Friday 8am - 9pm SEE THE MENU CONTACT US Catering At The Glasshouse Cafe we offer catering options and packages ready for your next event or meeting. We have a diverse range of delicious offerings, all designed with office eating in mind. Whether you are looking for something light or substantial, we can make sure that your next meeting or event is delicious and memorable. homepage_content: Great Eastern Motel Contact Us Phone (07) 5482 7288 \ 0427 728 888 Email info@greateastern.com.au Address 27-29 Geordie Road, Gympie, QLD 4570 Australia Make a Booking General Enquiry * Required fields 27-29 Geordie Road, Gympie QLD (07) 5482 7288 \ 0427 728 888 Book Now Enjoy a swim in the pool or have a relaxing drink at the bar. Dine in Geordies relaxed & friendly restaurant. Eat in or take away delicious pizzas available. Shop in Mary Street in the Gympie township – just a short drive from the motel. Walk across the road to the ‘Duck Ponds’, one of Gympie’s most popular family attractions, where you can feed the ducks and turtles! Enjoy the parklands and have a family BBQ, and let the kids explore the fabulous All Abilities Playground. Dear Guests: Our Restaurant is temporary closed until further notice. Welcome Leave your troubles behind, come in and meet our friendly staff -- who with a joke or two -- are always happy to help you enjoy your stay! Running parallel to the Bruce Highway on Geordies Road, the Great Eastern Motor Inn is conveniently situated on the south side of Gympie opposite the Information Centre and “Duck Ponds”. GOOD TIMES. VIEW PRODUCTS ADVENTURE STARTS WITH GOOD COFFEE. Simplicity — it’s a seriously underrated thing. Our philosophy is a reflection of our appreciation for the simple things in life, from that first cup in the morning, to good times spent with those closest to you. Sitting down for a cup with friends to manufacture your next moments is what we’re all about. No, we aren’t talking about those big moments you see in photo albums years later, but the ones that happen in-between; the ones you remember. You see, we like to think good coffee has the ability to bring people together and slow life down for a minute, so that you can hatch your next adventure. BLENDS VIEW PRODUCTS SINGLE ORIGIN VIEW PRODUCTS HOME BUNDLES VIEW PRODUCTS YOUR FRIENDLY NEIGHBOURHOOD COFFEE ROASTER Based in the beautiful Northern Rivers of NSW, we take a hands-on approach to everything we do, from production through to distribution. If we’re not on the tools, you’ll find us out and about enjoying everything this coastal paradise has to offer. Our home is part of who we are, and we take sustainability very seriously. We’re committed to minimising our impact on the natural environment and supporting the sustainable development of the global coffee industry. name: Jamdrop Cafe Cairns
homepage_content: Jamdrop Cafe Cairns - Beautiful Coffee - Office Catering Cairns Jamdrop Cafe Cairns Jamdrop Cafe Cairns is a beautiful little cafe located at 193 – 197 Lake Street, opposite the Cairns Private Hospital, look for the Jamdrop Cafe Sign. Operating here in Cairns serving up beautiful handmade temptations for nearly 20 years. Great Coffee, Snacks, Breakfast, Light Lunch & Takeaway is available Monday to Friday. Try our scrumptious handmade cakes, beautiful fresh coffee, fresh sandwiches and great fast service. We know you dont get allot of time for your lunch break so pop in and try Jamdrop Cafe today. Office Catering Cairns Having an office presentation, training or boardroom meeting? need some yummy morning / afternoon tea or even lunch? Jamdrop Cafe deliver office catering to your Cairns based office. Print out the menu to the right and give us a call with how many people you are catering for. You can find out more about Jamdrops Office Catering Cairns . Great Coffee Snacks Breakfast Light Lunch Takeaway Office Catering Located over the road from the Cairns Private Hospital Jamdrop is easy to find with our bright cream exterior and black Jamdrop logo. name: King Henryâ€™s Restaurant
homepage_content: King Henry's Restaurant Search this site Embedded Files Skip to main content Skip to navigation Jewel of the Dandenong Ranges A unique King Henry's VIII Themed Restaurant est. 1902 Step into our charming old-world British atmosphere, steeped in history since 1902, complete with romantic touches—two crackling fireplaces, soft lighting, and soothing music that set the stage for an unforgettable dining experience. Prefer the outdoors? Enjoy your meal on our elevated deck with stunning views of the lush fern tree lined forest. Wander through serene ponds, extensive gardens, or take a peaceful 5-minute stroll along the national forest trail. At King Henry VIII, every moment is designed to delight. Make a Reservation We are pleased to share that King Henry’s Restaurant has been awarded a Recommendation badge by Restaurant Guru, one of the world’s most popular foodie websites with over 30 millions monthly users. Congratulations on the team for this incredible achievement! Christmas Set Menu Available from December 1st to 25th WE ARE OPEN ON CHRISTMAS DAY LUNCH & DINNER Book Now OUR STORY King Henry's Restaurant is in the stunning tourist destination of Sassafras. Set on 5 acres with a large deck overlooking beautiful gardens. The old guest house, which dates back to 1902, has been totally renovated and is now one of the most popular destinations in the Dandenong Ranges. Award Winning The Australian Good Food Guide (AGFG) has named Sassafras’s King Henry’s restaurant in it’s 2024 Readers’ Choice Awards. LOOKING TO HOST AN EVENT? Be it a milestone birthday or anniversary, a corporate party, high tea, or a special event, you can book King Henry's Sassafras for your gathering. We will work with you from the planning stage until the day of the event to bring you an occasion to remember! Frequently Asked Questions Where do you source your ingredients? At King Henry's Sassafras we make all food to order using the best local products available. During peak periods including weekends and public holidays, we cannot alter food as this may delay the service of your food and beverages. Thank you for your understanding and patience. Do you cater for Private Dining or Group Bookings Yes we do. Please submit your enquiry today to discuss your requirements. Please note that a deposit will be required to secure your bookings. We offer a full refund if you cancel at least 7 days before the booking date. I have allergies, do you have any food options for me? Our menu offers a variety of gluten free (GF) and vegetarian (VGN) options. Should you have a sensitivity to a known allergen such as: -DAIRY -SULPHITES -BEE PRODUCTS -SESAME -PEANUTS -TREE NUTS -GLUTEN/WHEAT -EGG -SOYBEAN -SEAFOOD -FISH -CRUSTACEANS or any other products, we will endeavour to provide food and beverage alternatives, absent from your known allergen. Food and beverage will be served on the understanding and acknowledgement that it has been prepared in a kitchen and on equipment that has been used in the preparation of ingredients (among others) which are known allergens and as such, may contain trace amounts. Do you require a deposit for Group Bookings? Please note, a 1.5% processing fee applies for all card transactions and a 15% surcharge applies on public holidays Do you have surcharges on public holidays? Please note, a 1.5% processing fee applies for all card transactions and a 15% surcharge applies on public holidays Media Reviews "Sassafras’s King Henry’s Restaurant named in Australian Good Food Guide’s Readers’ Choice Awards" - AGFG "Mikkayla reviews: King Henry’s Sassafras — ‘sure to delight’" - 3AW "King Henry’s Restaurant in Sassafras is one of the most popular destinations in the Dandenong Ranges." - Villadamour " A new chapter for King Henry’s restaurant " - StarMail Newspaper Google Sites Report abuse Page details Page updated Google Sites Report abuse

homepage_content: Best Wholesale Serbian Burek Macedonian Bakery NSW The Burek Guy - Shop 1/166 Macquarie St, Liverpool, NSW 2 1 70 IN HOUSE DAILY BAKED AUTHENTIC BREADS 02 9734 8500 EMAIL US OUR STORY BUREK FOR GOOD OUR RANGE OF PRODUCT CONTACT & ORDER WELCOME Our traditional balkan bakery values are keeping our rich culture and beloved traditions alive and thriving. We bring traditional and authentic homemade food from the Balkan regions straight to our customers. You'll find baked goods from the countries of Serbia, Macedonia, Bosnia, and Croatia as well as surrounding countries. At LS Bakery, we are all about connecting with one another through traditional foods, and we've delighted customers since our opening in 2009. The aroma of freshly baked goods fill the air, and our valued customers can choose from our delightful array of breads, bureks, cakes and pastries. Our professional and knowledgeable staff pride themselves on our bread making process because it pays homage to our rich European culture. We are a family-owned and operated business that dedicates itself to excellence in all areas of the business including high quality great tasting products, customer service, cleanliness and also contributing to the community and world through the global goals. This dedication earned us the 2017 and 2018 “Outstanding Bakery/Cake Shop” award. We invite you to come in and experience our rich history, warm atmosphere and delicious food offerings that should be shared with family and friends of all cultures. name: Macpan
homepage_content: Home - Macpan | Commercial Kitchen & Baking Equipment Supply Welcome to mac.pan Thank you for your interest in Mac Pan products. Quality has always been our primary objective, and we have made it a veritable company style: it can be seen in both the product and the service offered by our commercial and technical staff. Our total dedication to quality has rewarded us in terms of customer satisfaction; the satisfaction of our sales personnel has spurred us on to strive for continuous improvement and for your continued satisfaction. READ MORE Our Products Mac Pan has considerable experience gained over many years in overhauling and manufacturing cake-making machinery. It has designed its own machines based on innovative principles, and new design and production criteria. As a result, the machines respond to the requirements of both the end user and current regulations. Mac Pan guarantees a complete after-sales service offering customised systems which will suit any of your requirements. READ MORE See us in Action See our quality products in use by our clients. Take a look through our videos of our equipment in action. See our new Water Doser delivering any quantity of water with an accuracy up to 99.9%. Take a look at our new servo driven cake and batter depositor at production speed of upto 1800 units per hr with this size muffin, making no mess into tulip papers. See Macpans electric servo drive depositor, able to cope with most tins and trays. READ MORE Macpan Automatic Pie Line 1500 per hr The macpan retailer pie machine can manufacture meat pies at an output speed of 1500 pies per hour. Trays are manually fed to the machine and firstly pass under the bottoms pastry pin and pastry laid and then dragged onto the pie pallet. The pallet then passes under the tray forming station which impresses the pastry into the pie form. The tray emerges from the station and pastry is water misted to allow adhesion of the top pastry when applied. The next step the tray indexes to the depositor station and each tin is filled with a measured quantity of meat. The next process the filled pie pallet travels under the tops pastry pin where tops pastry is laid on top, the pallet then passé through the trim where a pneumatic operated stamper/plate is pressurised against the pie pallet and the top pastry is crimped against the bottom pastry and trimmed around the pie tin. The tray then exits the machine and is manually de-scraped. Australian-Made Bakery Equipment At Macpan, we manufacture and produce high-quality bakery and pastry equipment right here in Australia. Our Australian-made equipment is produced using only the very finest quality supplies and materials. We offer a range of Australian-made products including our Conveyorised Egg Wash machines , Automatic Muffin, Cake, and Batter Depositors , Mobile Egg Wash machines , Wholesale Pie Machines , Humidity Units , Vari Fillers , VVF Volumetric Var-Fillers , Proofer Retarders , Retailer Pie Machines , Single Door Reach-in Proofers , and Cyclops Auto Cake and Batter Depositors. All of these machines are tried and tested to ensure that it meets our incredibly high quality-assurance testing. We supply our commercial bakery equipment to bakeries, patisseries, supermarkets, and food equipment retailers across Australia. Our Australian-made equipment is used by some of the market leaders in the food and bakery industry. We have a highly responsive 24/7 service department on hand to service any requests related to our equipment and machinery for your peace of mind. To find out more about our incomparable Australian-made bakery and patisserie equipment, contact us today.

The tray then exits the machine and is manually de-scraped. Australian-Made Bakery Equipment At Macpan, we manufacture and produce high-quality bakery and pastry equipment right here in Australia. Our Australian-made equipment is produced using only the very finest quality supplies and materials. We offer a range of Australian-made products including our Conveyorised Egg Wash machines , Automatic Muffin, Cake, and Batter Depositors , Mobile Egg Wash machines , Wholesale Pie Machines , Humidity Units , Vari Fillers , VVF Volumetric Var-Fillers , Proofer Retarders , Retailer Pie Machines , Single Door Reach-in Proofers , and Cyclops Auto Cake and Batter Depositors. All of these machines are tried and tested to ensure that it meets our incredibly high quality-assurance testing. We supply our commercial bakery equipment to bakeries, patisseries, supermarkets, and food equipment retailers across Australia. Our Australian-made equipment is used by some of the market leaders in the food and bakery industry. We have a highly responsive 24/7 service department on hand to service any requests related to our equipment and machinery for your peace of mind. To find out more about our incomparable Australian-made bakery and patisserie equipment, contact us today.

name: Luddenham Village Cafe
homepage_content: Welcome to Luddenham Village Café | Located in Luddenham, NSW we serve stunning Café cuisine Skip to content Welcome to Luddenham Village Cafe Ph: (02) 4773 4488 ORDER ONLINE ORDER CATERING RESERVATIONS GIFT CARDS Luddenham Village Café is the hidden gem in the small beautiful country town of Luddenham, located on Willmington Road, it stands smack bang in the centre of Penrith and Narellan. Our Cafe Expand Luddenham Village Café prides itself on its savoury sandwich / foccacia bar, Luddenham Village Café only use the most readily sourced local produce from a Mulgoa grower currently and depending on availability about 15-20% of certain produce is sourced from Victoria. We also use a variety of Italian cured meats to showcase that good produce mixed with homemade bread and cured meats is a match made in heaven. Apart from coffee not only for our locals but people travel from a far for our Italian cannoli, they are made & piped to order so there is no secrets, a fresh crunchy buttery pastry filled with our famous flavoured cream inside. We could go onto carry on about all our gorgeous specialty cakes but ultimately they speak for themselves. Whether it's coffee you're serving up to your family on a Sunday lunch, or an antipasto platter that?s being showcased at your kitchen tea, or even a large tray of gorgeous petite Italian sweets, we only sell to our customers what we would give to our families. If it's good enough for us, it's going to be just as amazing for our customers who are now our friends. In House Roasted Coffee Expand LVC is most renound for its ability to show the customer how important and unique it is to have freshly roasted coffee. It is a standard feature that whilst you’re waiting for your coffee, you are able to watch our roaster at work with its unique aroma customers are able to watch a raw coffee bean in its natural state go through its roasting process and finish as a readily consumable coffee bean all within 20 minutes. Our Catering Services Expand Corporate / Special Occasion Catering. Please contact us for information regarding Catering & Functions. Catering can be altered to suit your needs. Phone (02) 4773 4488 Trading / Kitchen Hours Mon – Sat: 5am – 4pm (Kitchen closes at 2.30pm) Sun: 6am – 4pm (Kitchen closes at 2.30pm) PUBLIC HOLIDAYS / CHRISTMAS/ JANUARY / EASTER HOURS MAY VARY - PLEASE SEE FACEBOOK OR INSTAGRAM FOR HOURS Address 3035 Willmington Rd, Luddenham, 2745 (Next To Ampol) Scroll to Top

homepage_content: Home - Maaric Dry Cleaners DRY CLEANING The best in dry cleaning with fast, reliable service Learn More LINEN HIRE High-quality bed linen, top sheets, table linen & towelling Learn More LAUNDRY Expert care and quick turnaround Learn More 4 5 LEADERS IN LAUNDRY & DRY CLEANING Welcome to Maaric Industrial Services Your specialists in domestic & industrial dry cleaning and laundry services. Located in Whyalla, South Australia, we service the Whyalla and Spencer Gulf regions. About Us WHAT WE DO Our Services DRY CLEANING Our experienced dry cleaners examine each item thoroughly and pre-treat the stains so you get spotless results. Pick and drop services available for your convenience. LINEN HIRE We provide a full range of high-quality bed linen, top sheets, table linen and towelling for hire. When you hire us, you can be sure that your linen will reach you on time. LAUNDRY Our large range of laundry services are available for industrial, commercial and domestic needs. We will wash, fold, and iron your washables and deliver them fresh and clean. LEADERS IN LAUNDRY & DRY CLEANING Simplify Your Life WITH mAARIC dry cleaners Simplifying your life starts with outsourcing the time-consuming tasks that can easily be handled by trusted professionals—and that’s where Maaric Dry Cleaners comes in. With a wide range of services tailored to meet everyday and specialised cleaning needs, Maaric makes it easier than ever to stay organised and stress-free. Whether you’re looking to quickly wash a load at our self-service, coin-operated laundromats or need expert care for delicate wedding gowns and household curtains, Maaric offers convenience, quality, and peace of mind all in one place. For businesses and busy households alike, Maaric also provides essential services such as industrial workwear cleaning, commercial dry cleaning, and even linen hire—helping reduce your workload while ensuring everything stays fresh and professional. Our unique work glove recycling option is not only efficient but also environmentally conscious, supporting sustainability in your daily operations. From heavy-duty blankets to everyday laundry, choosing Maaric Dry Cleaners means choosing more time, less hassle, and a cleaner life. Satisfaction Guaranteed  Commercial, Industrial & Domestic Be it commercial, industrial or domestic, we can service your needs.  save time with maaric Get your items picked up, cleaned, folded & delivered. Leave it all up to us!  expansive service area Based in Whyalla, we service the wider Spencer Gulf & Eyre Peninsula regions.  full featured self – serve laundomat In addition to our main operations in Patterson St, we operate a coin operated, self-serve laundromat in Whyalla. Contact Us KIND WORDS FROM OUR CLIENTS Testimonials { We have been using Maaric Dry Cleaners for over ten years and find their service and supply to be of the highest quality. Chrys and his staff have an old school service approach that is refreshing in the modern era, nothing is too hard and the quality of work is always at a very high standard. I can recommend Maaric without hesitation. John O’Halloran West Coast Cleaning Supplies Thank you for your outstanding service to us over the past 2 1/2 years. All of your staff are very professional, efficient and friendly which reflects from your great management/ ownership. We are extremely happy with the linen service you have provided at both Port Augusta and Whyalla Discovery Parks and are happy to continue this working relationship in the future. With 56 cabins we have a high turnover of linen but anytime an urgent order was required it has been no trouble you Maarics have got the job done. We appreciate your services and you are an asset to your industry. Kara-Jane & Kevin Quinn Discovery Parks Whyalla We have developed a great partnership with Maaric who have been our supplier since day 1. The dedication to ensuring our needs and standards are met is above and beyond. We appreciate the ‘can do’ approach and quality of the product and service. We are a 4.5 Star Hotel with high standards to uphold and we simply wouldn’t choose anyone else” to provide linen to our apartments. Quest Apartment Hotels I have been using Maaric Dry Cleaners Services for over 12 months for my Driver Facility on the Nullabor. I have found the company to be very professional company and they have a great time management process. On numerous occasions I have had to alter the required stock or delivery date and have found the company to be very flexible when this has occurred. I would not hesitate recommending this company to anyone requiring Laundry/Linen Services. Brett Benbow Terminal Manager Port Augusta Pacific National Tony Colyer Pty Ltd is a proud South Australian family business supplying Maaric, a proud Whyalla, family business. Maaric have been sourcing the best quality linens from Tony Colyer Pty Ltd for their customers over the past 10 years. We hear good reports from their clients as to the service that they continue to provide. Tony Colyer Pty Ltd is proud to be part of the success that Maaric has, and will enjoy into the future. Tony Colyer PTY LTD

name: Marble Bar Bistro
homepage_content: Home - Marble Bar Bistro Search X Home About Menu Functions Gallery Contact Skip to content see our menu drink see our drink menu eat see our bistro menu party book a private function beach see our location Raising The Bar The funky Sunshine Beach village charm you feel at the Marble Bar Bistro sets the perfect ambiance to relax and catch up with friends whilst enjoying a meal or a drink. Marble Bar Bistro has a reputation as one of the best night spots on the coast or somewhere to just simply kick back and watch the world go by at anytime of the day or night. We guarantee once you stop for one, it won’t be long before you settle in. This award winning Marble Bar Bistro has a large boutique beer and wine list, partnering a fantastic cocktail list. The share plates as well as the tapas and gourmet pizza menu is always a crowd pleaser with customers coming back for more every time. Book A Table Great Spot for a Drink and Meal Great spot for an afternoon drink, watch the passing parade whilst enjoying a beer or glass of wine. We also ordered a selection of Tapas items which were excellent. Great service and friendly staff. Very popular with the locals which is always a good sign. Missy601 June 2020 What a great little bar and restaurant What a great little bar and restaurant? It has a nice feel, I love their MB branded beer and the meals are fantastic. The menu has plenty of variety. I can never go past the pork belly entree and the main meals are delicious with large serves. You can sit at tables or at benches and watch the world go by! Thoroughly recommend it. billg63 March 2020 The BEST bar (and Tapas) in Noosa!!! The tapas style food here is some of the best on the coast! Consistently great, high quality and delicious meals / bites to eat, at very reasonable prices. The Beef Tataki is outstanding…and if you’re lucky Tuna tataki or sashimi even better! Great pizzas, and pork belly to die for! homepage_content: Affordable & Pet-Friendly Motel in Port Augusta | Motel Poinsettia Get in touch 08 8642 2411 motelpoinsettia@bigpond.com 0886422411 Choose Stay Dates Nights Adults Children Check Availability PROPERTY IS UNDER NEW MANAGEMENT NOW II 24 HOUR SURVEILLANCE CAMERAS || NEWLY INSTALLED DISPENSERS AND LED LIGHTS II MODERN KEYLESS DIGITAL LOCK SYSTEM II FULLY SECURED PARKING AREA WITH SECURITY GATES II 0886422411 Choose Stay Dates Nights Adults Children Check Availability Choose Stay Dates Nights Adults Children Check Availability Motel Poinsettia Motel Poinsettia Welcome to Motel Poinsettia Motel Poinsettia is perfectly positioned for your next business trip, short break, or holiday in Port Augusta. Our well-appointed 3 Star accommodation consists of 23 elegantly designed rooms, offering exceptional value for money. We offer free WIFI in all our spacious and comfortable rooms and our ‘famously friendly’ staff will make sure you have the most enjoyable stay possible. Whether it’s a drive to Australian Arid Lands Botanic Gardens or a visit to Wadlata Outback Centre, our friendly reception staff can provide detailed maps and advice to get you there. We are one of the few Pet-Friendly Motels in Port Augusta as we believe Pets are an integral part of a Family. We are striving to offer you a memorable experience of your stay. Motel Information amenities Motel Poinsettia Check-in: 1pm Family & Pet-Friendly accommodation in Port Augusta Pets Welcome (Please refer to our Pet Policy) Family & Pet-Friendly accommodation in Port Augusta Check-out: 10am Family & Pet-Friendly accommodation in Port Augusta Check-in: 1pm Family & Pet-Friendly accommodation in Port Augusta Pets Welcome (Please refer to our Pet Policy) Family & Pet-Friendly accommodation in Port Augusta Complimentary Secured On-Site Parking Family & Pet-Friendly accommodation in Port Augusta Check-out: 10am Family & Pet-Friendly accommodation in Port Augusta Complimentary Secured On-Site Parking Guest Rooms DELUXE QUEEN ROOM Button TWIN ROOM Button DELUXE TWIN Button STANDARD FAMILY ROOM Button TWO BEDROOM APARTMENT Button FAMILY JUNIOR Button FAMILY SUITE Button PET-FRIENDLY ROOM Button Guest Reviews "I stayed 2 nights at this motel, and spoke to young owners, Mac and her partner. Through the conversation, I came to aware that they just bought the place around 2 months ago, and very keen to make customer experience better. They openly and shamelessly asking for suggestions for improvement, which is fantastic. The motel is opposite Foodland, which makes shopping very accessible, they are also a few restaurants nearby. There is also a common laundry and kitchen at the motel. I enjoy my stay at this motel, mainly thanks for the hospitality of the owners, Mac and her partner." Tanya M Tanya M "Mac and staff have gone out of their way to make my stay enjoyable and comfortable. The added bonus of being pet friendly made it very convenient for me. I am a regular visitor to Port Augusta due to family ties and friends and can confidently say that I will be utilising their warm hospitality again!!!" Phil McCabe "There’s nothing like a warm welcome after a long day on the road. I would give the service 6 stars if I could! These guys really went above and beyond to help us out. We were very grateful to find pet friendly, affordable accommodation in the Xmas/ New Year period. After a long day driving we enjoyed the warm shower (excellent water pressure) and comfortable bed. A little detail that is often missing in hotels - we could sign into our own Netflix to watch some TV! The new owners are putting a lot of work into updating the place. Highly recommend a stay here with your fur baby." Snow Du Fau "Room was perfect for my family, bed very comfy and clean. Well priced. Good location. Staff friendly and happy to have a chat (something that is becoming a rarity these days). Highly recommend." Thu Hien Tran " 5/5 Very welcoming and friendly staff. Loved that our dog was made welcome. Rooms clean and beds very comfortable. Great location." Write your caption here Justine Padovan "This was my second stay at Motel Poinsettia in the past six months travelling with Fergus the Doberman. Rooms are specious and very clean. Motel is a bit dated but everything is in excellent working order. Only a very short walk ( 3 minutes) to a dog friendly park. Excellent value for money and is my new go to, pet friendly, motel." Write your caption here Eugene C "The service was above and beyond. I arrived very late in the evening without a booking and they still took me in. The room was spacious and very clean. I will stay here next time I'm in Port Augusta." Write your caption here Vinnjar Bruknapp "I stayed in a pet friendly room had a migraine. The hostess was very helpful and friendly. I give this place a high rating as its rare to get such a lovely person who cares. Thank you" Write your caption here Sky Flyer "Excellent, very clean and comfortable. Air-conditioning was turned on for us before we arrived, and it's a pet friendly accommodation." Write your caption here Rita Curphey "Great little motel in Port Augusta- has everything you need for a comfortable night sleep. The owners are also extremely friendly and accomodating!" name: Mr Wednesday
homepage_content: Mr Wednesday Cafe 0 Our Story Menu Photos Order Online Functions Reservations Located in the back streets of Fairfield, Melbourne, Mr Wednesday serves honest hearty food with influence from all across the globe using ingredients sourced locally. We serve specialty grade coffee and make everything in house where possible Bar Wednesday our cocktail bar in the rear of the venue is now open Thursday - Sunday 3pm - 9pm with happy hour running 4-5:30 and live music on Sundays ORDER ONLINE Using good local ingredients and adapting to current food trends We combine traditional preparations with local ingredients for dishes that are authentic to both their origins and Melbourne setting. Learn more about our story. Coffee is the life line of your regular Melbournian, so we source the best We use nothing but the best, and the best is INDUSTRY BEANS! We have had a long standing relationship with the team at Industry beans for their quality and consistency of providing top notch specialty coffee beans. BAR WEDNESDAY Hidden behind the cafe is our new wine, cocktail bar. Boasting the traditional Mr Wednesday stylings with a relaxed and ambient feel. Specially crafted cocktails and Australian Wine list, tap and bottled beers and as always high quality and delicious Bar Food. name: Murray Bridge Hotel
homepage_content: Murray Bridge Hotel - Home Welcome to the Murray Bridge Hotel The Murray Bridge Hotel is steeped in history dating back to 1914. The owner, Karen Milesi takes a hands on approach, being involved in every aspect of the day-to-day running of the business. She continues to evolve the Hotel into an attractive, sought-after place to eat, drink and socialise, whilst retaining its heritage. Located in Sixth Street, Murray Bridge, it is about 1 hours drive from Adelaide, straight up the South Eastern Freeway. There's plenty to do in Murray Bridge, so come for a relaxing day on the River Murray and then enjoy a fabulous meal or quiet drink with your friends or family at the Murray Bridge Hotel. The owner, Karen Milesi takes a hands on approach, being involved in every aspect of the day-to-day running of the business. She continues to evolve the Hotel into an attractive, sought-after place to eat, drink and socialise, whilst retaining its heritage. Located in Sixth Street, Murray Bridge, it is about 1 hours drive from Adelaide, straight up the South Eastern Freeway. There's plenty to do in Murray Bridge, so come for a relaxing day on the River Murray and then enjoy a fabulous meal or quiet drink with your friends or family at the Murray Bridge Hotel.

name: Old Wharf Restaurant
homepage_content: The Story of Old Wharf At Old Wharf, we stand in the historical location of former jetties, piers, homes and taverns from where, since the 1800s colourful traders, merchandisers, exporters and explorers have shipped Tassie’s renowned produce across the globe. Chef Alvin Sim and his team acknowledge this history and curate a menu that celebrates and explores classic dishes – with a Tasmanian twist. Reimagined and refined, this menu nods to Hobart’s past while championing our celebrated produce and boutique Tasmanian growers. *Please be advised that a 15% surcharge applies on all public holidays. name: Nurses Internet Cafe
homepage_content: Nursing Australia | Nursing Jobs and Healthcare Staffing Skip to main content Skip to main navigation Home Page Toggle Search bar open Search website Close search bar Submit search Menu Connecting healthcare professionals with opportunities across Australia With over 45 years of experience, Nursing Australia is your trusted partner in healthcare staffing and career growth. We provide registered and specialist nurses, midwives, technicians, and support workers with flexible, rewarding roles across acute care, aged care, disability support, and more. Whether you’re looking for your next career opportunity or seeking skilled professionals to complement your workforce, we’re here to help. Find a job (opens in new tab) Hire staff Your trusted partner in healthcare staffing solutions At Nursing Australia, we leverage our strong industry connections to deliver the best opportunities for healthcare professionals, and the best staffing solutions for facilities. Our mission is to provide exceptional service to both our team members and the healthcare organisations we support. With a management team that blends global nursing experience with extensive recruitment expertise, we understand how to develop fulfilling careers in healthcare. We’re proud to be an Australia-wide nursing agency with offices in Sydney, Brisbane, Adelaide, Perth, and Melbourne, enabling us to place nurses and support staff in roles across the country. As an approved provider to most State and Territory Health Departments and several large public and private healthcare organisations, we’re committed to building long-term relationships and delivering quality outcomes. Learn more about us Nursing staff solutions for every setting We provide highly qualified nursing and support staff for a variety of healthcare settings. Hospitals We place Registered Nurses, Enrolled Nurses, and Assistants in Nursing across specialties such as ICU, mental health, theatre, and paediatrics. Aged Care and Community Nursing Our nurses and support workers deliver compassionate care for elderly patients in residential and community settings, enhancing their quality of life and supporting post-discharge care needs. Disability Support With extensive experience in the disability sector, we provide skilled support workers who make a meaningful difference in clients’ lives. Our positive impact This variety not only keeps my work engaging but also allows me to broaden my clinical expertise across different settings. I am proud to represent Nursing Australia and highly recommend their services to both healthcare professionals seeking rewarding opportunities and healthcare facilities in need of dedicated and skilled nursing staff. Elizabeth Registered Nurse During my 17 years with Nursing Australia, I have had a varied and interesting work. It has been a very enjoyable and rewarding time and I can highly recommend working for this organisation. Dianne Assistant in Nursing Recruitment process was quick, efficient, easy and very professional. The staff at Nursing Australia are very helpful, providing me with a variety of shifts every week. I feel very supported by the team as I get to do the work that I am looking for. Margaret Registered Nurse I have worked with Nursing Australia since 2004. The flexibility and variety of work, from hospital settings to correction facilities, enables me to attain and maintain many skills and keeps my interest in the nursing profession. Deborah Registered Nurse I have had the pleasure of working for Nursing Australia for almost 4 years now and haven’t looked back. If ever I have a question, the staff are always friendly and eager to help. If you're looking for a job where you will feel appreciated and valued then I highly recommend Nursing Australia. My only regret is that I didn't join sooner. Esther Patient Services Attendant The team at Nursing Australia are very helpful and supportive, I always feel well looked after. What I love the most about working for Nursing Australia is the positive relationship between the office team and employees. Aso Assistant in Nursing The flexibility that agency offers suits my current situation. The team are fantastic and I couldn't speak highly enough of them. Nursing Australia offers me local shifts too so I never have to travel too far for work. Rob Registered Mental Health Nurse Previous testimonial Next testimonial

homepage_content: Organic Market Shop Online Home About Us Market Café Find Us Shop Online Desktop vertical spacing: 30 pixels // Mobile vertical spacing: 20 pixels We are passionate about providing you with the widest range of organic & whole foods. The True Cost It does cost a little more to make choices that are good for the planet, animal welfare and our health --- but that's our ethos and how we say NO to the Industrial food system. To achieve this, wherever we can we partner with local suppliers who provide us with organic, biodynamic, non GMO, ethically reared, free-range, sustainable, seasonal & local products. We aren't known for being the cheapest -- but it's something we do not shy away from. Browse our Market... Our store is chock-a-block full of diverse, interesting and delicious gourmet goodies, whole foods, fresh fruit & vegetables and sweet treats galore. With the hundreds & hundreds of lines we carry it's a visual feast for the eyes to peruse our shelves. Desktop vertical spacing: 21 pixels // Mobile vertical spacing: 14 pixels Head to the Shop Enjoy our cafe... The Cafe is a food lovers delight. Healthy food with flavour - some organic, some conventional, with a simple, home cooked menu. The cafe has a vegetarian focus and caters for most dietary requirements, with a choice of vegan, dairy free, gluten free and sugar free products on the menu. About the Cafe Explore our online store... There’s fresh, bulk & packaged foods including a comprehensive selection of vegan, raw and all the “free'' options to suit any dietary quirks. Whether you’re stopping by for a quick breakfast, a leisurely lunch, or a sweet treat, our diverse menu has something to satisfy every craving. Our menu is designed to bring you a delightful array of freshly baked goods, satisfying meals, and refreshing beverages, all crafted with quality ingredients and a touch of love. Whether you’re stopping by for a quick breakfast, a leisurely lunch, or a sweet treat, our diverse menu has something to satisfy every craving. Breakfast Menu Start your day right with Muffin Break’s breakfast offerings. Our new croissants range features three delectable fillings that are sure to make your morning special. Choose from classic ham and cheese, indulgent chocolate, or a healthy spinach and feta option. Pair your croissant with a freshly brewed cup of our award-winning coffee, and you’re set for a great day ahead. Lunch Menu For lunch, Muffin Break offers a variety of options that hit the spot. Our new baguettes range includes five delicious fillings, each crafted to provide a satisfying and flavorful meal. Whether you prefer a hearty roast beef, a classic chicken Caesar, or a vegetarian delight, our baguettes are made fresh daily to ensure maximum taste and quality. Complement your meal with one of our refreshing cold drinks, perfect for a midday pick-me-up. Sweet Treats No visit to Muffin Break is complete without indulging in our sweet treats. Our muffins, the cornerstone of our brand, come in a variety of flavors, each baked to perfection. From classic blueberry to decadent double chocolate, there’s a muffin for every taste bud. In addition to muffins, we offer an array of cakes, slices, and cookies that are perfect for satisfying your sweet tooth. Coffee and Beverages Muffin Break is proud to be recognized as the Roy Morgan Coffee Shop of the Year for the fifth time. Our coffee menu features a range of expertly crafted beverages, from rich espressos to creamy lattes. Every cup is made using premium beans and is brewed to perfection by our skilled baristas. If you’re in the mood for something cool and refreshing, our cold drinks menu includes iced coffees, smoothies, and more. At Muffin Break, we believe in rewarding our loyal customers. Join our rewards program through the Muffin Break app and enjoy perks like every 5th coffee free. It’s our way of saying thank you for choosing us. Visit Muffin Break today and experience the delicious offerings on our menu. With locations across Australia, there’s always a Muffin Break nearby, ready to serve you with a smile and a delicious treat. Good goes in, and great comes out!
