Place an order at orders@pierrespatisserie.com.au ORDER ONLINE About Us A cake for tea time, a customised cake for a birthday celebration or a cake for, well, just because – we have a range to suit any occasion and all preferences. Local to Turramurra and surrounding suburb residents, we’ve become the central meeting spot for a coffee catch up, a quick and easy dinner pie on your way home, or the place to go when looking for something sweet to take to a celebration. Discover our decadence. A quick visit, a coffee catch up or decadence on the go, we've got you. Cakes for any occasion A cake for tea time, a birthday celebration or just because – we have a range to suit an occasion and all preferences. PLACE AN ORDER A morning pick me up Coffee & pastry, the perfect pair for a pick me up, or breakfast on the run. ORDER ONLINE Serving authentic imported Italian coffee. name: Pure Indulgence Fine Chocolates
homepage_content: Chocolate & Confectionary Shop in Darwin | Pure Indulgence Call 08 8981 2947 Chocolate & Confectionary Shop in Darwin Discover Products From Scratch and Hand Made Is there anything in this world better than chocolate? At Pure Indulgence, our chocolates are hand crafted and served fresh to customers. Located in Darwin, we have been providing local families with our delicious range of chocolates and confectionary since 1997. From liquorice and nougat, to chocolate almonds, Rocky Road, Turkish Delight and HoneyComb, the treats we have are endless! Treat yourself today by visiting us in store! We can also deliver anywhere in the Darwin CBD or Northern suburbs. Give us a call to place an order! About Us Family Owned Since 1997 Pure Indulgence was established in 1997 to provide Darwin locals a taste of luxury. Our beautifully hand-crafted chocolates are made with Australian ingredients, providing a smooth and rich taste. We take pride in our high-quality treats and excellent customer service. We believe everyone should get a taste of our delicious chocolates and lollies, which is why we also offer deliveries across the Darwin CBD and northern suburbs. So, if you can’t make it to our store but you’ve got the chocolate cravings, just give us a call and we’ll be at your doorstep in no time. Our Products Chocolates Chocolates Handmade with Love Our chocolates are freshly made using Australian ingredients. Treat yourself or someone special to our beautifully crafted chocolates, gift boxes, and figurines. Lollies Lollies Spoil Yourself Chocolates not your thing? We also have a wide range of lollies including nougat, licorice, rocky road, honeycomb and Turkish delight. We’ve got something for everyone! Deliveries Deliveries Australian Made Treats What’s better than chocolates and lollies? Chocolates and lollies delivered to your door! We can deliver anywhere in the Darwin CBD and northern suburbs. Call us today. Expert Chocolatiers Beautifully Hand-Crafted Chocolates Our specialty chocolate shop stocks over 200 varieties of handmade chocolates from award-winning chocolatiers. These Belgian-style chocolates include everything from traditional chocolates, smooth caramels and fruit-flavoured centres to creamy truffles and nutty pralines. Select one for a taster, or have your selection boxed or in a gift basket. Our expert chocolatiers have curated delicious chocolates made with Australian ingredients. As a family-owned business since 1997, we take great pride in our store and we’re passionate in delivering high quality chocolates and confectionaries. From Honeycomb to Liquorice, there’s something for everyone at Pure Indulgence. With deliveries available, there’s no excuse to not try our chocolates. Visit us in store to see the full range of treats available! name: Pure Indulgence Fine Chocolates
homepage_content: Chocolate & Confectionary Shop in Darwin | Pure Indulgence Call 08 8981 2947 Chocolate & Confectionary Shop in Darwin Discover Products From Scratch and Hand Made Is there anything in this world better than chocolate? At Pure Indulgence, our chocolates are hand crafted and served fresh to customers. Located in Darwin, we have been providing local families with our delicious range of chocolates and confectionary since 1997. From liquorice and nougat, to chocolate almonds, Rocky Road, Turkish Delight and HoneyComb, the treats we have are endless! Treat yourself today by visiting us in store! We can also deliver anywhere in the Darwin CBD or Northern suburbs. Give us a call to place an order! About Us Family Owned Since 1997 Pure Indulgence was established in 1997 to provide Darwin locals a taste of luxury. Our beautifully hand-crafted chocolates are made with Australian ingredients, providing a smooth and rich taste. We take pride in our high-quality treats and excellent customer service. We believe everyone should get a taste of our delicious chocolates and lollies, which is why we also offer deliveries across the Darwin CBD and northern suburbs. So, if you can’t make it to our store but you’ve got the chocolate cravings, just give us a call and we’ll be at your doorstep in no time. Our Products Chocolates Chocolates Handmade with Love Our chocolates are freshly made using Australian ingredients. Treat yourself or someone special to our beautifully crafted chocolates, gift boxes, and figurines. Lollies Lollies Spoil Yourself Chocolates not your thing? We also have a wide range of lollies including nougat, licorice, rocky road, honeycomb and Turkish delight. We’ve got something for everyone! Deliveries Deliveries Australian Made Treats What’s better than chocolates and lollies? Chocolates and lollies delivered to your door! We can deliver anywhere in the Darwin CBD and northern suburbs. Call us today. Expert Chocolatiers Beautifully Hand-Crafted Chocolates Our specialty chocolate shop stocks over 200 varieties of handmade chocolates from award-winning chocolatiers. These Belgian-style chocolates include everything from traditional chocolates, smooth caramels and fruit-flavoured centres to creamy truffles and nutty pralines. Select one for a taster, or have your selection boxed or in a gift basket. Our expert chocolatiers have curated delicious chocolates made with Australian ingredients. As a family-owned business since 1997, we take great pride in our store and we’re passionate in delivering high quality chocolates and confectionaries. From Honeycomb to Liquorice, there’s something for everyone at Pure Indulgence. With deliveries available, there’s no excuse to not try our chocolates. Visit us in store to see the full range of treats available! homepage_content: Home - Rapid Response Locksmiths Rapid Response Locksmiths CONTACT US Rapid Response Locksmiths CONTACT US Rapid Response Locksmiths CONTACT US When You Want The Best 24/7 Service We can respond to your emergency at any hour of the day or night with our mobile locksmith service. No After Hours Call Out Fees Because the last thing you need when you get locked out is the added expense of an after hours call out charge. Fast & Professional We pride ourselves on our fast & efficient service without compromising on customer satisfaction. Fully Licensed We are one of few locksmiths in Adelaide that hold a current security & investigation agents license and are members of the Locksmith Guild of Australia. About Us Rapid Response Locksmiths is a mobile locksmith service providing expert security solutions to the city of Adelaide and surrounding suburbs. As the name suggests, we are committed to providing a fast and efficient service without compromising on customer satisfaction, so you can be sure that the service you receive will be both friendly and professional. Call Us Now! Flat Rate Call Fee CALL NOW ENQUIRE NOW Our Services Lock Outs Broken Keys Locks Changed Automotive car transponder keys and remotes made and copied Restricted Keys & ETSA Keys Security Evaluations We Work With All Industries Domestic Commercial Industrial Automotive Our Process 1. Contact Us 2. Free On-site Consult 3. Quote 4. Acceptance 5. Installation For all residential and commercial jobs, we offer a free on-site consultation where we complete a thorough inspection of your current security measures or damaged fittings, before providing you with an affordable and competitive quote to install or fix any necessary elements. Should you accept the quote, we will begin the process of installation or repair at your earliest convenience, before signing off on the job when we are 100% satisfied with it’s quality. You can trust Rapid Response Locksmiths to do the job quickly and to the highest industry standard, every time. Reviews An incredibly pleasant tradesperson, obviously talented at what he does. homepage_content: Fresh Provisions - Online Catering Store Search give us your feedback We would love to hear from you Catering for you Drool over this selection Be part of the winning team Fancy your food? Join us! Be part of the story Get your product in store Why Choose Us At Fresh Provisions, we demonstrate our passion for food by helping customers meet their dietary or ethical food requirements. We provide a range of specialty products which include seasonal and locally produced fresh foods, a range of organics, fermented, gluten free and vegan goodies to mention a few. Fresh Provisions’ emphasis is on making sure that our products are of the freshest and finest quality and that you receive value beyond the price at the checkout. We would love to help you find that special ingredient to make a favourite dish or that hip and happening trendy food fad that just kicked off last night. Boasting an extensive range of gourmet and everyday products, we want to encourage your passion for food in the kitchen. 100% Wow for YOU A foodies paradise from the moment you step in the door with amazing displays of wonderful and different foods from our corner of the globe that combine with food experiences from all over the world. 100% Fresh for YOU The team is dedicated to ensuring that our customers have the freshest selection of products and that they are always available. 100% Local like YOU As a Western Australian business we provide 100% of our support to our local produce manufacturers who receive preferential treatment from us. 100% Healthy for YOU We understand that our customer’s value is above price. Healthy happy tummies bring about healthy happy brains and our wonderful products deliver goodness to both! 100% Chic for YOU Food is fashion now and we know you want to be seen with all of the ‘in-vogue’ foods, especially when you rely on us most. 100% Made for YOU We are always listening to our customers to develop our product range and are widely recognised as the ‘go to place’ for that ‘something special.’ When we returned from three years in Melbourne one of the first things I did was go to Fresh Provisions in Bicton, even though we now live in Rivervale and its a half hour drive. Dragitsa and all the lovely staff serving behind the deli make it a pleasure to shop there and the food is out of this world. Way better than any similar food store in the upmarket areas of Melbourne. Top class. Louise Ashby 5 ⭐️ ⭐️ ⭐️ ⭐️ ⭐️ A great place to find a wide range organic and gluten free products. All clearly labelled to save time. Opening hours are convenient. Staff are always friendly and helpful. Products are fresh, clean and tidy. Cant rate this shop enough. Whether you’re hitting strength, cardio, or recovery, Jandakot gives you everything you need to keep moving forward—no distractions, just results. Ensuring Your Investment: The Importance of Home Inspections with R & E Petersen Pty Ltd Planning to purchase your dream home or make a smart property investment? It’s an exciting milestone, but ensuring your future property is up to standard is a step you shouldn’t overlook. That’s where R & E Petersen Pty Ltd comes in. With decades of experience, we provide thorough inspections to protect your investment and deliver peace of mind. Rex brings over 40 years of expertise in detailed reporting, while Mark adds 10 years of full-time experience as a registered builder and inspector. We are fully insured, giving you added security that your inspection is backed by the right protections. When choosing an inspector, it’s important to confirm they are also fully insured and hold a full unlimited building registration, not all inspectors do. Together, we bring unmatched knowledge and attention to detail, ensuring your property meets the highest standards before you take the next big step. Our Core Services At R & E Petersen Pty Ltd, we offer a wide range of inspection services tailored to meet the unique needs of every property buyer: Pre-Purchase Inspections Before you finalise any purchase, our pre-purchase inspection service ensures that you are fully aware of the property’s condition. We meticulously assess the building’s structure, systems, and finishes to uncover any hidden issues that could impact your investment. This thorough evaluation can save you from unexpected repairs and costly surprises down the line. Section 137B Owner Builder Report This report examines the quality of work carried out by the owner builder. This report covers any work that has not been carried out by a registered builder and does include but is not limited to: painting both internally and externally, new floor coverings, kitchen, bathroom and laundry renovations/upgrades. Although not all building works require permits, a lot of these works do require plumbing certificates, electrical safety certificates and even waterproofing certificates to be provided. These inspection reports cover works that were done by the current owners within the last 6 1/2 years and if these works cost more than $16,000 then owner builder insurance is required to have been obtained. Insurance is not required if the works were completed between 6 years and 61/2 years ago however the inspection report is still required. It is important to note that an owner builder inspection report is not a substitute for a building permit and this paperwork will be contained in your Section 32 to provide to prospective buyers. New Home Stage Inspections Our expertise shines in conducting new home stage inspections, which are carried out at various stages of the construction process. By evaluating the property at different stages, we identify any defects or areas requiring attention early on. This proactive approach enables builders to rectify issues promptly, ensuring that your new home is built to the highest standards. The practical completion inspection at the end of the build assess each property as per the Guide to Standards and Tolerances 2015 and also the relevant Australian standards, this assessment does provide a notation to the relevant page, chapter and note that the refers to the defect. Commercial Building Inspections We don’t just cater to residential properties; our commercial building inspection services are designed for businesses looking to invest in commercial real estate. Our detailed inspections assess structural integrity, compliance with safety regulations, and overall condition, giving business owners the assurance they need to move forward confidently. Maintenance Reports For existing homeowners, our maintenance reports are invaluable in identifying potential problems before they escalate. Regular inspections can help homeowners stay ahead of necessary repairs and maintenance tasks, preserving the integrity of the property and enhancing its value over time. Additional Services We also provide a variety of additional services, including pool barrier safety inspections, we can also put you in contact with pest inspectors and we are available to discuss issues /concerns you may have that relate to building defects. Our goal is to provide a comprehensive suite of inspection services to ensure every aspect of your property is thoroughly evaluated. The Importance of New Home Inspections Understanding the significance of home inspections cannot be overstated. When investing in a property, either a new build or a an existing dwelling, it is essential to have a clear picture of the construction quality and any defects that may exist so you can have a clear picture of works that are required to protect your investment and an indication of costs that may be incurred in these rectification works. We can also provide you with the names of trades that can provide you with quotes and expertise in relation to these works. Comprehensive Assessment : Our inspections cover every aspect of the property, including structural integrity, compliance with building codes, and the quality of workmanship. This thorough approach ensures that you are not left with any unanswered questions. Identifying Issues Early : This relates to new builds only and by conducting inspections at various stages of construction, we can identify defects and issues before they become costly repairs. This early detection allows for timely corrections, ensuring your new home is safe and secure. Peace of Mind : Buying a new home is one of the most significant investments you will make. Our detailed reports provide clarity and confidence in your purchase, allowing you to move forward with peace of mind. Our Core Services If you are considering a new home purchase or require inspection services, don’t hesitate to reach out to the experts at R & E Petersen Pty Ltd. Our team, Mark and Rex are dedicated to providing you with the highest level of service and expertise in the industry. For more information about our inspection services, please call us at 0418 508 112 or email us at libbypetersen@bigpond.com . Let us help you make an informed decision and ensure your investment is protected for years to come. It identifies hidden issues or defects, helping you make an informed decision and avoid costly repairs later. What does a new home stage inspection involve? A new home stage inspection assesses the property at various construction stages, checking for compliance with building codes and quality of workmanship to catch issues early. What is included in a Section 137B Owner Builder Report? A Section 137B Owner Builder Report evaluates compliance and quality of work by an owner-builder, ensuring adherence to building codes and safety regulations. homepage_content: Home - Spinifex Motel & Serviced Apartments - Mt Isa 07 4749 2944 admin@spinifexmotel.com.au Slide Welcome to Spinifex Motel & Serviced Apartments - Mt Isa, QLD The Spinifex motel was specifically designed by its owner who had travelled extensively throughout Queensland, NSW, the Northern Territory and Western Australia for more than thirty years. He incorporated all the features he believed a motel should have to provide the best accommodation for the business traveller to feal relaxed and at home. Added to this he has appointed managers that are down to earth people who would cater to the needs of our guests with a ready smile. As Mt Isa's newest accommodation, Spinifex Motel & Serviced Apartments is equipped with modern facilities including LCD TV's, DVD players, Austar and our licenced Maggie's Bar. Coupled with the very best in hospitality, Spinifex Motel & Serviced Apartments is the perfect accommodation solution in Mount Isa. Privately owned and not part of chain, we specialise in personalising your stay. This coupled with its convenient location makes it ideal for the corporate traveller or holiday maker. We are only 3 minutes from the train station and 10 minutes from the airport. Whether you're staying for business or pleasure, Spinifex Motel & Serviced Apartments has a room to suit you. We offer executive rooms, deluxe rooms, adjoining rooms and disabled access rooms. Comfortable Rooms All our rooms are spotlessly clean and feature reverse cycle air-conditioning High Speed Internet Ideally suited to the traveling worker Reception Hours Our reception desk is open from 7:30am to 8:00pm every day Our Available Rooms The motel has 34 large executive King & Queen rooms including 2 Disabled & 2 Family rooms which can sleep up to 2 adults and 2 children. All rooms have a kitchenette, LCD Tvs, Foxtel, Free Wifi & Aircon. Rooms are serviced daily and are supplied with a range of complimentary amenities. homepage_content: Taro's Ramen e-shopping Skip to content Item added to your cart View cart Check out Continue shopping Taro's Ramen Australia's Best Ramen to Brisbane. That's our mission. CURRENT DEALS For more information ABOUT In 2010, we set on a mission to provide Australia’s best ramen to Brisbane. We're committed to using the freshest, highest quality ingredients, sourcing locally whenever possible. Each component of our ramen is handcrafted, and our recipes are continuously refined. We prioritize food safety and ethical sourcing, avoiding harmful additives and supporting farmers who prioritize animal welfare. Our service combines traditional Japanese hospitality with a relaxed, friendly Brisbane atmosphere. We believe in a win-win philosophy, aiming to benefit our customers, suppliers, employees, and the business itself. name: The Gardens Club
homepage_content: Homepage - The Gardens Club Skip to content Welcome To The Gardens Club Nestled within Brisbane City’s Botanic Gardens, our café and event space prioritises community and connection. As a registered not-for-profit charity, we are dedicated to providing employment and training opportunities for individuals facing barriers. Book Now Café Join us for a coffee and bite to eat in the stunning Brisbane City Botanic Gardens with outdoor and verandah seating available. Learn More Celebrate with us Planning your next corporate workshop, a stunning celebratory event, or even looking to have your wedding in the Brisbane City Botanic Gardens, then we would love to speak with you! Learn More Picnic baskets Enjoy a beautiful day in Brisbane City’s Botanic Gardens with one of our hand crafted picnic baskets Learn More About US THE GARDENS CLUB is an initiative of Wise Foundation The Gardens Club is an initiative of Wise Foundation, a not-for-profit registered charity. We operate programs designed to assist those in the community facing barriers to employment. The Wise Hospitality Program, operated at The Gardens Club, provides 3 months of employment and training to individuals from refugee and asylum seeker backgrounds. Book Now

If parking, take note of half hour restrictions on weekdays with unrestricted access on weekends. ​ We are proud to be on Gadigal Land. We acknowledge the Gadigal people, Traditional Custodians of the Land, and offer our respect to their Elders past and present. We extend our respect to Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander people everywhere. We are all Redleaf Cafe Anchor 1 Anchor 2 Anchor 3 Anchor 4 bottom of page

name: The Royal on the Waterfront
homepage_content: The Royal: Your Local Waterfront Hero in East Perth - Pub Food & Drinks Skip to: Home Content Footer navigation Get $10 off your first order with The Pass - Download the app - Your Local Waterfront Hero In East Perth! An iconic local pub, set on Royal Street, East Perth. The Royal is your home away from home – a place to gather, drink and dine no matter the occasion. Dine against the backdrop of Perth’s best waterfront views at The Royal Restaurant. Our diverse menu boasts quality pub classics and modern Australian dishes showcasing the best in Western Australian produce. With a mix of indoor and outdoor spaces, quality pub food crafted from fresh seasonal produce, and an extensive selection of wine and craft beer, you won’t want to go anywhere else. The Royal is your home away from home – a place to gather, drink and dine no matter the occasion. Dine against the backdrop of Perth’s best waterfront views at The Royal Restaurant. Our diverse menu boasts quality pub classics and modern Australian dishes showcasing the best in Western Australian produce. name: The Terrace Restaurant and Bar
homepage_content: Tavola restaurant - Ballina Byron Islander Resort Tavola Restaurant Tavola Restaurant & Wine Bar Dine poolside in Ballina’s tropical heart Relaxed, fresh, and locally inspired. Tucked beside the lagoon-style pool and lush tropical gardens of the Islander Resort, The Tavola Restaurant & Wine Bar is one of the most relaxed places to eat in Ballina, offering seasonal breakfast and dinner menus inspired by the Northern Rivers region. Whether you’re staying onsite or visiting from around Ballina, you’re welcome to join us for breakfast, dinner, or drinks at the bar. Enjoy our All You Can Eat – Pizza and Pasta every night from 5pm to 7pm, 7 days a week. After 7pm, indulge in Chef Jason’s signature seasonal menu, available as an optional paid upgrade. All stays include a continental breakfast, with the option to upgrade to a breakfast and dinner package for even more value during your visit. Book a table Or call (02) 5711 2006 for bookings & enquiries. Opening Hours Operation hours Monday – Sunday Breakfast 7:00 – 9:30 am Dinner 5:00 – 8:30 pm View the Menu About the Tavola Restaurant & Bar The Tavola is a relaxed, modern à la carte restaurant that reflects the clean, green ethos of the Northern Rivers. Our chefs craft seasonal menus using fresh, locally sourced ingredients, including seafood from across the road at Northern Rivers Seafood and artisan coffee from Knockrow Ridge. Expect creative, modern fare with vegetarian, gluten-free, and dairy-free options available. We’re happy to accommodate dietary needs, just ask our friendly team. Dine indoors or alfresco under the covered courtyard by the pool. Walk-ins are welcome, but bookings are recommended during peak times. Looking for a great dinner in Ballina? Our á la carte dinner menu showcases local seafood, gluten-free options, and premium Northern Rivers produce. Our all-you-can-eat pizza and pasta is the perfect choice for big appetites. The Tavola is located within the Ballina-Byron Islander Resort and Conference Centre, just a few minutes’ drive from the Ballina CBD. Address: 1 Ronan Place, West Ballina NSW (inside Ballina Byron Islander Resort) Phone: (02) 5711 2006 Locally Sourced, Seasonally Inspired We’re proud to work with local producers and change our menu seasonally based on what’s freshest — but we also keep a few long-time guest favourites on standby. Our dishes are prepared with love, plated with care, and served in a setting designed to help you slow down and savour the moment. Group bookings and private functions are welcome — just give us a call to discuss your event needs. Note: Our menu may change slightly from day to day depending on what fresh ingredients are available. Subscribe for local-only specials, Cucina banquets, and early access to our festive events. Why dine at the tavola restaurant Tranquil poolside setting Vegetarian, gluten & dairy free options Walk-ins welcome, bookings preferred Friendly service & casual atmosphere Convenient location just off the main road in Ballina Catering for Events & Groups Hosting a celebration, conference, or group retreat? The Tavola Restaurant offers flexible catering options for onsite events at the Islander Resort. From casual cocktail functions in the Wine Bar to elegant group dinners or tailored menus for weddings and corporate events, our team works closely with you to create a dining experience that suits your occasion. Whether it’s a shared platter, set menu, or bespoke multi-course meal, we’ll ensure your guests enjoy fresh, locally inspired food served with warm, professional service. Our Catering Room Service, Delivered Fresh to Your Door Prefer to dine in? Guests staying at the Islander Resort can enjoy the full Tavola Restaurant and Bar menu from the comfort of their room. Whether you’re after a relaxed breakfast, a quiet dinner, or a late-night treat, our in-room dining service brings fresh, locally-inspired meals right to your door. Just scan the QR code to order during restaurant hours — we’ll take care of the rest. FAQs What kind of food does The Tavola Restaurant serve? Tavola offers modern Australian cuisine inspired by Northern Rivers produce, including local seafood, vegetarian, gluten-free, and dairy-free dishes. Menus change seasonally to showcase what’s freshest from local suppliers. Is Tavola open to the public or only resort guests? Tavola is open to everyone — guests, locals, and visitors from nearby towns like Byron Bay and Lennox Head. Walk-ins are welcome, and bookings are recommended during busy times. What are the opening hours? Breakfast: 7:00 – 9:30 am Lunch: 12:00 – 2:00 pm Dinner: 5:00 – 9:00 pm (Sun–Thu) and 5:00 – 9:30 pm (Fri–Sat). The Wine Bar opens from 5:30 pm Monday–Saturday, closed Sundays and public holidays. What is the all-you-can-eat pizza and pasta offer? Every night from 5 pm – 7 pm, Tavola serves all-you-can-eat pizza and pasta. After 7 pm, guests can upgrade to Chef Jason’s seasonal à la carte menu for an elevated dining experience. Does the restaurant cater to dietary requirements? Yes — Tavola’s menu includes vegetarian, gluten-free, and dairy-free options, and the team is happy to accommodate additional dietary needs on request. Can I dine by the pool or outdoors? Yes — guests can dine alfresco beside the lagoon-style pool or under the covered courtyard surrounded by tropical gardens. Indoor seating is also available. Does Tavola take group bookings or host events? Yes — Tavola provides group dining and event catering for weddings, conferences, and private celebrations, with set menus, buffets, and custom catering options. Is room service available from the restaurant? Yes — guests staying at the Islander Resort can order from the full Tavola menu via in-room QR code during restaurant hours, with meals delivered fresh to their door. What local ingredients does Tavola use? Tavola proudly sources seafood from Northern Rivers Seafood, artisan coffee from Knockrow Ridge, and seasonal produce from nearby farms and markets. Is there a bar on site? Yes — the Tavola Wine Bar opens from 5:30 pm Monday – Saturday, offering boutique wines, cocktails, beers, and light snacks in a relaxed, poolside setting. Can I book a private dining area? Yes — private dining can be arranged for small groups, functions, or special occasions. Contact the restaurant directly on (02) 6686 8866 to discuss your event needs. Where is Tavola located? Tavola is inside the Ballina Byron Islander Resort & Conference Centre, 1 Ronan Place, West Ballina NSW, just a few minutes’ drive from the Ballina CBD. × Become a Tavola Member Unlock exclusive dining perks & VIP offers.

Welcome To Truly Asia Hervey Bay ! (Previously Whale Bay Asian) - A modern Asian Fusion Cuisine! At Truly Asia , our extensive menu focuses on the flavours and ingredients of Asian fusion. By taking the elements from different Asian cuisines our chef combines them to create dishes with unique flavours and textures, and use different cooking techniques to bring out the best in each dish. The result is an exciting mix of flavours and ingredients like never before seen or tasted . ​ Come along and enjoy, prepared for you by our master chef with over 20 years experience, their food is assured to delight your taste buds. And, our service is second to none! ​ Kind regards! ​ Head Chef Song (Malaysia n, 20+ years experience) Chef Uncle Nop (Thai, 30+ years experience) Chef Liang, Chef Hao & Chef Mark (Malaysian, 20+ years experience) Chef Gindi (Indian, 8 years experience) Chef Jordan ( Australian, 4 years experience) Maria (floor manager) DRESS CODE humble request (dinner only) We are a family restaurant Parents please be considerate of other customers & refrain children from running around. * Reservation required, Please inform us if you are bringing a dog with you, for unforeseen events. * Please keep your dog on a leash and under control at all times. * It is your responsibility to clean it up after your dog, bag it & bin it. ADDRESS & CONTACT ​ At the Marina, 11 Buccaneer Drive, Urangan, Hervey Bay, QLD 4655 ​ PH: 07 - 4125 5599 (Primary) Mobile: 0417 073 391 ​ Email: trulyasiahb@outlook.com ​ Website: www.trulyasiaherveybay.com WHERE ARE WE? name: Yarra Glen Cafe
homepage_content: Yarra Glen Cafe | Cafe & Restaurant | Thai restaurant. Cafe & Restaurant See Menu & Order Booking Table Welcome to the Yarra Glen Cafe The historic Yarra Glen Cafe is located in the 160 year old William Herbert farm house in the main street of Yarra Glen. This beautiful building features exquisite original artworks on display by local artist Veronica Holland plus original photos of Yarra Glen from Yesteryear. We pride ourselves on our quality menu, featuring great quality traditional house made cafe food using a great selection of local ingredients. The cafe is located 40 kms north east of Melbourne in the beautiful Yarra Valley which is well known for its wineries, gardens and outdoor activities. Catering Thai Dinner Friday & Saturday 5:00 pm to 8:30 pm​ The Yarra Glen Cafe serves only the finest coffee from Segafredo, Italian Heritage and Australian Roasted. Segafredo has been growing and roasting coffee beans for generations, perfecting the artisan craft since 1970. Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet, consectetur adipiscing elit. Read More 1 October, 2025 - 31 January, 2026 $7 Resch's ALL DAY EVERYDAY Read More SHOW MORE WELCOME TO THE CASTLEREAGH Bevs . Bites . Banter Discover The Castlereagh, where dining meets elegance. On level 1, our bistro offers a relaxed dining atmosphere with warm friendly service. Indulge in our modern Australian cuisine, meticulously crafted by Head Chef Peter, featuring daily specials and unpretentious dishes. Join us for Tight Ass Tuesday and enjoy fantastic $18 deals, or unwind during our $10 Happy Hour with refreshing Margaritas. Our venue boasts versatile spaces perfect for any function, including a private wine room for intimate gatherings and the sun parlour for more expansive events. Whether you’re planning a corporate meeting, a social celebration, or a special occasion, our flexible spaces can be tailored to meet your needs. For fitness enthusiasts, The Castlereagh is home to a state-of-the-art World Gym spread over two floors. Open 24 hours, our gym offers a wide range of equipment and personal trainers to keep you in peak condition. Come and experience fitness at its finest right here at The Castlereagh.

homepage_content: Eat & Drink | The Art Gallery of Western Australia Eat & Drink Plan Your Visit Design Store AGWA Rooftop Eat & Drink Accessibility Venue Hire Stay in WA If you’re looking for a casual drink or bite to eat, visit the AGWA Cafe and Bar or AGWA Rooftop Bar. AGWA Cafe and Bar AGWA Cafe and Bar offers coffee, juices, toasties, and sweet treats throughout the day, with a bar drinks menu available in the afternoons. Opening Hours 10am-5pm, Wednesday-Monday. FOOD MENU DRINKS MENU Book Now AGWA Rooftop With 360-degree views of Perth AGWA Rooftop opens up a whole new space for enjoying arts and entertainment in WA. The AGWA Rooftop Bar features food and beverages with a distinct WA flavour. Open from 4pm Friday and Saturday, enjoy a sunset drink taking in the city views and sculpture park with laid-back beats. AGWA Rooftop Bar Hours AGWA Rooftop Bar is currently closed. We’re working on a new, fresh and fabulous look for the AGWA Rooftop Bar, coming Spring/Summer 2026. name: Bentley Bakery
homepage_content: Bakery - Bentley Park, QLD 4869 Bentley Bakery A locally owned bakery bringing you nostalgic Australian bakery favourites Contact Us Thank you! Your enquiry has been sent successfully. Your Name Email Address Message Loading... Submit Address Shop 7/96 McLaughlin Rd, Bentley Park QLD 4865 Phone 0402 924 995 Email admin@bentleybakery.com.au ABN 33684258419 Operating Hours 6am - 3pm Monday - Friday 7am - 1pm Saturday Closed Sunday & Public Holidays About Us Bringing Back the Classics – Just South of Cairns Welcome to your local Bentley Park bakery, where nostalgia is baked fresh every day. We’re proudly locally owned and community focused, serving up the traditional Aussie treats you grew up with and still love today. Our premium Cheesy Pork Sausage Rolls and Slow Cooked Beef Pies are made using quality meat from Greenwood’s Butchers — packed with flavour and proudly crafted in-house. Craving variety? Our full pie range includes Chilli, Steak & Kidney, Pea, Curry, Mushroom, and classic Plain Mince hot, hearty, and ready to go. Sweet tooth calling? You’ll find all your favourites: Lamingtons, vanilla slice (yes, the beloved snot block - no icing, just the way it should be!), pavlova, lemon meringue tarts, Biscoff brownies, and fresh-baked muffins. We’ve got your cream-filled cravings covered too — indulge in our long cream donuts (Long Johns), cream buns, and apple turnovers , all filled with real fresh cream — no mock cream here! Love a gooey centre? Our Nutella donuts and Nutella danishes are a fan favourite - or try our caramel and apple danishes for the ultimate bakery indulgence. Need a caffeine fix? We serve fresh coffee roasted with White Whale beans , made just how you like it - with your choice of Oat, Soy, Almond or Lactose-Free milk. After something cooler? Grab an iced latte for that perfect FNQ refresher. And don’t forget the essentials! We bake fresh White, Wholemeal & Grain Bread daily. To avoid disappointment, pre-order your loaves or rolls ahead of time. Hosting an event? Contact us to arrange a custom bread or roll order. Whether you’re a Bentley Park local or just passing through, stop in and enjoy friendly service, fresh flavours, and a true taste of Aussie tradition — just a short drive south from Cairns. name: Griffith Tourism Hub
homepage_content: Home - Visit Griffith Welcome to Griffith A cultural oasis in the heart of regional NSW Griffith is one of Australia’s most vibrant cosmopolitan centres. With a population of 27,000, Griffith exudes a rich blend of cultures and traditions, with more than 60 nationalities adding to our cultural tapestry. Once you visit Griffith we know you will feel at home, especially when you’ve had a taste of our genuine hospitality. our history Experience Griffith Experience amazing food and wine With great local food producers, wineries and passionate chefs, Griffith has become the new destination for foodies. Explore More Outstanding local experiences A vibrant regional centre bursting with life and energy. Explore More Griffith Spring Fest 12 - 25 October 2025 Explore More Griffith Easter Party 2 - 5 April 2026 Explore More A Taste of Italy Griffith 24 - 30 August 2026 Explore More What's on in Griffith Major event campaigns, community festivals, circus, theatre, sporting events, markets and more, we have a huge range of experiences for everyone. Explore More So much to see and do Whether you’re into food and wine, the great outdoors, or art and culture; Griffith has it all. The annual festivals are a wonderful time to visit as they showcase our local food and world class wines, friendly people and colourful cultures. Visit in October for Griffith Spring Fest where you will witness over 70 large citrus sculptures line the main street. Or immerse yourself in our authentic culture in August at A Taste of Italy Griffith. homepage_content: Art Gallery of Ballarat – Black Mist Burnt Country Operation Hurricane (detail), Kate Downhill Art Gallery of Ballarat 3 December 2016 – 5 February 2017 Venue info: 40 Lydiard St North Ballarat, VIC Ph 03 5320 5858 www.artgalleryofballarat.com.au Opening Hours Daily, 10am – 5pm (closed Christmas Day and Boxing Day) Maps were disabled by the visitor on this site. Click to open the map in a new window. Reviews Konrad Marshall, The Good Weekend 4 February 2017 View PDF Previous Next Program Wednesday, 30 November 2016, 5-6.30 pm One Step Closer New international initiatives to prohibit nuclear weapons On 27 October the United Nations General Assembly adopted a landmark resolution to launch negotiations on a treaty outlawing nuclear weapons. 123 nations voted in favour of the resolution (Austria was among the co-sponsors). Yet, most nuclear-armed nations voted against the UN resolution as did most of their allies, including nearly all NATO members. Australia also voted against the resolution. An expert panel will give an overview of the efforts which led to this new initiative and analyse the resolution in view of future negotiations in 2017 for a legally binding instrument to prohibit nuclear weapons, leading towards their total elimination. Panelists: Dr Phoebe Wynn-Pope , Director of Humanitarian Law and Movement, Relations, Australian Red Cross Dr Bernhard Zimburg , Ambassador Austrian Embassy Canberra Prof Richard Tanter , School of Political and Social Studies at the University of Melbourne Assoc. Prof. Dr Tilman Ruff , Co-president of International Physicians for the Prevention of Nuclear War Tim Wright , Asia-Pacific Director of the International Campaign to Abolish Nuclear Weapons (ICAN) Moderate: Bishop Philip Huggins , Oodthenong area of episcopal car e Sunday 4 December 2016, 3 pm Official Exhibition Opening Saturday, 10 December 2016, 11 am Guided tour with the curator An overview of artwork in the exhibition with exhibition curator JD Mittmann and an insight in the artistic responses to the British atomic tests in Australia 60 years ago. Saturday, 10 December 2016, 2 pm Author Liz Tynan launches her book “Atomic Thunder – The Maralinga Story” In 1950 Australian prime minister Robert Menzies blithely agreed to atomic tests in Australia and relinquished control over them. In this new book Journalist and academic Elizabeth Tynan reveals the devastating consequences of that decision, and how Maralinga has continued to be shrouded in mystery decades after the atomic thunder stopped rolling across the South Australian test site. www.newsouthbooks.com.au/books/atomic-thunder/ Film Screenings at M.A.D.E. Museum of Australian Democracy at Eureka, Ballarat Sunday, 11 December 2016, 1 pm Backs to the Blast: An Australian Nuclear Story Dir. Harry Bardwell 52 min, Australia 1981 A documentary history of the uranium and nuclear industry in South Australia from 1910 to 1980. Incorporates rare archival footage and contemporary interviews with workers, scientists and politicians, presenting an analysis of the effects of uranium and its products. Provides a detailed examination of the uranium mine at Radium Hill, the uranium oxide refinery at Port Pirie and the British atomic weapons test site at Maralinga. Sunday, 18 December 2016, 1 pm Silent Storm Dir. Peter Butt 52 min, Australia 2003 Set against a backdrop of the Cold War, the saga follows scientist Hedley Marston’s attempt to blow the whistle on radioactive fallout from the British atomic tests in Australia. His claims that cities and grazing lands were contaminated and that Strontium 90 was in the milk supply were disputed, but the government’s own bone surveys proved his assertion right. Sunday, 15 January 2017, 1 pm Half Life: A Parable for the Nuclear Age Dir. Dennis O’Rourke 84 min, Australia 1985 Between 1946 and 1958 the U.S. Atomic Energy Commission exploded at least 66 nuclear devices in the Marshall Islands, contaminating them for centuries to come. This film is about the devastating effects of radiation on the islanders. In the course of his investigations, the filmmaker found that the official view of the tests was unsustainable. Won the Peace Film Award in 1986 at the Berlin International Film Festival. Sunday, 22 January 2017, 1 pm Nobody told us anything Dir. Charles Stewart 96 min, United Kingdom 2014 Between 1952 and 1967, in the largest Tri-Service operation since the D-Day landings, over 20,000 servicemen participated in British Nuclear Weapons Tests. The 2011 British Nuclear Test Veterans Health Needs Audit shows that a daunting shadow still hangs over the Veterans. This documentary tells that story in archive footage and candid interviews with the survivors and their children. Sunday, 29 January 2017, 1 pm Australian Atomic Confessions (with film maker Kathy Aigner) Dir. Gregory K. Young 50 min, Australia 2005 Documentary about the compelling story of the 12 British atomic bomb tests in the 1950s, discussed by Aboriginal elders, veterans, experts and the premier of South Australia. With the building of a new 500 million dollar nuclear reactor in a Sydney suburb, the expansion of more multi-national uranium mines and the associated poisoning of the Great Artesian Basin, reflecting about nuclear energy uses is now as important as ever. name: BSKT Cafe
homepage_content: Cafe Nobby Beach - All Day Breakfast Lunch Coffee & Alcohol | BSKT Skip to content Restaurant Home bskt-manager 2025-05-24T21:27:50+10:00 THE BEST BEACHSIDE CAFE – NOBBY BEACH Gold Coast's #1 Health Cafe BSKT (biscuit) was founded in 2013 as a destination for delicious & healthy food on the Gold Coast, Australia. View Our Menu About Us Family owned & operated, supported by a wonderful team of friendly staff. We simply believe in living a healthy lifestyle with delicious food & being grateful for the life we live. Great coffee, great people, in a great location! Welcome BSKT is a beachside health cafe with a difference. Located at Nobby Beach, we are puppy friendly & family orientated with a children’s outside play area. We offer an extensive food & drinks menu & cater to all dietary types. Gluten Free • Vegan • Vegetarian • Keto • Paleo Bookings We are generally a walk-in be seated kind of establishment, however if you have a group of 6 or more we would be happy to reserve a table. We also have an area available for casual events for 30 people max. Please SMS the cafe direct to check on availability – 0455 266 544 No bookings available on Public Holidays. Welcome BSKT is a beachside health cafe with a difference. Located at Nobby Beach, we are puppy friendly & family orientated with a children’s outside play area. We offer an extensive food & drinks menu & cater to all dietary types. Gluten Free • Vegan • Vegetarian • Keto • Paleo About Us Family owned & operated, supported by a wonderful team of friendly staff. We simply believe in living a healthy lifestyle with delicious food & being grateful for the life we live. Great coffee, great people, in a great location! Bookings We are generally a walk-in be seated kind of establishment. When you arrive at BSKT just come to the front area and we will take you to the next available table. If you have a group of 8 or more we would be happy to reserve a table. This will however be subject to availability on the day. Please SMS the cafe direct on 0455 266 544 to check on availability. No bookings available at all on public holidays. All Day Breakfast Menu Granola Bowl 18 18 BSKT Fruit & Nut Granola, Coconut Yoghurt, Fresh Apple, Goji, Blueberry & Strawberry BSKT Breaky Burrito 16 16 BSKT Beans, Scrambled Eggs, Spinach, Cheese Vegan Huevos Rancheros 24 24 Corn Tortilla, Breaky Beans, Avo Salsa, Jalapeno, Chipotle Mayo, Fresh Greens & Spiced Tofu Scramble Opening Hours BSKT is open from 6am for all day breakfast and lunch. We offer take away coffee, all day breakfast and lunch from 10.30am. Online ordering for pick up available through View Menu link. Kitchen closes at 2pm everyday & coffee til 2.30pm. Mon- Sun 6am – 2.30pm Public Holidays 6am – 2pm 0455 266 544 VIEW OUR MENU BSKT Healthy Benny Poached Free Range Eggs on Rye Sourdough served on Fresh Spinach Your choice of Grilled Ham, Smoked Salmon, or Bacon Topped with Kalenaise, Turmeric Béarnaise or Spiced Tomato Mayo DF (GF V Option) EXPLORE THE MENU Nobby’s Big Breaky Poached Eggs, Tumeric & Chicken Sausages, Garlic Mushrooms, Bacon, Hash Brown, Spinach and Rye Sourdough DF (GF Option) EXPLORE THE MENU Nana Choc Nut Pancakes Vegan Choc Chip Pancakes, Banana & Nut Dukkah, Nut Butter & Chocolate Drizzle GF VG DF EXPLORE THE MENU Great Food, Great Beachside Location The Best Table In Town Enjoy great food only a stone’s throw from one of the best beach’s on the Gold Coast Explore the menu What We Offer Breakfast Spoilt for choice! Traditional favourites, tasty vegan meals, and delicious sweet brunch plates. Try our No 1 local favourite – the BSKT Healthy Benny or the Nana Choc Nut Pancakes – Gluten Free, Vegan & Dairy Free and Instagram famous! Lunch Healthy summer salads, grilled chicken burgers, miso salmon bowls, beef & prawn taco plates are some of our stand out lunch options. Vego, Vegan, Gluten Free & Dairy Free Options. We are also a licenced venue & offer beer, wine & cocktails. Oakberry #1 Açaí brand in the World. Our organic açaí bowls with unlimited toppings are now part of the healthy lifestyle of millions of people in many countries, becoming even more present amongst health-conscious individuals. Coffee Our boutique Melbourne espresso blend is bold, rich and chocolatey – and perfect for those who also love an iced long black. Our ordering system is fast & we pride ourselves in offering an extensive range of alternative milks, chilled coffee & specialty matcha drinks. Free Wifi Our Cafe is a great place to chill out or kick into work mode. We have so many different areas to the cafe you can work solo, bring a work colleague or book in a team meeting. Sip & work with Free WiFi with a relaxed vibe by the beach. What Our Locals Say Amazing little gem in Nobby Beach. The menu has anything you can wish for… they serve a variety of different dietary options and there is literally something for everyone. The location is good, parking is easy and the staff is really nice and welcoming…. of course the food was amazing as well, we even had some ocean views with it!!! We loved every minute of it and can’t wait to come back. Thanks so much BSKT Team for a lovely breakfast experience!!! homepage_content: Café Corretto – Italian restaurant Skip to content Menu CAFFE CORRETTO HISTORY The Francese family opened their first restaurant in 1971 in Melbourne, Australia. It was an instant success thanks to their authentic Italian home-style pizza and pasta, paired with warm, friendly service. Over the years, the Francese family has developed a unique Italian dining experience rooted in generations of cherished family recipes from Southern Italy. Caffè Corretto opened its doors in 1972 on the iconic Lygon Street in Carlton. Since then, it has become known for its exceptional Corretto Pizza, handmade pasta, signature parmigiana, and sizzling charcoal-grilled steaks packed with bold, unforgettable flavour. The restaurant’s vibrant atmosphere and welcoming spirit have made it a beloved destination for locals and visitors alike. Caffè Corretto takes pride in its strong ties with the community and maintains a personal connection with its guests from around the world. The restaurant enjoys a longstanding relationship with the City of Melbourne and actively supports events within the Carlton precinct. Whether it’s Australian and international singers, actors, artists, sports personalities, or long-time loyal customers, many choose to return to Caffè Corretto to enjoy a meal and share in the warmth of the Francese family’s hospitality. The mission of Caffè Corretto is simple: to serve you, and to serve you again. With three generations now involved, the family continues to uphold its legacy of traditional cuisine and authentic service, preserving the Caffè Corretto dream for future generations to enjoy, both in Australia and abroad.

name: Caffe Acqua
homepage_content: Caffe Acqua - Mount Barker Order now Book a table About Us Established in 2011, Caffe Acqua Mt Barker is a family-owned and operated cafe restaurant pizzeria. We have sourced our staff from all over Adelaide. Many have lived their whole lives locally, but some travel long distances just to work as part of our team. You will always be greeted with a smile for breakfast, lunch and dinner and our experienced chefs cater to your needs and dietary requirements as best they can. ​ We have a generous amount of seating (140 seats inside, 30 seats outside) and are happy to provide our establishment for corporate and social events, large and small. Our facilities are wheelchair friendly and the fish tank is a constant source of entertainment for the kiddies. We are also vegetarian and vegan friendly with a seasonal menu and regularly changing daily specials, with the old favourites always available. We also have every day value lunch specials and plenty of gluten-free options. Our kitchen is open all day, so you are welcome to come in for a late lunch, early dinner, brunch or snack. We serve coffee and cake throughout the day into the night and have a great selection of gelati and other desserts. homepage_content: Gip's Restaurant, Function Venue, Weddings - Toowoomba BOOKINGS GIFT VOUCHERS MODERN AUSTRALIAN CUISINE Please be advised that, in line with standard industry practice in Queensland, a 10% surcharge will apply when open on Sundays, and a 15% surcharge will apply when open on Public Holidays. Discover Gip's, a charming dining and event destination nestled in beautiful gardens and one of Toowoomba's most historic buildings. Whether you're looking to savour a delicious lunch, elegant dinner, delightful coffee, or refreshing cocktails, Gip's offers an inviting atmosphere for every occasion. Perfect for hosting business functions, celebrating weddings, or marking any event special, Gip's combines timeless elegance with exceptional service to make your moments truly memorable. Additionally, consider our catering services if you prefer to host your event at a different location. Toowoomba's Favourite Cuisine Established in 1999, Gip’s Restaurant has become an iconic part of the Toowoomba restaurant landscape. Our chef, Craig Edser and his talented team presents a creative fusion of fresh, uncomplicated dishes with a strong, modern Australian influence. BOOK NOW Button Button Weddings At GIp's A casual-style wedding in Gip’s garden restaurant area or something more refined in the majestic Clifford House or marquee; we have a style to suit your special day. More About Weddings Corporate Events From conferences and seminars to Christmas parties, Gip's is the perfect place for your next corporate event. More About Corporate Events Special Events You choose: casual-style functions in our restaurant or a more grandiose get-together in the James Taylor Room, marquee or in the garden under the lights. More About Special Events WHAT PEOPLE SAY ABOUT US Thank you again for looking after us so well for our wedding reception. It was absolutely tremendous, and our out-of-town guests were blown away by the beauty of the building and the gardens. The food was exceptional and the staff lovely. Ady & Paul, 2024 Perfect! The food was spectacular...that smokey flavour was...wow! Staff were very professional. Jemma, 2024 Our guests were raving about [the food] for hours...the steak, fish, pork belly, all top quality - not diminished at all by serving to an event in bulk. ﻿ This team clearly pride themselves on their food!! Casey, 2024 Weddings A casual-style wedding in Gip’s garden restaurant area or the majestic Clifford House adjoining the restaurant, it’s up to you. name: Cafe 102 Meal
homepage_content: Harvest Ministry of Food – Harvest Ministry of Food Skip to content Food Pantry Make an appointment Book now 5331 5957 Appointments available: Tuesday 1pm - 2pm Wednesday - 1pm - 3pm Thursday - 10am -12pm Thursday - 1pm - 3pm Contact for more information office@hilltop.church Harvest Ministry of Food We provide fruit and vegetables, frozen meals and pantry items to people in Ballarat effected by food insecurity. Whether you need a hand up while finding work, experiencing hardship with an influx of bills coming through or feeling the pinch with rising costs of living, when the question is 'what is for dinner?' we want to be part of an answer for you. Book now One of our friendly staff in the office at Hilltop.Church will answer your call and they will ask some simple questions to gauge your current situation. If you get the answering machine, please leave your name and contact number and the reason you are calling. When a time is booked, we'll let you know where the address is and what to expect. We offer a 30-minute booking where you may stay for a cuppa, a sandwich or a cup of hot soup. Here we'll get to know you and your needs, and help plan a food relief program that suits your needs. Donate We are a charity with deductible gift recipient status. If you would like to donate towards purchases of pantry and hygiene items, our Account details are Bank: Bendigo Bank Account Name: Harvest Ministry of Food BSB: 633 000 Account: 156 223 752 Ref: Pantry items or please email us for more details at office@hilltop.church See the list below for items we accept. You can bring donations to our office, please call to arrange a time. 5331 5957 We need these items: Weet Bix, Vita Brits Tin soup - tomato, chicken noodle, vegetable Long life milk Tin Fruit Tinned protein - tuna, beans, spam, stew Pasta or Rice Pasta Sauce Tin Vegetables - corn, mixed beans Snack -crackers, biscuits Tea/coffee Hygine items eg: Toothpaste, toothbrush, soap A big thank you to our major sponsor A thank you to Secondbite, FareShare and Bakers Delight Help for you Please see below for resources available in Ballarat. Anglicare Ballarat Community takeaway breakfast Monday to Friday from 8.30am to 10am 49 Lydiard Street South Ballarat Emergency food relief: 1800 809 722 Monday to Thursday from 10.30am to 12pm 14 Victoria Street Ballarat Uniting Ballarat Breezeway Meals Program Everyday 10.30am to 1pm 105 Dana Street Ballarat Central Free takeaway meals for those in crisis situations. Salvation Army Ballarat Emergency food relief: 5337 0600 Monday to Friday 9.15am to 2pm 102 Eureka Street Ballarat Café 102 Meal Tuesday and Thursday 12pm 102 Eureka St Ballarat Takeaway service outside the reception entry.

name: Heavenly Cakes and Sweets
homepage_content: Home | Heavenly Cakes and Sweets Skip to content Welcome to Heavenly Cakes and Sweets! Sweeten your celebrations with custom cakes from Heavenly Cakes and Sweets . We’re passionate about making your occasions unforgettable with the perfect cake; let’s create something beautiful together! Ready to order? Here’s how: Fill out our enquiry form with your dream cake details and event specifics. We will craft a design and provide you with an accurate quote. Thank you for your interest in our products and services. To ensure that we can respond to you in a timely and efficient manner, we kindly request that you **only fill out the form** on our website. Please do not send us private messages on social media or mobile, as we may not be able to monitor them regularly. We will get back to you as soon as possible via email or phone. Thank you for your understanding and cooperation. name: Lawash Bakery
homepage_content: Home Page - Lawash Bakery Our Story Lawash Bakery was started back in 2004 by four brothers with a common dream of serving the community with delicious and quality Afghan food. Today, we serve the community with up to 1000 handmade Flat Afghan bread (Lawash) as well as hundreds of Afghan dishes. Now, what was a dream one day has become a well-known restaurant where delicious Afghan foods are served by hundreds of South Australians on daily basis. Read more Some Google Reviews posted by our customers "Fresh bread and great range of tasty food. The combo wrap is the best ever!" Cobra30 "Food is always well prepared, good size for a great price." Nick Arman "Excellent food and fresh bread always." salmaan khan "Great people, good value for money, good portions. Best part awesome, delicious & yummy taste. Never fail to wow." Yogendra SHRESTHA "Super delicious afghani food. I buy the bread and freeze it for later too as you cant buy it in foodland anymore. Go if u love meat and bbq." jo tuckey "Taste was really good but there bread was really hard otherwise food was really good and fresh." Mateen Ahmed Read more reviews Lawash Bakery Menu We offer a range of delicious and authentic Afghan foods plus some sepcial foods and drinks/coffees Authentic Afghan Cuisine Eat delicious and authentic Afghani food served with either rice or lawash bread View the menu Specials Our special foods are designed for family or other occasions View the menu Coffee, Cakes & Drinks Destress yourself by drinking a cup of coffee or hot tea at Lawash Bakery View the menu Photo Gallery Family Qabuli Palaw × Chicken & Lamb Kebabs ×

name: Heaven Scent Flowers & Gifts
homepage_content: Florist Ingham | Heaven Scent Flowers & Gifts Skip to content Fresh Flowers Delivered Daily To Ingham and Surrounding Areas Heaven Scent Flowers is more than just a florist, specialising in individually designed floral bouquets and arrangements using the most beautiful selection of fresh flowers that arrive daily. We also have a stunning selection of silk flowers and arrangements, which can be made to suit your style and budget, as well as exquisite gifts that are sure to please and show someone how much you really care. Our talented florists have loads of experience and will help you create the perfect gift for any special event or precious moment you are celebrating. Complement any of our florals or gift baskets with a helium balloon, chocolates, a soft toy, a bottle of wine, a gift voucher, or any piece from our exquisite range of Urban Rituelle Australian-made candles, diffusers, hand and body washes, soaps, petit parfums or hand creams. All orders received by 4pm on the desired day of delivery (Monday to Friday) will be delivered to Ingham and surrounding areas. Saturday orders must be received by 11am. Deliveries to Townsville and Cardwell are available Monday through Friday for orders placed by 10:30 a.m., and same-day delivery is guaranteed. Wedding Flowers From the latest trends in nature-inspired wedding flowers to traditional rose bouquets, our experience in wedding flowers and decorating knows no bounds. We understand how important it is that everything is perfect on your most special day. To make this possible, we only use the freshest flowers and we keep our prices competitive. Make an appointment to book a wedding consultation today. Shop Online Choosing the perfect gift for any occasion has never been easier. Shop online to view our range of fresh seasonal flowers, living plants and stunning floral arrangements and bouquets. We have many options ready to go when you need them, and if you do not see what you would like, our florists are always happy to make something especially for you. Close Menu × × Cart

name: Mackay Cakes ( Exclusive Cakes 4 All )
homepage_content: Mackay Cakes: wedding cakes, birthday cakes, special occasion cakes For speciality cakes in Mackay or surrounds call Exclusive Cakes 4 All on 07 4953 1493 or 0407 580 131 Call between 7.00am to 9.00pm 7 days a week or EMAIL EXCLUSIVE CAKES 4 ALL YES WE ARE STILL OPEN! We’re happy to reassure you we still maintain an extremely high standard of hygiene and we are still open for business! Welcome to Exclusive Mackay Cakes 4 All Hello I’m Roz. You’re here for a reason right? You want a cake for a special occasion. Maybe something memorable for your dear old mum, dad or a 21st birthday cake (how great would it be to be that age again) or a beautiful wedding cake or perhaps a cake to celebrate the birth of a new baby? Now you can buy cakes in Mackay and just about anywhere so why are you considering one of my cakes? I’ll tell you what I think and believe in. A cake is not just a cake. It signifies something sacred, something dear to our hearts. Cakes celebrate life, achievement, love and death. As you can see, Mackay Cakes is very passionate about cakes. All our cakes are made with love because that’s what we love to do. I want to help you make memories that you will never forget. I will work with you to create something you and your family will be proud of. I’ve been doing that for 10 years with thousands of cakes and I’m ready to help you create a cake for your special occasion. Give me a call on 0407 580 131 and create that lifetime memory. Roz Exclusive Cakes 4 All are based in Mackay but our cakes don’t stop there! We supply cakes to Mackay, the Whitsundays, Airlie Beach, Cannonvale, Bowen, Proserpine, Sarina, Moranbah, Clermont. Testimonials I’m not quite sure where to start, but my partner & I got married yesterday, and had Roz make our wedding cake! I had one meeting with Roz and from there she made our cake a masterpiece. It was absolutely amazing to look at and even better to eat! You are the best cake maker in town & I wouldn’t recommend anyone else. ❤️❤️ Steph Fredrickson, Mackay Testimonials Roz, the cake you made for my parents 50th Wedding Anniversary was absolutely beautiful! I can’t thank you enough for the effort and quality workmanship you put into our cake, especially at such short notice. I can’t thank you enough Sonia Pace, Mackay We are so grateful for the amazing Minion Birthday cake you made for our son Sascha’s 3rd Birthday Party!!! We loved it so much we didn’t want to cut it, but then we were so glad we did because it was so delicious!! You definitely exceeded our expectations and at such short notice too. Kristine Di Carlo Testimonials Just thought I would let you know that everyone loved the cake it was a complete success and my mother was so impressed and love it also. So don’t be surprised if you may get a few orders for out here. Thank you very much again. Susan Lidel Just wanted to say a massive thank you for Brad’s cake last night. It looked amazing and tasted even better. Will definitely recommend you to everyone 🙂 Krystal Turner OMG Roz – my cake was absolutely STUNNING!! Definitely a statement piece of the night! Leanne Muscat Hi Roz just wanting to thank you for a fantastic job done on our son’s 18th Birthday cake. Everyone was raving about it at the party, it was too good to cut up and eat! Thanks again. Michelle Sanderson Just wanted to let you know how much myself and Andy loved your work on our wedding cake. It was just perfect! I couldn’t believe how amazing it looked. Thanks for all your hard work on it 🙂 Robyn Thank you so much for the lovely birthday cake on 7th April. The cake was amazing both in flavours and design and all the kids went crazy seeing the cake. Their favourite cartoon characters after all. We liked the cake too. Thank you Kajal Thank you so much for the lovely birthday cake on 7th April. The cake was amazing both in flavours and design and all the kids went crazy seeing the cake. Their favourite cartoon characters after all. We liked the cake too. Thank you Kajal Sending you two pics to let you know that the cake was amazing. Not only did it look superb it tasted amazing. Everyone was full of praise for the cake Priyank Singh I would just like to say a huge THANK YOU FROM THE BOTTOM OF OUR HEARTS! That was the most amazing cake that we have ever had and it topped our original cherry ripe mud cake ten fold. Everyone who attended our night could not stop raving about it. Once again Roz, thank you so much we both really appreciate what you did for us – it was beautiful. Bek Pace I think you done a fantastic job with the cakes roz!!! Check out the photos! We are very happy with your work and taste absolutely amazing!!!!!! Thank you so much! Rochelle WIlson Exclusive Mackay Cakes 4 All is fully licensed : Food Licence FL 2362 – Mackay Regional Council Here at Mackay Cakes , Roz understands just how important it is to spoil someone on an important day which is why she is so passionate about designing, creating and delivering your beautiful cake to your home or venue in Mackay or surrounding areas. She caters for every budget and occasion and can create your cake and deliver safely to Mackay, Sarina, Whitsundays, Airlie Beach and Moranbah. Roz is an internationally trained and qualified chef and has even represented Australia in the Culinary Olympics. She has over 25 years of culinary experience and with her creative eye for detail what better way to express this than in the creation and design of speciality cakes . She uses only the best top quality ingredients and wherever possible uses local Mackay produce. If you have any special dietary requirements this isn’t a problem just ask Roz. Exclusive Mackay Cakes 4 All makes birthday cakes in Mackay and Airlie Beach, Whitsundays, Sarina, Moranbah. wedding cakes , speciality cakes , cupcakes, corporate cakes, easter cakes, Christmas cakes, gluten free cakes in Mackay, Sarina, Whitsundays, Airlie Beach and Moranbah

name: Loulou Bistro Boulangerie & Traiteur
homepage_content: Bistro • Boulangerie • Traiteur • Café Milsons Point • Martin Place Honest French food – from classic bistro dishes to freshly-baked breads, viennoiserie and wine – that’s the heart of Loulou. Our vision comes to life across two Sydney locations: our original Bistro, Boulangerie & Traiteur nestled in the neighbourhood charm of Milsons Point, and our Petit Loulou café and 130-seat bistro amid the sophisticated pulse of Martin Place, in Sydney’s CBD. Each venue channels the spirit of Parisian classics, European delis, and New York’s contemporary bistro scene. From morning croissants to evening aperitifs, discover your perfect Loulou moment at our locations. Loulou Bistro Milsons Point BOOK NOW VENUE DETAILS A neighbourhood French bistro in Lavender Bay where classic fare meets local charm. Intimate dining, bar snacks, Champagne and Burgundy, alongside signature plates like fruits de mer and steak frites. From lunch to late evening. Boulangerie & Traiteur Milsons Point SHOP NOW STORE DETAILS Baking four times daily, we offer fresh bread, croissants and other viennoiserie with a menu consisting of classic baguettes, miche loaves, and sweet treats. Weekend specials feature an expanded selection of pastries to be enjoyed alongside our fresh coffee. Our takeaway section has gourmet meals from Toulouse sausage, terrines, rotisserie chickens, and artisan products. Your local French bakery, bringing European flavours to Milsons Point. Petit Loulou Martin Place SHOP NOW STORE DETAILS A bustling kiosk-style café bringing Paris to Martin Place. Fresh French croissants, viennoiserie, rotisserie chicken baguettes, and Loulou’s famous sausage rolls—perfect for takeaway or quick dining. Centrally located in the CBD, at the Hunter & Elizabeth St Metro exit. Loulou Bistro Martin Place BOOK NOW VENUE DETAILS Loulou Martin Place evokes the relaxed bistros of Paris and New York, just like its Milsons Point sibling. The bistro and bar flows over two levels and spills out along Elizabeth Street, the perfect Parisian-style vantage point for people watching. Open for breakfast, lunch and dinner the menu reflects Loulou’s signature style – a lighter take on contemporary and classic French dishes, inspired by the south of France. Reservations We take reservations for our Bistros. Stop by anytime and experience the hospitality of our Loulou team. Reserve now through the links below: LOULOU BISTRO – Milsons Point 61 Lavender St, Milsons Point NSW 2061 LOULOU BISTRO – Martin Place (cbd) 1 Elizabeth St (Cnr Elizabeth & Hunter St), Sydney NSW 2000 Contact Phone (02) 8000 7800 For general enquiries or reservations: EMAIL MILSONS POINT EMAIL MARTIN PLACE Follow us on Instagram for all our latest news and updates: LOULOU.SYDNEY • LOULOU.BISTROSYDNEY • PETITLOULOU.SYDNEY LE JOURNAL Loulou B&T | Petit Loulou Christmas Special: Bûche de Noël Loulou Bistro Martin Place New Year’s Eve Bookings NOW OPEN! homepage_content: Morris House | Melbourne CBD, Rooftop, Late Nights, Comedy Skip to: Home Content Footer navigation Get $10 off your first order with The Pass - Download the app - bookings functions Make more of the festive season​ Mon – Wed: enjoy a corporate upgrade on us​ Sunday: book with no minimum spend ​ Available on functions held between 24th November – 17th December 2025. ​ T&Cs apply. Enquire Today Enquire Today Welcome to Morris House Sitting on the corner of Exhibition & Little Collins Street, Morris House fuses Melbourne’s love of the arts, city rooftop views and good food & wine across four levels.Visit the NYC-inspired basement for Melbourne’s best live comedy shows, enjoy a meal in the dining room, meet friends for after-work drinks & live music on level one, and finally, reach the leafy-green rooftop for city views and settle in for sociable snacks and nostalgic signature cocktails. Would you like to… Book a table View the menu Make an enquiry Purchase a voucher Sitting on the corner of Exhibition & Little Collins Street, Morris House fuses Melbourne’s love of the arts, city rooftop views and good food & wine across four levels.Visit the NYC-inspired basement for Melbourne’s best live comedy shows, enjoy a meal in the dining room, meet friends for after-work drinks & live music on level one, and finally, reach the leafy-green rooftop for city views and settle in for sociable snacks and nostalgic signature cocktails. Dining Room The Ground Floor Dining Room serves up a seasonal produce-driven menu, centered around tasty plates to share between friends. By day, dine on loaded bagels and burgers; by night, top-quality cured meats, tasty share plates and reimagined pub classics. See the menu Level One Whether you’re here to meet for after-work drinks, to dine with friends, or to let your hair down, the Level One Bar & Terrace is for good vibes and good fun. Complete with comfy booths and a sunny outdoor terrace, head on up for live music, on every weekend. Book a spot Rooftop An open-air oasis in the heart of the city, head to the Rooftop for share-friendly plates alongside a complementary selection of easy-drinking wines, beers and spirits. Our signature cocktails are a playful mix of nostalgic classics reimagined (iced-vovo margarita, anyone?) plus a nod to classic New York heroes with a Melbourne twist. HEAD ON UP Come in and say hello! Trading Hours Monday – Thursday: 11.30am – 11pm Friday – Saturday: 11.30am – late Sunday: 11.30 – 10pm Return to top Privacy Policy Terms & Conditions Responsible Service Site by Sod Our Basement Comedy Club is accessible via stairs and a wheelchair lift, which provides access from the ground floor entrance on Exhibition Street. Please note that large, motorised wheelchairs may not be suitable for this lift, please contact our team to confirm whether the wheelchair lift will be suitable for your visit. The Ground Floor Dining Room, Level One Bar and Rooftop are only accessible via stairs. We apologise for any inconvenience this may cause. homepage_content: Food, shops and services | Royal Brisbane and Women's Hospital Home / Patients & visitors / Food, shops and services Food, shops and services Ian 2025-09-15T14:59:29+10:00 Food, shops and services On this page The hospital has a range of shops and services for people to access. Cafes, food and drink outlets on campus are available for visitors and staff to purchase meals and refreshments. More than 8 000 people come to Royal Brisbane and Women’s Hospital each day. Patients who stay in hospital are served their meals at regular times each day. Cafes, food and drinks Please provide Feedback about our food services . Café Royale Location: Level 1 Ned Hanlon Building Open: Monday-Friday 7.00am-6.00pm and weekends 7.00am-4.00pm Hot food Salads Sandwiches Sweets Snacks Cold drinks Made to order Prepacked Seating Café Lattes Location: Level 1 Ned Hanlon Building Open: Monday-Friday 7.00am-6.00pm and weekends 7.00am-4.00pm Coffee Sweets Prepacked Seating Subway Location: Level 1 Ned Hanlon Building Open: Monday-Friday 8.00am-6.00pm and weekends 9.00am-4.00pm Phone: (07) 3636 0821 Sandwiches Salads Sweets Snacks Cold drinks Made to order Seating Catering available Online orders are also available. Choose store location for collection – “1320” Food Ct/Butterfield St, Royal Brisbane Women’s Hospital, Herston, QLD 4029, AUS. Coffee Clinic Location: Level 1 Atrium (Between Ned Hanlon Building and Dr James Mayne Building) Open: Monday-Friday 6.00am-1.30pm Light meals Sweets Snacks Coffee Cold drinks Prepacked Seating Coffee Cube Location: Level 6 Ned Hanlon Building Open: Monday-Friday 6.00am-1.30pm Light meals Sweets Snacks Coffee Cold drinks Prepacked No seating 2C Coffee Cart Location: Level 4 Joyce Tweddell Building Open: Monday-Friday 7.00am-2.30pm Light meals Sweets Snacks Coffee Cold drinks Prepacked No seating City Pantry – Open All Hours Location: Level 1 Atrium (next to Coffee Clinic) Open: 24 hours a day 7 days a week Light meals Snacks Vending machine Prepacked Seating Fresh fruit and meals that can be served cold or heated in the supplied microwave. homepage_content: Mya Tiger | St Kilda Restaurant & Dining at Hotel Esplanade Skip to: Home Content Footer navigation - Welcome to Mya Tiger Up the ornate stairs beneath a glittering chandelier at the Hotel Esplanade, you will find Mya Tiger, a fast-paced, flavour-filled Cantonese restaurant serving up inspired cocktails, dumplings, Peking duck and epic sunsets. Mya Tiger offers a welcoming and warm setting, inspired by the Chinese cook-shops that sprang up throughout St Kilda during Victoria’s 1850s gold rush era. With spanning views of St Kilda bay & the city, a jam-packed beer & wine menu curated to match the designed to share menu, you have all the ingredients for a fun-filled Cantonese adventure. name: Darwin Fisherman's Wharf Eatery
homepage_content: myDarwin | City of Darwin | Darwin Council, Northern Territory Skip to main content The myDarwin program is currently closed. City of Darwin thanks you for your participation of the initiative. The myDarwin economic stimulus is an initiative to provide support to local businesses and community residents through digital discounts. It was designed for local businesses in retail, tourism, and hospitality who were affected by closures, social distancing measures, and restricted hours of trade-related to the COVID-19 pandemic. myDarwin success in a snapshot As of April 2022, the myDarwin program has completed 10 rounds of funding which resulted to an average 5.7 multiplier effect into the local economy. Key statistics to date are: 476 Merchant registrations 343 Approved Merchants 54,433 User registrations 141,491 Discounts Redeemed $1,750,000 Funded Discounts $9,906,948 Economic Spend in local Businesses (x5.7 multiplied spend) Due to its success the Northern Territory Government has provided $1 million in funding for the myDarwin web application to be extended to other councils in the Northern Territory. This resulted in the creation of a white label version of myDarwin web application which can be used independently by other councils. The following councils have rebranded and implemented their version of myDarwin with shared success. In the Northern Territory: Alice Springs Council Palmerston Council Litchfield Council Katherine Council Barkly Regional Council In the Australian Capital Territory: Canberra’s ACT Government Discover more interesting facts about the myDarwin success and economic impact in YourDARWIN platform.
