homepage_content: Sealanes | Fish + Chips FUSION KITCHEN EXPLORE . DREAM . TASTE . FOLLOW US morsel@yourdomain.com +88(0)101 0000 000 Sealanes Fish and Chips offers not only the best quality classic fish and chips, but a range of seafood items to suit everyone. Our focus is on producing delicious and fresh local fish and chips, as well as specialty items and seasonal dishes. Our takeaway containers are 100% biodegradable, and is our drink options are 90% plastic-free. Our location Being across the road from South Beach, means you can enjoy your meal in front WA’s amazing coastline, on the beautiful grassed area, or down on the sand. There is also our decked out café area, where you can enjoy your meal. Something for everyone We love kids and dogs, so have made the area perfect for both! We have an activity area for kids, plus a water station for dogs – we just ask that you please keep them on their lead, much to their dismay.. the dogs that is! Make sure you follow us on Facebook and Instagram to see what’s on special! We’re open Tuesday to Sunday, 12pm – 8pm. Fish + Chips Menu

name: Sweet Caramel
homepage_content: Sweet Caramel Bathurst Skip to content Takeaway Lunch Tue to Sun 11am till 3pm Trading Hours | Tuesday - Sunday 9am - 3pm Item added to your cart View cart Check out Continue shopping Order Take Away's Trading Hours | Tuesday - Sunday 9am - 3pm View Menu Takeaway Lunch and Dinner Order Now 1 2 Indulge in a culinary journey at Sweet Caramel Where every meal is a delightful experience. Nestled in the heart of Bathurst, NSW, Australia, Sweet Caramel invites you to savor the flavors of the day from breakfast till lunch. Begin your morning with a sumptuous breakfast spread, featuring lovely pancakes and freshly brewed coffee. High Teas Our High Tea service is a celebration of elegance, presenting a delectable array of delicate pastries, scones, and artisanal teas. As twilight descends, Sweet Caramel transforms into a haven for dinner enthusiasts, offering an enticing menu of culinary delights crafted with locally sourced ingredients. From succulent steaks to seafood sensations, our dinner offerings promise to tantalise the taste buds and leave you craving more. For High tea bookings, please contact 02-6331-0535 Sweet Caramel Bathurst Located at 185 George St, Sweet Caramel beckons you to experience a culinary haven where every bite is a symphony of flavors and every moment is savored. Discover the essence of exquisite dining at Sweet Caramel, where indulgence meets excellence. name: Shisha Basha
homepage_content: Shisha Basha - Craigieburn Order now About Us At Shisha Basha, we're passionate about sharing the flavors of the Middle East. Our menu features all your favorite dishes, alongside some hidden gems we know you'll love. We use only the freshest, high-quality ingredients, replicating the authentic tastes we grew up with. Our menu is designed for sharing, perfect for bringing friends and family together for a memorable meal. Enjoy mezze plates, aromatic shisha, and delicious food in a welcoming atmosphere. Shisha Basha offers more than just exceptional cuisine. We create a unique and vibrant ambiance that you won't find anywhere else in Melbourne. Our dedicated team provides impeccable service, ensuring you have a relaxing and enjoyable experience. Immerse yourself in the atmosphere with live music, top-quality shisha, and delectable dishes. It's the perfect place to unwind, connect with loved ones, and create lasting memories. We cater to all your dining needs. Enjoy a delicious meal in our restaurant, or let us bring the flavors of the Middle East to your next event. We offer catering services for small gatherings, ensuring you can share our authentic cuisine with loved ones at your own table. Come experience our warm hospitality and embark on a culinary journey through the rich flavors of the Middle East. Featured Items View Menu Delivery Areas Broadmeadows Dallas Jacana Coolaroo Meadow Heights Attwood Westmeadows Greenvale Campbellfield Somerton Craigieburn Roxburgh Park Epping Wollert Dear Customers, Thank you for ordering directly, and supporting local business. We are committed to hiring locals and using as much local producers as possible. Team Shisha Basha

name: Royal Khalsa Bakery Truganina
homepage_content: Royal Khalsa Bakery - Truganina Discover Royal Khalsa Bakery Truganina Opening Hours Order Online Cake Menu Custom Cakes Choose Craigieburn Our Story About Us Welcome to Royal Khalsa Bakery, the ultimate destination for eggless cakes. Since our inception in 2012, we've been on a mission to satisfy the growing demand for egg-free cakes in Craigieburn, Reservoir, and Truganina. Our commitment to quality has made us a popular choice for those who are looking for delicious cakes that are made using high-quality ingredients and are free from eggs. At Royal Khalsa Bakery, we take great pride in the quality of our cakes. From classic sponge cakes to rich chocolate cakes, we offer a diverse range of flavors to suit all tastes. Our cakes are made fresh to order, and we use only the finest ingredients to ensure that each cake is of the highest quality. If you have a special occasion coming up, we can create a custom cake design that's tailored to your needs. Our experienced cake designers can bring your vision to life and create a cake that's not only beautiful but also delicious. We understand that some of our customers may have dietary restrictions, which is why we offer a range of vegan and gluten-free options. Our vegan cakes are made without any animal products, and our gluten-free cakes are made with gluten-free ingredients, ensuring that everyone can enjoy our delicious cakes. Whether you're looking for a cake for a small gathering or a large event, we've got you covered. We can cater for large events and parties and offer delivery services to make things easier for you. We're always experimenting with new flavors and designs, so be sure to check our website or follow us on social media to stay up-to-date with our latest offerings. homepage_content: Museum of the Great Southern | Western Australian Museum Skip to main content Museum of the Great Southern Residency Road, Albany What's on Exhibitions Visit us Residency Road, Albany, WA, 6330 Get directions on Google Maps > Plan your journey by public transport > Opening hours Open daily 10am – 4pm Public holiday hours Anzac Day 1pm – 4pm Closed Christmas Day, Boxing Day, New Year's Day & Good Friday General Admission Free General Admission entry Donations are welcome Some special exhibitions and events may charge a fee Information for educators > Contact us (08) 9841 4844 reception@museum.wa.gov.au ‌‌ ‌‌ ‌‌ ‌‌ @wamuseum Accessibility The Museum of the Great Southern is mostly accessible A lift is available for access to the mezzanine floor in the Eclipse gallery space, but not for access to the Brig Amity More about accessibility and amenities > Explore the unique natural and social history of the Great Southern region. The Museum of the Great Southern precinct overlooks picturesque Mamang Koort / Princess Royal Harbour on the site of the first European permanent settlement in Western Australia (1826). Here you will find permanent and travelling exhibitions, a replica of the Brig Amity , pop-up artworks, public and educational programs, and information on the natural and social history of the region. The Museum shares the stories of the Menang Noongar people and the influence of Mokare, an intermediary who assisted European explorers in an unfamiliar environment. It also explores the region's unique landscapes, flora and fauna. What's on at Museum of the Great Southern Special exhibitions Men of the Kokoda Explore the story of Brigadier Arnold Potts and the 21st Brigade of the Second AIF, whose actions during the defence of the Kokoda Trail during WWII became some of the most debated in Australia’s military history. Museum of the Great Southern Saturday 18 October – Sunday 23 November 2025 Saturday 18 October – Sunday 23 November 2025 Activities & workshops Crochet Circle Join our Crochet Circle, a relaxed gathering of women who loves to crochet or wants to learn. Museum of the Great Southern Wednesday 26 November 2025 Wednesday 3 December 2025 Wednesday 26 November 2025 | 9.30am - 12pm Wednesday 3 December 2025 | 9.30am - 12pm Special exhibitions Transition: Viewpoint artists & Lorraine Harrison 3D Youth Prize See exhibited works of art, part of the Lorraine Harrison 3D Youth prize. Museum of the Great Southern Saturday 29 November – Friday 12 December 2025 Special exhibitions Albany Then & Now: Historical Panoramas of Menang Noongar Boodja Step into Albany’s past and present through panoramas spanning more than a century. Museum of the Great Southern Friday 12 December 2025 – Monday 1 June 2026 Special exhibitions Bound & Unbound - Encyclopedias Re-imagined Local artists celebrating Albany and its rich culture and history. Museum of the Great Southern Monday 12 January 2026 Tuesday 21 January 2025 Monday 12 January 2026 | 10.30am - 12.30pm Wednesday 21 January 2026 | 10.30am - 12.30pm Activities & workshops Mexican cooking workshop: Cocinar la comida! Learn simple techniques to create cheesy quesadillas, a tangy guacamole dip with corn chips, and finish with a festive Piñata cupcake. Museum of the Great Southern Tuesday 13 January 2026 Tuesday 20 January 2026 Tuesday 13 January 2026 | 10.30am - 12.30pm Tuesday 20 January 2026 | 10.30am - 12.30pm Activities & workshops Junior program: Little explorers Mexican playdate Enjoy the colour and fun of Mexico in this activity rich early years program. Museum of the Great Southern Wednesday 14 January 2026 Monday 19 January 2026 Wednesday 14 January 2026 | 10.30am - 12pm Monday 19 January 2026 | 10.30am - 12pm Activities & workshops Workshop: Frida’s Reflection Create vibrant, Frida Kahlo-inspired art exploring self-expression through mixed media on canvas. Museum of the Great Southern Thursday 15 January 2026 Thursday 15 January 2026 | 10.30am - 12pm Activities & workshops Workshop: Vistoso Niche memory box Design and personalise your own Nicho, a traditional Mexican memory box, to decorate your home. Museum of the Great Southern Thursday 22 January 2026 Thursday 22 January 2026 | 10.30am - 12.30pm Explore all exhibitions and programs More to explore at the Museum Exhibitions Discover our State’s rich cultural and natural heritage through our permanent and special exhibitions. Education at the Museum Explore our range of facilitated education programs and self-guided trails for educators and students. Resources Explore the history of the Great Southern with these resources from the Western Australian Museum. More information to help plan your visit Accessibility and amenities Access within Museum All galleries have level flooring. Level 2 of the Eclipse building is only accessible via elevator. ACROD Parking Main Museum carpark. Two large bays available. Level access. No barriers. Free (no cost). Audio Guides Available on the Brig Amity . Captioning Not available. Drop Off Area Main Museum carpark. Drop off in front of Eclipse Building or Residency Building. Level access. No barriers. Entry to Museum Accessible path from parking and drop off area to Museum entry. Small ramp leading down to Eclipse Building entrance, small ramp leading up to Co-op Building and School Room. No stairs to either main entrances. All entrances level. All doors manual opening. Equipment Available One manual wheelchair available for use. Hearing Loops No hearing loops available. Reception The reception desk is located in the Eclipse Building on the ground floor, immediately inside the doors. Share Paths The Museum is central located in Albany and easily accessible by walkers and cyclists using Albany’s extensive network of Share Paths. The Albany TravelSmart Map shows all the available paths. Albany TravelSmart Map [PDF 2MB] Storage Please be aware that the Museum of the Great Southern does not have cloaking facilities or bag storage areas. As a consequence, luggage and bags should not be taken into the Museum. Toilets The site does not have universal access toilets. If required urgently, there is access to a larger, handled toilet within the staff administration area. Trained Guide or Assistance Dogs Visitors accompanied by a Trained Guide or Assistance Dog or a dog undergoing such training are welcome in this site. Getting here, public transport and parking Address Museum of the Great Southern Residency Road, Albany, Western Australia, 6330, Australia Get directions on Google Maps > By Car Parking is available in onsite. By Bus The Museum of the Great Southern is located within walking distance of the town centre, which is serviced by the several bus services, plan your journey by public transport > Subscribe to be the first to know about all the latest in exhibitions, events, discoveries and much more! Join us for our free Barista Courses webinar. Click here to join a session now. Barista Basics - Training Value Packages All our barista courses are nationally accredited. SITXFSA005 Use hygienic practices for food safety is included with our courses at no charge. Your coffee education starts here. Select any of our world class training courses below: Barista Basics Accredited 3 Hrs This is a 3-hour barista experience that actually teaches you how to identify all the key variables that go into making espresso-based coffee... Learn more Barista Basics Accredited 5 Hrs This is a 5-hour barista experience that actually teaches you how to identify all the key variables that go into making espresso-based coffee... Learn more ​(Sydney Only) ​(Sydney Only) (Sydney Only) Welcome to Barista Basics Coffee Academy If you are a student, a barista or simply a coffee fanatic and if it’s nationally accredited courses you are looking for, you have come to the right place. name: BTWN
homepage_content: Darling Harbour Restaurant | BTWN at W Sydney Skip to main content menu open HOME MENUS ABOUT PRIVATE DINING ROOM 2AM: DESSERTBAR OFFERS AND EVENTS GALLERY GIFT VOUCHERS CONTACT AND LOCATION Get Notifications Facebook Facebook Instagram Instagram Reserve now booking widget MADE TO SHARE A DYNAMIC DINING EXPERIENCE CELEBRATE NATIVE INGREDIENTS Next 1 / 3 Play Pause Slider BTWN BTWN Embracing its dynamic location 'between' sweeping expressways, this hotel restaurant in Sydney evolves and transforms as the day unfolds to an ever-changing backdrop of Sydney's Darling Harbour. The dining experience moves ‘between' spaces and experiences, as you share in dishes that reflect the season and the region, with a menu celebrating locally sourced ingredients from ‘between the borders' in NSW. BTWN HOURS' Celebrating native ingredients with a meticulously designed drinks list, BTWN Bar delivers zeal and zest to any social soiree. Join us at BTWN Bar from 5PM - 6PM Monday to Saturday for BTWN Hours' to experience a special offer on beverages whilst savouring bite-sized shared snacks. BOOK NOW 2AM: DESSERTBAR BY JANICE WONG Step into a world where art meets dessert. The new 2am: dessertbar menu at BTWN is a feast for the senses, featuring exclusive creations by Janice Wong that blend Singaporean flair with locally sourced Australian ingredients. From the bold Chilli Chocolate to the refreshing Green Garden, every dish is handcrafted and paired with thoughtfully curated cocktails or non-alcoholic sips. RESERVE NOW A TASTE OF THE CITY BTWN revolves around the joy of sharing, allowing the finest local ingredients to tell their stories on the plate. Ranging from small bites to substantial dishes, the new menu embraces shared dining with bold and modern takes on autumal flavours for a journey of taste that's as exciting as it is sustainable. See Menus DYNAMIC DINING IN MOTION Inspired by airstream food trucks, a series of curvilinear pods lead into the main dining space, each with its own culinary journey that changes throughout the day to create a vibrant dining destination on the Harbour's edge. Discover BTWN Previous Slide Next Slide View Offers STAY IN THE KNOW Learn more about upcoming offers and events at BTWN. SIGN UP × THE BTWN CHRISTMAS TABLE Forget ordinary roasts, celebrate Christmas BTWN-style high above the buzz of Darling Harbour. Book Now All Day Dining Reservations: 61290720090 Close Hours BTWN RESTAURANT IN SYDNEY CITY Tues - Sun 6PM - 10PM 2AM: DESSERTBAR Tues - Sun 6PM - 10PM BTWN BAR Mon - Sun 5PM - 10PM SEE MENU

homepage_content: Arena Joondalup | Your local sporting, fitness and entertainment hub Skip to main content What's on today? 50m pool closed. The 50m pool is closed and construction of the new pool has commenced. Read here for the latest updates on the project. 1 What's on today? Arena Cup Registrations Open Arena Cup is here! Mixed Netball and Ladies Soccer have limited space, it's not too late to register. Register now Laneway Festival Laneway Festival 2026 has officially landed, and in its 21st year, is coming to Arena Joondalup on 15 February, headlined by Chappell Roan! Tickets now on sale. Find out more Wildlands Something bold awaits you this summer. Wildlands returns to Arena Joondalup on Saturday 3 January 2026. Find out more Summer fun starts here! Prepare to make a splash this summer - starting with swimming lessons this spring! Learn more Click to see slide 1 Click to see slide 2 Click to see slide 3 Click to see slide 4 Leisure Pool Closed to Public Saturdays 8am-11:30am On Saturdays, the Leisure Pool is reserved for Swim School customers only from 8am to 11:30am and is not accessible to the public or casual lap swimmers during this time. See more Lane Availability here. Show more Jump straight in Class Timetable With over 100 group fitness classes on offer, find the perfect one to match your goals today Learn more Class Timetable Lane Availability Plan your visit and find the ideal time for your swim Learn more Lane Availability Social Sports Explore competitive social sport in Joondalup, with indoor futsal and netball all year-round and outdoor soccer and netball over spring and summer. Learn more Social Sports The premier sporting, fitness and entertainment hub for Perth’s northern suburbs A modern gym with a dedicated group fitness studio, crèche, café and function spaces are all located inside the venue. Venture outside to find dedicated tennis courts, hockey pitches, rugby fields and netball courts surrounded by lush gardens. Our family leisure pool was recently renovated, featuring a waterslide, toddler area and lanes. The 50m competition pool is not available and will open in early 2026. Explore our venue facilities Swim, train and play We've got a range of services available with flexible options to suit your needs. Become a member or visit on a casual basis. Gym Swim Social Sport Gym People of all ages, sizes and fitness levels are welcome to enjoy our gym facilities and classes. Next group fitness class: Fetching next class information... View the group fitness timetable Swim Our renovated family leisure is open, however the 50m competition pool is currently closed for renovations until early 2026. Current swim lane availability: Fetching pool availability... See more on the leisure pool reopening Social Sport While competitions can be competitive, social sport is all about the fun, hanging out with friends or meeting new ones, sharing a laugh and keeping fit at the same time. Enjoy mixed netball, indoor futsal and outdoor soccer at Arena Joondalup. Explore our social sporting competitions Venue hire Discover the variety of facilities and spaces available for hire at Arena Joondalup. name: Bunbury Regional Art Gallery
homepage_content: BRAG | Exhibitions & Events in City Of Bunbury WA Skip to main content City of Bunbury Our Websites https://www.bunbury.wa.gov.au/bunbury-brighter https://www.bunbury.wa.gov.au/sports-centre https://www.bunbury.wa.gov.au/wildlife-park https://www.bunbury.wa.gov.au/libraries https://www.bunbury.wa.gov.au/museum https://www.bunbury.wa.gov.au/brag Contact Art in the heart of Bunbury. Enriching lives through meaningful engagements with art, the environment and Aboriginal culture, and researching, exhibiting, and preserving the legacy of artists practicing in Australia's South West. Current Exhibitions BRAG's program of flagship events and touring exhibitions includes the work of WA, national and international artists. Find out more about what's on now! Learn more Visiting BRAG Open to the public from 10am-4pm Wednesday to Sunday, and by appointment for group bookings, a visit to BRAG is one of the top things to do in Bunbury. Learn more Glow: Creative and Connective Moments Discover a diverse suite of experiences that foster deeper connections and creative moments for parents and caregivers of new babies. Learn more Noongar Arts Program BRAG’s Noongar Arts Program celebrates the dynamic work of Noongar artists of the South West; the NAP Shop showcases original pieces created here on Wardandi Country. Learn more Latest events 15 Oct After School Art Classes | Creative Kids Term 4 (6-8yrs) 04:00 PM - 05:30 PM Bunbury Regional Art Gallery 15 Oct After School Art Classes | Tween Visions Term 4 (11+yrs) 05:30 PM - 07:30 PM Bunbury Regional Art Gallery 16 Oct Mums and Bubs in the Gallery (0-24 months) | Term 4 10:15 AM - 10:45 AM Bunbury Regional Art Gallery 16 Oct Mums and Bubs in the Gallery (2-5 years) | Term 4 11:00 AM - 11:30 AM Bunbury Regional Art Gallery Events Calendar News and community updates The Launch of BRAG's Artist Incubator Program Iluka Visions 2025 Winners Announced Essential Maintenance Underway for Beloved Public Artwork Read more BRAG News Subscribe to get the latest updates from BRAG Label for newsletter signup Subscribe The Bunbury Regional Art Gallery is owned and operated by the City of Bunbury, with support from the WA Government.

name: Cairns Botanic Gardens.
homepage_content: Botanic Gardens | Cairns Regional Council Botanic Gardens Share Facebook Send In Messenger Send In Messenger Twitter Email The Cairns Botanic Gardens is a tropical paradise, renowned as one of the best exhibitions of tropical plants in Australia. Come and explore the beauty of tropical plants, relax in stunning surroundings and learn about tropical flora and horticulture. Christmas period operating hours The Flecker Botanic Gardens will remain open throughout the Christmas period, and will be open daily from 7.30am to 5.30pm. The Botanic Gardens Visitor Centre will be closed on Christmas Day. It will be open from 9.30am to 2pm on each day from 26 December to 1 January inclusive. Usual opening hours (8.30am to 4pm weekdays and 9.30am to 2pm weekends) will resume on 2 January 2025. The Gardens will remain open throughout the Christmas period. The Flecker Garden will be open daily from 7.30am to 5.30pm. Garden tours: resume Monday 24 February 2025 Bird walks : resume Tuesday 25 February 2025. Plant trolley sales: resume Wednesday 5 February 2025. Heritage Tours : Last tour 12 December 2024, resume 6 March 2025. Friends Shop (Flecker Garden) : closed from 20 December 2024, reopen Monday 13 January (mornings only) Opening hours Flecker Gardens, including Watkins Munro Martin Conservatory, open every day from 7.30am to 5.30pm (subject to weather conditions). All other garden areas are open around the clock. Botanic Gardens Visitor Centre open 8.30am to 4pm weekdays, 9.30am to 2pm weekends and public holidays. No animals are allowed in any part of the Cairns Botanic Gardens (including the Centenary Lakes area), however registered assistance animals are accepted. You may be asked to provide evidence that your dog is a legitimate assistance animal. So please ensure you bring appropriate evidence. Phone 4032 6650 for enquiries Admission is FREE Location Collins Avenue, Edge Hill. The Freshwater and Saltwater Lakes can be easily accessed from Greenslopes Street. On-street parking available along Collins Avenue and Greenslopes Street. Sunbus stops on Collins Avenue directly outside Flecker Gardens. Download a map ( PDF, 0.89 MB ) showing the key features and areas. Wheelchair / pram access: some paths in Flecker Garden are not suitable for wheelchairs and prams. The remainder of the gardens, including Centenary Lakes, is fully accessible. Download the accessibility map ( PDF, 3.57 MB ) or view the accessibility map on-screen ( JPG, 0.94 MB ) to identify areas where carer assist is required and areas that are not accessible. Visit the Gardens Visitor information centre, library, food and volunteer opportunities. Garden areas & collections From the Aboriginal Plant Use Garden to the Zhanjiang Friendship Garden, there's so much to explore in the Cairns Botanic Gardens. One visit is just not enough! Walking tours Discover more about the plants and animals in the Cairns Botanic Gardens on one of our free tours! Events & functions The Cairns Botanic Gardens is the perfect place to hold your next family function or corporate even Birds of the Gardens Come for the flowers, stay for the birds! The Cairns Botanic Gardens is known for its gorgeous plants but beautiful birds also abound here. Little Taccas Fortnightly, nature-based activity program for children under five. Features art and craft, storytelling, sing-alongs and garden discovery walks. Little Sprouts Registrations are open for the Term 4 Little Sprouts program. This program fills quickly so register now so you don’t miss out. name: Springwood Aquatic and Fitness Centre
homepage_content: Leisure Centres | Blue Mountains City Council Skip to main content Blue Mountains Leisure Centres Leisure Centres To purchase a membership via our online system, click on the button below. Please use the Google Chrome browser when using this website. Book now Glenbrook Swim Centre About Glenbrook The Glenbrook Swim Centre is a competition centre opened all year. It offers an outdoor heated 50-metre pool and enclosed heated program pool, for swim classes. Location: Corner Fletcher and Wascoe Streets, Glenbrook Contact: (02) 4780 5987 Email: leisurecentres@bmcc.nsw.gov.au Facilities Heated enclosed program pool with ramp access Heated toddlers’ pool Playground equipment 50-metre heated pool Entry Fees Please see the Outdoor Pools fee brochure . Blue Mountains City Council provides free entry to the aquatic facilities for people 3 years and younger and 75 years and older. Operating hours: Open Year Round! Closed Christmas Day & Good Friday. The centre closes at 5pm on Christmas and New Year's Eve Program pool (year-round) Monday to Friday: 6am - 9am Additional times may be available subject to programs 50m pool Summer (October - March) Monday to Friday: 5.30am – 7pm Weekends: 8am – 7pm Public Holidays: 8am – 6pm 50m pool Winter (April - September) Monday to Friday: 6am – 12pm Tuesday and Thursday: 4 – 7pm Saturday and Sunday: 8am – 12pm Closed on public holidays. Springwood Aquatic and Fitness Centre About Springwood The Springwood Aquatic and Fitness Centre is an indoor multipurpose aquatic, fitness and recreational facility. Location: 11 Plateau Road, Springwood Contact: (02) 4780 5111 Email: leisurecentres@bmcc.nsw.gov.au Facilities Indoor heated 25-metre pool Heated program pool with ramp access Learn To Swim classes Heated leisure pool with children's beach area, huge waterslide and turbo pool Spa, sauna and steam room Fully equipped fitness centre Air-conditioned group fitness room Active Kids Care (Crèche) - Monday, Tuesday and Thursday: Session 1 9:30am -10:30am, Session 2 - 10:30am -11:30am. Wednesday: Session 1 9:30am – 10:30am, Session 2 10:30am – 11:30am, Session 3 11:30am – 12:30pm Entry fees Please see the Springwood Aquatic and Fitness Centre Fee Brochure . Blue Mountains City Council provides free entry to the aquatic facilities for people 3 years and younger and 75 years and older. Operating hours Aquatic Areas Monday to Friday: 6am – 8pm Saturday and Sunday: 8am – 6pm Public Holidays: 8am – 6pm During the Winter season, the 25m Pool closes every second Monday at 7pm for swim club events. At times any of our Aquatic Areas may be closed, if so, please speak to our lifeguards on pool deck to check on reopening times. Casual use of the sports court is available dependent on bookings. Please contact the Centre to check availability. The Centre also offers a tumbling and trampoline program catering for recreational athletes to competitive athletes. Entry fees Please see the Katoomba Sports and Aquatic Centre Fee Brochure . name: Springwood Aquatic and Fitness Centre
homepage_content: Leisure Centres | Blue Mountains City Council Skip to main content Blue Mountains Leisure Centres Leisure Centres To purchase a membership via our online system, click on the button below. Please use the Google Chrome browser when using this website. Book now Glenbrook Swim Centre About Glenbrook The Glenbrook Swim Centre is a competition centre opened all year. It offers an outdoor heated 50-metre pool and enclosed heated program pool, for swim classes. Location: Corner Fletcher and Wascoe Streets, Glenbrook Contact: (02) 4780 5987 Email: leisurecentres@bmcc.nsw.gov.au Facilities Heated enclosed program pool with ramp access Heated toddlers’ pool Playground equipment 50-metre heated pool Entry Fees Please see the Outdoor Pools fee brochure . Blue Mountains City Council provides free entry to the aquatic facilities for people 3 years and younger and 75 years and older. Operating hours: Open Year Round! Closed Christmas Day & Good Friday. The centre closes at 5pm on Christmas and New Year's Eve Program pool (year-round) Monday to Friday: 6am - 9am Additional times may be available subject to programs 50m pool Summer (October - March) Monday to Friday: 5.30am – 7pm Weekends: 8am – 7pm Public Holidays: 8am – 6pm 50m pool Winter (April - September) Monday to Friday: 6am – 12pm Tuesday and Thursday: 4 – 7pm Saturday and Sunday: 8am – 12pm Closed on public holidays. Springwood Aquatic and Fitness Centre About Springwood The Springwood Aquatic and Fitness Centre is an indoor multipurpose aquatic, fitness and recreational facility. Location: 11 Plateau Road, Springwood Contact: (02) 4780 5111 Email: leisurecentres@bmcc.nsw.gov.au Facilities Indoor heated 25-metre pool Heated program pool with ramp access Learn To Swim classes Heated leisure pool with children's beach area, huge waterslide and turbo pool Spa, sauna and steam room Fully equipped fitness centre Air-conditioned group fitness room Active Kids Care (Crèche) - Monday, Tuesday and Thursday: Session 1 9:30am -10:30am, Session 2 - 10:30am -11:30am. Wednesday: Session 1 9:30am – 10:30am, Session 2 10:30am – 11:30am, Session 3 11:30am – 12:30pm Entry fees Please see the Springwood Aquatic and Fitness Centre Fee Brochure . Blue Mountains City Council provides free entry to the aquatic facilities for people 3 years and younger and 75 years and older. Operating hours Aquatic Areas Monday to Friday: 6am – 8pm Saturday and Sunday: 8am – 6pm Public Holidays: 8am – 6pm During the Winter season, the 25m Pool closes every second Monday at 7pm for swim club events. At times any of our Aquatic Areas may be closed, if so, please speak to our lifeguards on pool deck to check on reopening times. Waterslide Weekends: 10am – 2pm School Holidays: 10am – 2pm Fitness Centre Monday to Friday: 6am – 8.30pm Saturday and Sunday: 8am – 6pm Public Holidays: 8am – 6pm Program Pool (open to public during the following times) Monday to Friday: 6am – 9am, 12pm – 3.30pm and 6pm – 8pm Saturday: 12pm – 6pm Sunday: 12pm – 6pm Creche Monday, Tuesday & Thursday: Session 1 - 9:30am – 10:30am, Session 2 - 10:30am – 11:30am Wednesday: Session 1 - 9:30am – 10:30am, Session 2 - 10:30am – 11:30am & Session 3 - 11:30am – 12:30pm Limited spots available – 8 x children per/session (Max. 3 children from 6month -12month. Max. 5 children from 1 - 5 years old). Our creche is a nut free zone. For more information please call Springwood Aquatic and Fitness Centre. Blue Mountains Leisure Centres are closed on Good Friday and Christmas Day. Centres will be open from midday on Anzac Day. Lawson Swim Centre About Lawson The Lawson Swim Centre is a heated, seasonal outdoor swimming centre. Location: St Bernards Drive, Lawson 2785 Contact: Phone: (02) 4759 1458 Email: leisurecentres@bmcc.nsw.gov.au Facilities 50-metre heated pool Heated learners’ pool Heated toddlers’ Pool Playground equipment Aqua aerobics Lawson Swim Centre will run Aqua Aerobics on Saturday mornings at 9am, from 12 October 2024. Entry Fees Please see the Outdoor Pools Fee Brochure . Blue Mountains City Council provides free entry to the aquatic facilities for people 3 years and younger and 75 years and older. Operating hours Lawson Swim Centre opening dates – from Saturday 27 September 2025 until Sunday 5 April 2026. Opening hours are as follows: Mon-Fri: 6am – 6pm Sat & Sun: 8am – 6pm Public Holidays: 8am – 6pm December to February the centre will close at 8pm every day, or 6pm on Fridays and Public Holidays (5pm Christmas and New Year’s Eve). Closed Christmas Day and Good Friday. name: Clover Fresh
homepage_content: Sandwich Manufacturer, Pre-Packed Sandwiches, Baguettes | Clover Fresh Made Just For You Clover Fresh is a Melbourne based fresh sandwich manufacturer specialising in premium pre packed and plattered range sandwiches for the food service industry. Our products include sandwiches, baguettes, pitas, turkish, mini rolls and salads which are made sealed & labeled for retail sale. We supply retail and food service lines to cafés, hospitals, clubs, universities, schools, cruises, airlines, major events and sporting events. Our retail sandwiches are thermally sealed in a wedged container to maintain freshness and safety for your customers. Other products are flow wrapped or presented in a clear clam containers. Why Choose Clover? Local Sourcing ingredients from local businesses which support farming communities and other production businesses in the area, we have been able to achieve the quality and freshness our customers receive every day. Quality As part of our QA system, product and ingredient testing are part of our routine to ensure the highest standard of food safety. We are a HACCP / Spotless accredited facility utilising a certification body to ensure our compliance to regulatory and supplier requirements. Experience We have been in the industry for more than 20 years! Along this journey we have enjoyed creating recipes, lunches, and menu designs for our many retail, corporate and health sector clients. They're Talking About Us! Ferguson Plarre Bakehouses "Ferguson Plarre Bakehouses has been in partnership with Clover Fresh to supply our Sandwiches, Wraps, Toasties and Rolls for over 5years now. Clover Fresh have been more than accommodating to work in partnership with us to bring to market our fresh Signature Range. The quality and freshness of product cannot be faulted and the team at Clover Fresh are always will and able to help at all times. I have personally referred Clover Fresh to other industry colleges." Judd Sandwell, Chief Retail Officer Melbourne Cricket Ground "I’ve been using Clover Fresh for over 15 years across the high volume companies I have worked with. Their food is always fresh, delicious, creative and delivered on time. Most importantly the feedback we receive from our clients is continually positive. Liaising product selection and delivery with their staff is a completely hassle free experience I definitely recommend their service" Shane Freer, Executive Sous Chef Social Responsibility Clover Fresh is committed to positive change and aims to give back to those who need it the most. Here are some of our amazing charities... Clover Clients Get In Touch

name: Discovery Cafe CSIRO
homepage_content: HOME | discoverycafe top of page Discovery Building at CSIRO Acton, A.C.T Open Mon to Fri (closed public holidays) 7.30am to 2.30pm Discovery Café opened in 2014 and offers CSIRO staff and guests delicious food and exceptional coffee with a touch of personality. ​ Situated in the Discovery Centre on the base of Black Mountain opposite ANU, it is a great place to relax and enjoy the glasshouse like feel of the building with views across Acton and up to Mount Ainslie. ​ Open for breakfast from 7:30 to 10:30am and serving lunch from 11am to 2pm there are options to suit everyone. From our gourmet breakfast and lunch menus to hot dishes in the bain marie and of course options for those on the run. ​ Discovery Caf é also provides CATERING for conferences, meetings and events on the CSIRO Black Mountain site. bottom of page

name: Barking Gecko CafÃ© (Cleland Wildlife Park)
homepage_content: Cleland Wildlife Park | The Barking Gecko Café Skip to content The Adelaide Rally is on Friday 21-Sunday 23 November but Cleland Wildlife Park will be open as usual! Access via Crafers open at all times. Access via Greenhill Rd may vary. For road closure information. Dismiss National Parks and Wildlife Service South Australia The Barking Gecko Café The Barking Gecko Café is open daily from 9:30am - 5:00pm (food served 10.00 – 4.00 and coffee 9.30 – 4.30). Entry to the café is free if not entering the wildlife park. We serve a seasonal menu and pride ourselves on sourcing products from the Adelaide Hills. You can grab light lunch or sit down to a delicious hot meal, pairing it with a fresh roasted coffee, or a glass of wine. We’ve even got a kids menu to keep the little ones happy. In hot weather, it’s always that little bit cooler in the Adelaide Hills. Soak up the sunshine in the leafy café garden. You’ll see Superb Blue Wrens and potoroos, and if you’re on the garden lawn at 12.45pm, you’ll catch the Garden Dwellers keeper talk! In winter you can warm up next to our wood fire. The Barking Gecko Café can also host your next corporate lunch or afternoon tea. Find out about our catering packages Read our café menu here Sustainability Commitment: The Barking Gecko Café not only takes pride in providing outstanding food and service, but also supporting our environment. Since 2019 the café has demonstrated best practice in sustainability and proud to be completely landfill free. Actions that we have used to achieve sustainable and landfill free business park wide: We use a commercial local family owned green waste service to divert all waste to become a commercial compost. Our staff educate our visitors about our commitment to divert and sort waste. Any waste that slips though the green or recycle bins are then diverted to become a fuel to power an Adelaide cement business. All takeaway cups, containers, cutlery, and all plastics used in the kitchen are compostable plastic (PLA) made from plants. All single-use refundable plastic bottles, plastic milk bottles and non-refundable plastic containers are separated by staff and sent to Scouts Recycling. PET and milk bottle lids, plastic rings are cut off and recycled in domestic recycle bins. Plastic rings are also snipped so they’re not a threat to wildlife. We have an active worm farm that food scraps are used for, the worms are then used to feed animals within the Park. Such initiatives are only possible through the commitment of all the café staff and have proven so successful the café now features in our education packages on how to operate a sustainable food business! Buy tickets Find us

name: The Essential Grain
homepage_content: Home | Essential Grain Bakery top of page RISING ABOVE THE REST Home: Welcome OUR STORY Background Essential Grain Bakery has been baking our artisan sourdough and specialty breads since 2000. Select participants Adult - 0 + Concession - 0 + Child - 0 + Family (2A+2C) - 0 + Companion Card - 0 + Check Availability Highlighted reviews 5 /5 Based on 5 review s Read all reviews N Nigel Holden about 1 year ago Hard Times Mine Underground Tour in Mount Isa Queensland. A very extensive and interesting tour, tour guide a retired local who had worked in the mines for 50+ years. His knowledge of the equipment and mining kept everyone interested (including the kids) for the 3 hour tour. A well organised and run tour, highly recommended N Neville GREGORY over 1 year ago Informative and enjoyable underground experience.. Enjoyable and informative experience going underground with a former and knowledgeable miner as guide, who related his experiences and stories during the tour. Gumboots, coveralls and the helmet with a light were definitely required to enjoy the hands-on experiences. What you can expect Gain an insight into the world of mining in Australia with an underground tour of the Hard Times Mine in Outback Mt Isa in Queensland. There is no better way to understand the trials and tribulations of miners than on a guided tour with an ex-miner. Listen to the fascinating stories of the good and hard times deep under the earth plus see how tunnels are formed and shaped below the surface. The Hard Mines Underground tour in Mt Isa also gives participants the opportunity to get up close to machinery and try their hand at the air-leg drill under expert guidance. The underground mine tour is recommended for all people 7 years and above and each person will be provided with safety equipment including overalls, hard hats and gumboots. Location 19 Marian Street, The Gap, QLD 4825 What you need to know Inclusions Fully guided walking tour at an underground mine in Mount Isa Group souvenir photo Steel toed gumboots, overalls, hard hats and additional safety equipment Exclusions Transport to/from your home destination or accommodation Meals Highlights Award-winning Hard Times Mine Underground adventure Truly authentic modern mining experience Fully guided walking tour takes visitors 25 metres underground to experience the realities of a miner's working day See huge mining machinery in action and hands on drilling try your hand at the air-leg drill and feel the earth rumble with the firing of the blast face Take home a group souvenir photo Time Tours depart at 9am, 11am and 1pm daily (Closed Christmas Day, New Years Day, Good Friday and Boxing Day) Duration 3 hours in duration Departure Location 19 Marian Street, Mount Isa, Queensland What To Bring A pair of socks Light clothing is highly recommended (preferably shorts and a t-shirt as skirts and dresses are not recommended under overalls) Additional Information A ‘Waiver of Liability’ must be signed by all participants. No cameras are permitted to be taken underground A minimum of 3 people on each tour is required for the tour to operate The minimum age for children is seven (7) years of age Cancellation Policy Amendments or cancellations made less than seven (7) days prior to arrival will incur a 100% cancellation fee Booking Information Confirmation in the form of a tour voucher will be received at time of booking Upon completion of purchase, please print the voucher and present on day of the experience Vouchers can also be presented on your mobile device for this attraction Availability was accurate at the time of booking however, is subject to change due to circumstances out of our control For your information, complete Tour Operator Information including contact details is included on your tour voucher We strongly suggest reconfirming your booking with the tour operator within 24 hours of making your booking and prior to making other travel arrangements Recent reviews 5 /5 Based on 5 review s Photo gallery N Nigel Holden about 1 year ago Hard Times Mine Underground Tour in Mount Isa Queensland. A very extensive and interesting tour, tour guide a retired local who had worked in the mines for 50+ years. His knowledge of the equipment and mining kept everyone interested (including the kids) for the 3 hour tour. A well organised and run tour, highly recommended N Neville GREGORY over 1 year ago Informative and enjoyable underground experience.. Enjoyable and informative experience going underground with a former and knowledgeable miner as guide, who related his experiences and stories during the tour. Gumboots, coveralls and the helmet with a light were definitely required to enjoy the hands-on experiences. Reply from Experience OZ Customer Support Hi Neville, so pleased to see you enjoyed your Outback at Isa, we appreciate the time you have taken to share your experience! V Victoria Vickers over 2 years ago Very knowledgeable presentation from an old-time miner The trip down into the mine was very real. We got to be hands-on with a drill to set a blast. We saw heavy equipment in operation and felt a simulated blasting of the rock wall. This mine is still in operation and pulling our mineral-rich ore and these rock samples were so heavy! Highly recommended! Load More Need help? name: Fremantle Visitor Centre
homepage_content: Fremantle Visitors Centre - City of Fremantle Search the City Clear search field Search filter toggle Search Pages Events Documents News Close search panel Fremantle Visitors Centre The Fremantle Visitor Centre is the official visitor information centre for Fremantle and the true hotspot for visitors to plan their visit. The friendly, experienced staff and ambassadors are local experts and can assist with: Free brochure and maps General tourism information and advice accessibility information guides on events and what’s on free wifi and bike hire information for corporate and conference enquiries Check out the Visit Fremantle website for information about Fremantle including things to do, tours and attractions, hotels and places to stay. Follow @visitfremantle on Facebook , Instagram and Pinterest for all things Fremantle. This facility is accessible. For more information visit the Disability access and inclusion page. Location The Fremantle Visitor Centre is located within Walyalup Koort at 155 High Street, Fremantle. Opening hours Monday to Friday 9am–5pm Saturday 9am–4pm Sunday and public holidays 10am–4pm Closed Good Friday, Christmas Day, and Boxing Day. Fremantle Ambassadors Fremantle Ambassadors are volunteers who provide a friendly face and local knowledge to ensure visitors are able to experience the best Fremantle has to offer. There are three types of ambassadors: Visitor Centre Ambassadors are based at the Fremantle Visitor Centre in Walyalup Koort, 7 days a week, and do a 2.5 hour shift, a least once a week. Roving Ambassadors provide a welcome smile, a map and assistance to visitors at key tourist locations. Roving Ambassadors also play an important role during the cruise ship season (October – April). Roving Ambassadors do a 2 hour shift, at least once a week, 7 days a week. Cruise Ship Ambassadors welcome passengers (during cruise ship season between October and April) from all over the world who are visiting Fremantle for a day (or overnight). Cruise Ship Ambassadors are based at either the Fremantle Passenger Terminal or at the free shuttle stops and do a 2–4-hour shift per cruise ship visit. To become a Fremantle Ambassador, or for more information, please contact the Volunteer Program Officer on 08 9432 9988 or via email at volunteerfvc@fremantle.wa.gov.au Contact us Fremantle Visitor Centre Walyalup Koort, 155 High Street, Fremantle Western Australia 6160 T 08 9432 9988 E info@visitfremantle.com.au Share this page Share on Facebook Share on LinkedIn The City of Fremantle acknowledges the Whadjuk people as the Traditional Owners of the Fremantle/Walyalup area and we recognise their cultural and heritage beliefs are still important today. Our site Connect with us Contact us Back to of the page

Deals Park Info See & Do Groups & Functions Park Features Accessible BBQ Camp Kitchen Conference Facilities Dump Point Family Bathroom Laundry Playground Mini Golf Swimming Pool Bouncing Pillow WiFi Kids Facilities Activity Room Bike/Pump Track Defibrillator Camp Fire (Seasonal) Retail Shop Current Deals Park Info Welcome to Discovery Parks - Hahndorf, right in the heart of the Adelaide Hills, South Australia. Yep, the place where German charm meets Aussie laid-back vibes. Just a 20-minute drive from Adelaide’s CBD, and will transport you into a history-soaked world of pretzels, bratwurst, friendly locals and fine produce. When you're not munching on artisan cheese or savouring some local German grub, why not wander through the picturesque main street? Galleries, quirky shops, and cafes are just begging to be explored. And if that isn't enough, the stunning Adelaide Hills villages and top-notch cellar doors are just a drive away. Got the family in tow? Pick (and taste) juicy strawberries from the famous Beerenberg Farm or forge your own path through the hiking trails and National Parks nearby. Whether you're a couple looking for a cosy getaway, a family ready for an expedition, or friends on a weekend spree, we've got you sorted. From powered campsites to hotel-style rooms, the choice is yours at Discovery Parks – Hahndorf. Discover endless fun when you stay at Discovery Parks - Hahndorf! From thrilling activities to family-friendly events, there's something for everyone. Click here from your mobile to find out more. Campfires are not permitted across our parks from 1 November 2025 - 30 April 2026. Outside of these times, our property managers will monitor local conditions and may under their discretion ban campfires due to the current risk at that time. You may also check with the park team when you arrive if campfires are permitted or banned during your stay. Rising above the valleys in the picturesque Mount Lofty Ranges, the centre is perched atop 32 acres of manicured grounds 800 metres from Hahndorf’s main street. Combine this with incredible food from our on-site 5-star Executive Chef, fully integrated AV solutions, stunning on-site accommodation, break-out room options and event management services and you have every quality and convenience to make your event a huge success in Adelaide. Deals Park Info See & Do Groups & Functions Park Features Accessible BBQ Camp Kitchen Conference Facilities Dump Point Family Bathroom Laundry Playground Mini Golf Swimming Pool Bouncing Pillow WiFi Kids Facilities Activity Room Bike/Pump Track Defibrillator Camp Fire (Seasonal) Retail Shop Current Deals Park Info Welcome to Discovery Parks - Hahndorf, right in the heart of the Adelaide Hills, South Australia. Yep, the place where German charm meets Aussie laid-back vibes. Just a 20-minute drive from Adelaide’s CBD, and will transport you into a history-soaked world of pretzels, bratwurst, friendly locals and fine produce. When you're not munching on artisan cheese or savouring some local German grub, why not wander through the picturesque main street? Galleries, quirky shops, and cafes are just begging to be explored. And if that isn't enough, the stunning Adelaide Hills villages and top-notch cellar doors are just a drive away. Got the family in tow? Pick (and taste) juicy strawberries from the famous Beerenberg Farm or forge your own path through the hiking trails and National Parks nearby. Whether you're a couple looking for a cosy getaway, a family ready for an expedition, or friends on a weekend spree, we've got you sorted. From powered campsites to hotel-style rooms, the choice is yours at Discovery Parks – Hahndorf. Discover endless fun when you stay at Discovery Parks - Hahndorf! From thrilling activities to family-friendly events, there's something for everyone. Click here from your mobile to find out more. Campfires are not permitted across our parks from 1 November 2025 - 30 April 2026. Outside of these times, our property managers will monitor local conditions and may under their discretion ban campfires due to the current risk at that time. You may also check with the park team when you arrive if campfires are permitted or banned during your stay. Thank you for your understanding (08) 8388 7921 145A Mount Barker Road, Hahndorf, SA 5245 Useful Downloads Hahndorf Park Map (568KB) Contact Park First name Last name Email Phone Message See & Do Groups & Functions Discovery Events - Adelaide Hills Convention Centre Located a convenient 20 minutes from Adelaide’s CBD and with capacity for 400+ guests, the multi-award-winning Adelaide Hills Convention Centre offers an unparalleled function centre to host your next conference, corporate incentive, wedding or gala event. Rising above the valleys in the picturesque Mount Lofty Ranges, the centre is perched atop 32 acres of manicured grounds 800 metres from Hahndorf’s main street. Combine this with incredible food from our on-site 5-star Executive Chef, fully integrated AV solutions, stunning on-site accommodation, break-out room options and event management services and you have every quality and convenience to make your event a huge success in Adelaide. Deals Park Info See & Do Groups & Functions Park Features Accessible BBQ Camp Kitchen Conference Facilities Dump Point Family Bathroom Laundry Playground Mini Golf Swimming Pool Bouncing Pillow WiFi Kids Facilities Activity Room Bike/Pump Track Defibrillator Camp Fire (Seasonal) Retail Shop Current Deals Park Info Welcome to Discovery Parks - Hahndorf, right in the heart of the Adelaide Hills, South Australia. Yep, the place where German charm meets Aussie laid-back vibes. Just a 20-minute drive from Adelaide’s CBD, and will transport you into a history-soaked world of pretzels, bratwurst, friendly locals and fine produce. When you're not munching on artisan cheese or savouring some local German grub, why not wander through the picturesque main street? Galleries, quirky shops, and cafes are just begging to be explored. And if that isn't enough, the stunning Adelaide Hills villages and top-notch cellar doors are just a drive away. Got the family in tow? Pick (and taste) juicy strawberries from the famous Beerenberg Farm or forge your own path through the hiking trails and National Parks nearby. Whether you're a couple looking for a cosy getaway, a family ready for an expedition, or friends on a weekend spree, we've got you sorted. From powered campsites to hotel-style rooms, the choice is yours at Discovery Parks – Hahndorf. Discover endless fun when you stay at Discovery Parks - Hahndorf! From thrilling activities to family-friendly events, there's something for everyone. Click here from your mobile to find out more. Campfires are not permitted across our parks from 1 November 2025 - 30 April 2026. Outside of these times, our property managers will monitor local conditions and may under their discretion ban campfires due to the current risk at that time. You may also check with the park team when you arrive if campfires are permitted or banned during your stay. Deals Park Info See & Do Groups & Functions Park Features Accessible BBQ Camp Kitchen Conference Facilities Dump Point Family Bathroom Laundry Playground Mini Golf Swimming Pool Bouncing Pillow WiFi Kids Facilities Activity Room Bike/Pump Track Defibrillator Camp Fire (Seasonal) Retail Shop Current Deals Park Info Welcome to Discovery Parks - Hahndorf, right in the heart of the Adelaide Hills, South Australia. Yep, the place where German charm meets Aussie laid-back vibes. Just a 20-minute drive from Adelaide’s CBD, and will transport you into a history-soaked world of pretzels, bratwurst, friendly locals and fine produce. When you're not munching on artisan cheese or savouring some local German grub, why not wander through the picturesque main street? Galleries, quirky shops, and cafes are just begging to be explored. And if that isn't enough, the stunning Adelaide Hills villages and top-notch cellar doors are just a drive away. Got the family in tow? Pick (and taste) juicy strawberries from the famous Beerenberg Farm or forge your own path through the hiking trails and National Parks nearby. Whether you're a couple looking for a cosy getaway, a family ready for an expedition, or friends on a weekend spree, we've got you sorted. From powered campsites to hotel-style rooms, the choice is yours at Discovery Parks – Hahndorf. Discover endless fun when you stay at Discovery Parks - Hahndorf! From thrilling activities to family-friendly events, there's something for everyone. Click here from your mobile to find out more. Campfires are not permitted across our parks from 1 November 2025 - 30 April 2026. Outside of these times, our property managers will monitor local conditions and may under their discretion ban campfires due to the current risk at that time. You may also check with the park team when you arrive if campfires are permitted or banned during your stay. Rising above the valleys in the picturesque Mount Lofty Ranges, the centre is perched atop 32 acres of manicured grounds 800 metres from Hahndorf’s main street. Combine this with incredible food from our on-site 5-star Executive Chef, fully integrated AV solutions, stunning on-site accommodation, break-out room options and event management services and you have every quality and convenience to make your event a huge success in Adelaide. Yep, the place where German charm meets Aussie laid-back vibes. Just a 20-minute drive from Adelaide’s CBD, and will transport you into a history-soaked world of pretzels, bratwurst, friendly locals and fine produce. When you're not munching on artisan cheese or savouring some local German grub, why not wander through the picturesque main street? Galleries, quirky shops, and cafes are just begging to be explored. And if that isn't enough, the stunning Adelaide Hills villages and top-notch cellar doors are just a drive away. Got the family in tow? Pick (and taste) juicy strawberries from the famous Beerenberg Farm or forge your own path through the hiking trails and National Parks nearby. Whether you're a couple looking for a cosy getaway, a family ready for an expedition, or friends on a weekend spree, we've got you sorted. From powered campsites to hotel-style rooms, the choice is yours at Discovery Parks – Hahndorf. Discover endless fun when you stay at Discovery Parks - Hahndorf! From thrilling activities to family-friendly events, there's something for everyone. Click here from your mobile to find out more. Campfires are not permitted across our parks from 1 November 2025 - 30 April 2026. Outside of these times, our property managers will monitor local conditions and may under their discretion ban campfires due to the current risk at that time. You may also check with the park team when you arrive if campfires are permitted or banned during your stay. Rising above the valleys in the picturesque Mount Lofty Ranges, the centre is perched atop 32 acres of manicured grounds 800 metres from Hahndorf’s main street. Combine this with incredible food from our on-site 5-star Executive Chef, fully integrated AV solutions, stunning on-site accommodation, break-out room options and event management services and you have every quality and convenience to make your event a huge success in Adelaide. Yep, the place where German charm meets Aussie laid-back vibes. Just a 20-minute drive from Adelaide’s CBD, and will transport you into a history-soaked world of pretzels, bratwurst, friendly locals and fine produce. When you're not munching on artisan cheese or savouring some local German grub, why not wander through the picturesque main street? Galleries, quirky shops, and cafes are just begging to be explored. And if that isn't enough, the stunning Adelaide Hills villages and top-notch cellar doors are just a drive away. Got the family in tow? Pick (and taste) juicy strawberries from the famous Beerenberg Farm or forge your own path through the hiking trails and National Parks nearby. Whether you're a couple looking for a cosy getaway, a family ready for an expedition, or friends on a weekend spree, we've got you sorted. From powered campsites to hotel-style rooms, the choice is yours at Discovery Parks – Hahndorf. Discover endless fun when you stay at Discovery Parks - Hahndorf! From thrilling activities to family-friendly events, there's something for everyone. Click here from your mobile to find out more. Campfires are not permitted across our parks from 1 November 2025 - 30 April 2026. Outside of these times, our property managers will monitor local conditions and may under their discretion ban campfires due to the current risk at that time. You may also check with the park team when you arrive if campfires are permitted or banned during your stay. homepage_content: Hebby’s Bakery | Coffee, Cakes & Pies in Gloucester Call 02 6558 1837 Hebby’s Bakery Offers Fresh Pies, Cakes, Coffee & More in Gloucester Contact Us Freshly Baked Sweets & Savouries Come on down to Hebby’s Bakery in Gloucester for a wide selection of cakes, sandwiches, sausage rolls, pies and much more. Need a pick-me-up? How about a fresh cup of coffee or tea? We are a family-owned and operated business, well-known for providing mouth-watering baked goods for customers throughout the Mid North Coast including Forster, Taree and surrounding areas. Our bakers make all of our bread, pies and sweets on-site in our Church Street bakery – making your breakfast or lunch selection a hard one to pick! We even offer catering services and delivery options for customers in Gloucester, Forster and Taree! For a tantalising range of fresh, tasty food options and delicious hot and cold drinks – you can’t go past Hebby’s! Visit our friendly team on Church Street today! Get in Touch Button Get in Touch Button The Mid North Coast’s Best Pies At Hebby’s Bakery, we are famous for our massive range of meat pies, offering 23 different varieties in a huge range of flavours. Our pies are incredibly popular and bring in hordes of returning customers from throughout the Mid North Coast. We often have lines of hungry customers piling out of our doors waiting to get their hands on our tasty pies! All of our pies are baked fresh in our bakery every day. Our selection includes: Steak Bacon & cheese Kidney Curry chicken Chilli Mushroom Tomato & onion & heaps more! Visit our Church Street bakery today to start tasting your way through our tantalising pie menu! We’ve got something for everyone! Get in Touch > Hot & Cold Drinks We serve a huge selection of hot and cold drinks including coffee, tea, juices and soft drinks. Visit our Gloucester bakery today to discover our drinks range! Cakes & Slices We bake a massive selection of delicious cakes and slices in our Church Street bakery every day. From tarts and doughnuts to pastries and birthday cakes—we’ve got you covered! Freshly Made Sandwiches Our friendly team make fresh sandwiches daily from our sandwich bar. We bake our own bread instore and only use high-quality local produce for our fillings. Who We Are At Hebby’s Bakery, we are a family-owned and operated bakery established in Gloucester in 1935. We are a community-oriented business with a great reputation on the Mid North Coast for serving a huge range of tasty food options that’s paired with excellent customer service. Our experienced bakers make all our sweet and savoury goods in our Church Street bakery every day. We serve a range of delicious pies, yummy cakes, sausage rolls and freshly made sandwiches – as well as a massive selection of hot and cold drinks. Hebby’s Bakery has got your hunger cravings sorted. Visit us today! Contact Us Gallery Button Button Button Button Button Button Button Button Get in Touch Visit Hebby’s Bakery in Gloucester for a range of delicious pies, coffee, cakes, sandwiches and more! We bake all our goods in our Church Street bakery every day and take pride in serving high-quality food and drinks to our customers. homepage_content: Veterinary Clinic | Greencross Vets Southport Search for: Search Book Online Find Your Local Greencross Vet Healthy Pets Plus Emergency Services Preventive Care Wellness Dental Checks Parasites Microchipping Vaccinations Blood Tests Medical Care Surgery Desexing Digital X-Ray Ultrasound Clinical Pathology Knowledge & Advice Puppy School Kitten School Nutrition Weight Pet Health Parasite Prevention Flea Prevention Giardia Tick Prevention Zoonotic Diseases Intestinal Worming Heartworm Prevention Common Diseases Dental Disease Diabetes Melitis Kidney Disease Arthritis Common Conditions Bladder Stones Diarrhoea Ear Infections Hip Dysplasia Itchy Skin Vomiting Luxating Patella Pet Articles Dogs Dog Articles Puppy Articles Senior Dog Articles Cats Kitten Articles Cat Articles Senior Cat Articles Other Pets Pocket Pet Articles Bird Articles Careers Careers Vet Nurse Careers Vet Nurse Practical Pathway International Vets Total Care Loyalty Pet Sitting Hello, from Greencross Vets Southport Welcome to Greencross Vets Southport We are your local team of pet care professionals, we are truly ‘passionate about pets’ and we love what we do. We offer a comprehensive range of professional veterinary services to cater for all your pet needs, ranging from preventative health care to weight loss programs through to surgery and diagnostic medicine. Although Greencross Vets is part of a national organisation, our practice is run and managed by a team of dedicated vets, nurses and support staff who understand and value the bond between you and your pet. Our team is committed to offering you and your pet’s exceptional service, and the very best in veterinary medicine and preventative health care. We encourage you to contact us directly should you have any questions about your pet’s health and wellbeing or if you simply want more information about the services that we can provide you and your pets. Our clinic is a new, purpose-built facility in Queen Street Village, with carpark entry available via either Nerang St or Queen St. Book an Appointment Online Our Services. Greencross Vets Southport offer a comprehensive range of professional veterinary services to cater for all your pet care needs utilising the latest diagnostic equipment. View Our Services Desexing Getting your pet desexed (neutered or spayed) is essential to their health. All Greencross Vets facilities are completely sterile and use the latest in surgical equipment. Learn More Vaccinations Prevention is the best medicine. Kitten and puppy vaccinations (injections) and adult pet vaccinations prevent disease. Get your pet’s vaccinations up-to-date. Learn More Heartworm Prevention Heartworm can be hard to detect, but it needn’t be hard to prevent. Greencross Vets recommends year round heartworm prevention. Ask your vet about prevention today. Learn More Dentistry Greencross Vets offer a range of dentistry services like cat and dog teeth cleaning. Consider us your pet’s veterinarian and dentist combined. Learn More X-ray/Radiology Greencross Vets clinics are equipped with high-quality radiograph equipment including X-ray machines, automatic processors, and X-ray view equipment. Learn More Clinical Pathology Clinical pathology allows our vets to analyse and diagnose health conditions. Common laboratory tests include blood tests, urinalysis, faecal tests and biopsy examination. Learn More Laboratory Testing The latest in-house laboratory equipment allows our vets to perform a range of diagnostic tests to achieve accurate, rapid diagnosis of your pets’ health status. Meet The Team Iva Iva Veterinary Nurse Iva completed her Certificate IV in Veterinary Nursing in 2025. Her passion for animal care began in childhood while helping her grandmother care for stray cats in Croatia. This early experience sparked a lifelong dedication to animal welfare, particularly feline care. She has a strong interest in feline nursing, veterinary pathology and emergency care, and aspires to become an emergency Veterinary Nurse. A devoted cat enthusiast, Iva shares her home with four cats—including a lively Bengal—and an American Staffy cross puppy. Outside of her professional pursuits, she enjoys pet sitting and exploring new places on road trips. Melanie W Melanie W Veterinary Nurse Melanie began her career with Greencross Vets in 2023, although her passion for the animal industry began in 2022 when she started fostering cats and kittens. She holds a Certificate IV in Veterinary Nursing and takes great pride in the high standards she sets in her work. Melanie’s professional interests include caring for neonates and overseeing the recovery of hospital and surgical patients. Outside of work, she is a dedicated mother to four boys. Allison Allison Veterinary Nurse Ally is a passionate veterinary technician who graduated from the university of Queensland in 2023. She thrives in fast-paced environments and hopes to pursue a career in emergency. She ensures that every pet receives the highest level of care and making sure your pets get all the love and attention. In her free time, she enjoys traveling and doing outdoor activities. Dr Cian Z Dr Cian Z Veterinarian Dr. Cian grew up in London and returned there after completing his studies to work in a charitable medical practice, where he honed his skills in Emergency Medicine. Relocating to Australia allowed him to transition from the bustling city lifestyle to the tranquility of the beach, all while continuing to dedicate himself to supporting pets and their owners—an opportunity he deeply values. Outside of his professional life, Dr. Cian enjoys long walks, exploring Australia’s natural landscapes, and producing music, in addition to cherishing moments with his beloved cat, Honey. Jessica Jessica Veterinary Nurse Jess’s lifelong love of animals began at a young age while living in the Solomon Islands. She started her nursing career in 2017 with Greencross Gold Coast, working as a locum across various clinics. After taking some time off to focus on her family, Jess was excited to return to working in the clinic. She has a three-legged cat named Mortimor, who is known for being a very cool cat. Dr Taylor A Dr Taylor A Originally from Alaska, Taylor grew up on a small hobby farm. Where she raised a variety of animals from chickens to reindeers. Taylor practiced as an emergency veterinary nurse before making the move to Australia to study for her Doctorate of Veterinary Medicine. She loves the Australian life style and her favourite dogs are Labradors. When she is not at work Taylor likes to spend time with her friends and practice her ukulele. Kirra Kirra Veterinary Nurse Kirra started her journey in the industry when she was in high school, working as a kennel hand in a Townsville based vet clinic. She made the move to the Gold Coast in 2021 and shortly after that she began her studies to become a vet nurse. She is now a Certificate IV Veterinary Nurse and loves all aspects of surgical nursing. When not at the clinic you can find her at the beach or on a long walk with her fur-baby Ruby (Jack Russel). She also loves travelling and exploring the Gold Coast. Dr. John M Dr. John M Veterinary Director Dr. John made the permanent move to the Gold Coast from Durban in South Africa during April 2021 after many years in canine and feline practice. He has a special interest in soft tissue surgery, dentistry, dermatology, pain management and all other aspects of medicine. Dr. John is married to Mareuil and also brought Leah (greyhound cross) and Shimano (whippet) with to the Gold Coast. When not working, he enjoys spending time with family (he has 2 young grandsons) and mountain biking. He appreciates “all things nature” and enjoys birdwatching, hiking, camping and time on the beach. He enjoys being part of the caring Greencross and Southport Team and providing quality care to pets. Anita Anita Veterinary Nurse Anita holds a Certificate IV in Veterinary Nursing and loves all aspects of her job, especially surgical nursing and being an advocate for all fur babies while they stay are patients at Greencross Vets. She likes to keep up to date with best medical practices to ensure that she is always learning and able to provide our patients with exceptional care. When Anita isn’t in clinic, she is busy being a wife and mum to her son, as well as enjoying the company of her fur babies; Eleanor and Shelby. Naomi Naomi Practice Manager Naomi has been working within the Greencross Vets network for a number of years and brings with her a wealth of knowledge about the community. Although she now spends much of her time in an admin and reception role, she continues to love assisting on nursing tasks whenever possible. She especially loves seeing patients go home to their owners after a stay in the clinic. Naomi’s life is filled with animals, her dog Teddy the Staffy who loves to go for walks at the beach, and her two horses Stoka and Sharma. Chloe B Chloe B Veterinary Nurse Chloe began her Vet Nurse training at the young age of 14 through Greencross Vets as school-based trainee and absolutely fell in love with the industry. She has a very strong passion for all aspects of her job, including preventative medicine and having a soft spot for the geriatric patients we see in clinic. Chloe has an older Burmese cat named Leo who loves swimming at the beach with her on the weekends. She currently holds a certificate IV in Veterinary nursing and when she is not in clinic, you can find her surfing, or placed at SeaWorld or Paradise country working with the animals. name: The Greenhouse
homepage_content: The Greenhouse Café Nightcliff Welcome to The Greenhouse Follow Follow Located in the vibrant northern suburbs of Nightcliff, The Greenhouse Café is dedicated to delighting guests with the food they love, crafted with care and served exactly the way you like it. Our menu features a tantalizing selection of dishes and beverages that are as visually appealing as they are satisfying. Committed to supporting local producers, we operate entirely on sustainable electricity and are proud to host the Northern Territory’s first café-based plastic makers space, a small-scale community recycling initiative! By dining with us, you’re not only enjoying exceptional food, you’re helping build a greener, more sustainable future within the local community!  More About Us Discover What Makes The Greenhouse Special View Menu About Us Gallery Our Reviews The Greenhouse Reviews Contact Us Get In Touch With Us Whether you’re booking a table, asking about our menu, or just want to learn more about our sustainability projects, our team is here to help.  admin@greenhousenightcliff.com.au  admin@greenhousenightcliff .com.au  0459 773 994  Shop 2a/40 Progress Dr, Nightcliff NT 0810  Monday - Friday, 7:30AM - 4:00PM

homepage_content: Karma Tea house. Yours Vegan Kitchen Welcome to Karma TEA House Our Productions Explore More Previous Next About Us Karma Tea House Yours Vegan Kitchen Being the best Vegan restaurant in Sydney Karma Tea House, situated on Keira St in Wollongong NSW, stands as a beacon of tradition and health. Embodying the philosophy: "Tea and Vegan dishes bring friends together, forging good bonds atop Wollongong," the establishment came to the city with a mission - to introduce more people to the wonders of Vegan cuisine. Operating on a rigorous schedule, they remain open seven days a week, all year round. At Karma Tea House, meat is strictly off-limits - a testament to their commitment, ensuring guests experience a truly Vegan environment, even barring any outside meat products brought in by customers. Building upon the core essence of Taiwanese Vegan delicacies, after over two years of rigorous experimentation and refinement, the restaurant now proudly showcases a trio of culinary lines: Vegan (VG), Vegan (V, which includes dairy and eggs), and Gluten-Free (GF) - all exuding rich Asian flavors. Additionally, they maintain a strict no-five pungent spices policy in their dishes. Always eager to cater to the local palate, Karma Tea House actively collaborates with local businesses. Through deep partnerships with professional teams, they consistently innovate, introducing dishes that resonate with the local taste. The team passionately hopes to guide more individuals further on their "Vegan journey." Being your second vegan kitch Discover the most comprehensive range of Vegan ingredients and condiments in Australia at Karma Tea House. Catering to the needs of Vegans and those passionate about plant-based diets, we provide an extensive selection to enrich your home cooking experience. Our online store, Karma Sydney Delivery, offers a convenient and hassle-free way to purchase all your Vegan essentials. From novice cooks to seasoned chefs, you'll find everything needed to effortlessly create a variety of Vegan delights. Join us in celebrating the joy of Vegan cuisine and explore the endless possibilities with Karma Tea House. name: Kang Thai
homepage_content: Authentic Thai food in the Bendigo - Kang Thai (Williamson Street) Skip to content DISCOVER THAI Discover authentic Thai food in the Bendigo. We use the fresh high quality local ingredients to create our Thai signature dishes. Order Online Table Reservation Kang Thai (Williamson Street) is known for traditional cuisine with a warm welcoming ambience. We set standards for quality and service through our attention to detail. We established Kang Thai (Williamson Street) to celebrate the delicate ingredients and dishes of our culture. Our menu incorporates modern flavours with traditional, combining to make the perfect dining experience. About us Opening Hours Monday, Wednesday – Friday : 11:00 am – 3:00 pm & 5:00 pm – 9:00 pm Saturday : 11:00 am – 3:00 pm & 5:00 pm – 9:00 pm Sunday : 12:00 pm – 3:00 pm & 5:00 pm – 9:00 pm Tuesday : Closed AUTHENTIC THAI DISHES OUR MENU Appetizer Perfect starters for the family Dessert Fresh made to order signatures Stir fry Traditional recipes served hot Noodles Customer favourites with flavour Order Online Reviews Our average customer rating is 4.9 / 5 "Take it from a Thai person that this is the most authentic Thai food you can find on LI. My husband is American and he can take way more spice than I can and we asked for Thai spicy. I recommend you get homemade coconut ice cream with stick rice at the end of your meal. Awesome staff, clean place and great food!." Poy T Granati "Some of the best Thai good I've had. This is small restaurant serving absolutely amazing dishes. There are only a couple of tables so it is mostly takeout. My favorite is their Pad CU, but everything I've had has been delicious." Lisa Votino Takeaway food & delivery Legend has it you’ll start believing in love at first sight once you see our menu. But don’t take our word for it!
